VALUES
	(1,'Beverage','Beverage --- Mary Elizabeth\'s Christmas Punch','Mrs. John Collier','Makes 1 gal. Or 30 cups\n\n1 ---------- Qt. Pineapple juice\n1 ---------- doz Lemons or Lemon concentrate ( 6 oz. )\n1 ---------- 3 ounce box island pineapple or orange \n                 pineapple jello. This is hard to find, you can \n                 mix flavors.\n2 ---------- cups hot water (dissolve jello in water and \n                 add juice.)\n2 ---------- cups sugar\n3 ---------- cups warm water. \n                 Pour in containers and freeze. Depends on\n                 tempature, take out of freezer about 2 or 3\n                 hours. Place in punch bowl.\n                                   \n                                    Add\n1/4 ------- small bottle almond extract. I don/t always\n                 use this.\n1 ---------- qt ginger ale\n\n                 I use food color to make the punch any color.\n                 I use red for Christmas.\n                 You can freeze small amounts in molds to\n                 to decorate punch',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(2,'Beverage','Beverage --- Lemonade','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- Box Country Time Lemonade. Large size\n                 5 lb. 2.5 oz.\n4 ---------- cups sugar\n4 ---------- gals water\n3 ---------- Lemons sliced thin.\n\n                 You can store Lemonade for several days,\n                 Remove lemon slices, this gives the\n                  Lemonade a bad taste if you leave them \n                  in.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(3,'Beverage','Beverage --- Margarita','unknown','1 ---------- Can Limeade\n1 ---------- Can Tequila\n1/2 ------- Can Triple Sec\n\n                 Put in a blender, Add ice.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(4,'Beverage','Beverage --- Orange Pineapple Slush','Joyce Ferguson','2 ---------- cups suger\n1 1/2 ----- cups boiling water\n2 ---------- 6 oz. cans orange concentrate\n1 ---------- 20 oz can crushed pineapple\n1 ---------- small jar maraschina cherries chopped\n1 ---------- large pkg. frozen strawberries chopped fine\n6 ---------- mashed bananas\n \n                 Ginger ale\n                  For ever qt. of above mixture 1 qt.of Ginger\n                  Ale.Freezes well. Take out of freezer\n                  2 hours before serving.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(5,'Beverage','Beverage --- Pina Cladas','Got this in Hawaii','Serves 3\n\n2 ---------- ozs. Coco Lopez    mix well\n4 ---------- ozs. Pineapple juice\n3 ---------- ozs. Rum, Gin or Vodka\n1 ---------- large cup ice cubes in a blender.\n\n                 Pour over ice and add cherry.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(6,'Beverage','Beverage --- Slushie Punch','Linda Worley','Serves 100 people\n\n5 ---------- cups sugar\n2 1/2 ----- quarts warm water\n8 ---------- pkgs. Kool aid lemonade\n4 ---------- large cans pineapple juice\n4 ---------- 6 ozs. Frozen lemonade\n4 ---------- large ginger ale\n\n                 For different color, add colored kool aid. Mix\n                 all ingredients except ginger ale. Freeze in \n                 half gal.containers. Set out of freezer 2 hours\n                 before serving. Pour ginger ale over at \n                 serving time.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(7,'Beverage','Beverage --- Jello Punch','Martha Murry','2 ---------- large cans 12 oz. constituted orange juice\n2 ---------- large cans 12 oz. lemonade\n2 ---------- small cans 6 oz. limeade\n2 ---------- large cans pineapple juice\n2 ---------- cans apricot nector\n2 ---------- scant cups sugar\n1 ---------- large red cherry or orange slices\n\nMix in quart or pint containers. Freeze until ready to use. Take out of freezer 2 hours before ready to serve. Mix 1 quart ginger ale to 1 quart mix. It\'s better to let mixture get soft before mixing ginger ale.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(8,'Salad','Salad --- Spinach With Feta Cheese & Basil','Faye Thompson','1/2----------- cup olive oil\n1/4 ---------- cup red wine Vinegar\n2    ---------- t. sugar\n1/4 ---------- t. salt\n1/4 ---------- t. pepper\n5    ---------- fresh Basil leaves, chopped\n1    ---------- Garlic clove minced\n\n1    ---------- lb. fresh spinach\n1    ---------- ripe Avocado\n                    peeled & sliced\n1    ---------- cup crumbled Feta Cheese\n1/2 ---------- cup chopped walnuts toasted, or Pine nuts.\n                     Kalamata Olives (Optional)\nCombine first 7 ingredients in a jar. Cover tightly, and shake vigorously. Chill 2 hours. Remove stems from Spinach; wash leaves troroughly, and pat dry; Tear leaves into bite size pieces, if desired. Combine Spinach, Avocado, Feda Cheese, Pine nuts, and Olives, if desired, in a large bowl; toss gently. Pour dressing over salad, and toss gently. Serve immediately. Yield: 10 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(9,'Dessert','Desserts --- Apple Dumplins','Faye Thompson','4 ---------- Apples peeled & halved\n1 ---------- Can refregirated Crescent rolls\n1 ---------- stick butter melted\n1 ---------- Cup Sugar\n1 ---------- Cup Orange Juice\n2 ---------- T. Cornstarch\n\nWrap each apple half in a Crescent roll & place in a baking dish. Mix next 4 ingredients & pour over apples. Bake 350°F oven until bubbly & brown, about 45 minutes. Bake uncovered for about 20 to 25 minutes, Cover with foil until done. They will get to brown if you leave them uncovered the full cooking time.\nThere are other ways you can make this. Instead of orange juice, you can add 1 can of Mountain Dew and a little Cinnamon to taste. The last half of cooking time it\'s bettter to cover dish dish with foil, so it won\'t brown to much.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(10,'Sea Food','Sea Food --- Shrimp Tarragon With Rice','Fay\'s','2 ---------- Tablespoon Butter\n3 ---------- Tablespoons Flour\n1 ---------- can (10 1/4 0zs.) Cream of Celery soup\n1/2 --------  cup Chicken Broth\n1/4 -------- cup Sauterne ( if you use this leave out salt)\n4 -----------Teaspoon Lemon juice\n1/2 --------Teaspoon pepper, salt and onion powder\n1/4 --------Teaspoon Tarragon\n1 ----------- pound raw Shrimp, peeled and deveined\n                  or Crab meat\n                   Pimiento Rice\n\nBlend butter and flour until smooth. Slowly add soup, broth, sauterne, lemon juice, and seasonings. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Add shrimp and cook 5 to 10 minites longer. Serve over Pimiento Rice. Sprinkle with fresh parlsey.\n\nPimiento Rice\n1 ------------ onions chopped\n2 ------------ Tablespoon butter\n3 ------------ cups cooked rice\n1/4 ---------- cup Pimientos, diced\nSaute onions in butter until tender. Add rice and \npimientos, and cook until thoroughly heated.\nServes 6.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(11,'Cakes','Cake --- Pineapple Nut','Mary Jones   Teacher at Parkin','2 ---------- eggs \n2 ---------- cups sugar\n2 ---------- cups flour S. R.\n1 ---------- Teaspoon soda\n1/4 ------- Cup crisco oil\n1 ---------- 20 ounce can crushed pineapple drained\n\nMix eggs and sugar. Add flour, soda, crisco oil & pineapple. Pour in a greased floured 9 by 13 inch\nbaking pan. Bake 350°F oven for 45 minutes.\n\nIceing\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- small can carnation milk\n1 ---------- stick butter\n1/2 -------  cup coconut\n1 ----------  cup chopped pecans\n\nboil until candy reaches 200, stirring constantly. This needs to be a little less than soft ball.Mix 1 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 cup coconut. Ice cake while hot.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(12,'Cakes','Cake --- Fresh Apple','The cheese shop in Stuttgart','2 ---------- Cup Sugar\n2 ---------- Eggs \n3 ---------- Cup Flour\n2 ---------- Cup nuts\n1 1/2 ----- Cup crisco oil\n2 ---------- Teaspoon Salt\n2 ---------- Teaspoon soda\n4 ---------- Cup apples chopped\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla\n\nMix all ingredients by hand, add apples and nuts last. \nBake 350°F for 45 minutes to an hour in a tube pan.\n\nIceing \n1 ---------- stick butter\n2 ---------- Tablespoon milk\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla\n\nEnough powdered sugar to make spreading consistent. Spread cake while  warm. Let drip down sides.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(13,'Sauces','Sauces --- Zesty Cocktail Sauce','Fay\'s','1/4 ---------- Cup ketchup\n1    ---------- Tablespoon lemon juice\n1    ---------- Tablespoon prepared horseradish\n4    ---------- drops tabasco sauce\n                    salt & pepper to taste\n\nMix all ingredients well and chill until ready to serve.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(14,'Pies','Pies --- Apple Pie',NULL,'Double crust apple pie. Serves 8.\n6 ---------- Cups sliced peeled tart apples ( 5 to 6 \n                 medium)\n2 ---------- Tablespoons water\n1 ---------- Tablespoon lemon juice\n1/2 ------- Cup sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup packed brown sugar\n3 ---------- Tablespoons all-purpose flour\n1 ---------- Teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1/4 -------  Teaspoon ground nutmeg\n1/8 -------  Teaspoon ground ginger\n1/8 -------  Teaspoon salt\n2 ---------- Pastry for double crust pie ( 9 inch)\n\nThis is for top of the pie , after the pie is put together ,beat  the following together and spread on top of pie.\n\n2 --------- egg yolk\n3 --------- Tablespoons heavy cream\n2 --------- Tablespoons sugar \n\nIn a saucepan, combine apples, water and lemon juice; cook over medium-low heat just until the apples are tender. Remove from the heat and cool (do not drain). In a large bowl, combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt; add apples and toss to coat.\nLine a 9 inch pie plate with bottom pastry; trim even with edge. Add filling. Roll out remaining pastry to fit top of pie; place over filling. Seal and flute edges. Cut slits in top. Bake at 450°F for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°F; bake 35 to 45 minutes longer or until golden brown. If the edges of the pastry is getting to brown wrap a piece of foil around the outside, to slow down the browings. Sometimes the pastry will brown before the pie is cooked.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(15,'Candy','Candy --- Milk Chocolate Fudge','Kent Thompson','12 ---------- oz. Milk chocolate chips\n1   ---------- Can milk chocolate cake iceing\n1   ---------- Cup minature marshallows\n1/2 --------- Cup chopped nuts\n\nMelt chocolate chips in microwave for 2 minutes Take out and stir. Put back in microwave and cook 2 more minutes, the last 30 seconds put in the marshallows. Take out stir, Mix cake iceing, add nuts and mix well. Spread in a 9 x 9 x 2 inch buttered pan cool until hard enough to cut in small pieces. Do not double the reciipe and cook together at one time, this does not work well in melting the chololate.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(16,'Sauces','Sauces --- Parkin Bar-B-Que Dry Mix','Charles Thomas','1 ---------- Cup plus 2 Tablespoon salt\n1 ---------- Cup plus 2 Tablespoon sugar\n1/4 ------- Cup plus 3 1/2 Tablespoon black pepper\n1/4 ------- Cup plus 2 Tablespoon garlic salt\n1/4 ------- Cup plus 2 Tablespoon m.s.g.\n3 ---------- Tablespoon paprika\n\nRub meat before cooking, and just before finished cooking brush on vinegar.\n\nFor large amounts\n\n1 ---------- Cup salt\n4 1/2 ----- Cup sugar\n1 3/4 ----- Cup +2 Tablespoon black pepper\n1 1/2 ----- Cup garlic salt\n1 1/2 ----- Cup m.s.g.\n3/4 -------- Cup paprika\n\nThis can be mixed ahead of time . Keep sealed in jar.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(17,'Bread','Bread --- Spreads forFrench Bread',NULL,'1 ---------- stick butter\n1/2 -------  lb. Jelapenia cheese\n1 ---------- Cup mayonnaise\n\nMix together, spread on sliced French bread, place in oven on broil until light brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(18,'Salad','Salad --- Pumpkin Seed',NULL,'4 ---------- Teaspoon sherry  wine vinegar or red wine \n                  vinegar\n3/4 -------- Teaspoon ground cumin\n1/4 -------- Cup extra virgin olive oil\n1/8 -------- Teaspoon salt\n1/8 -------- Teaspoon black pepper\n2 ----------- bunches of red tip lettuce, about 12 cups\n3 ----------- medium seedless tangerines, peeled &\n                  sectioned\n1 ----------- medium  red onion thinley sliced\n2 ----------- medium avocados,halved, seeded, peeled\n                  and cut in chunks\n8 ----------- Tablespoon cumin toasted pumpkin seed\n\ncumin toasted pumpkin seed\n1 ----------- Cup raw pumpkin seed or shelled sunflower \n                  seeds\n2 ----------- Teaspoon cooking oil\n1/2 -------- Teaspoon ground cumin\n1/2 -------- Teaspoon salt\n\npreheat oven 325°F rinse pumpkin seeds in water until pulp & strings are washed off, drain. Spread on parchment paper in baking pan. Bake uncovered 1 hr. remove paper, add oil, cumin & salt. Stir to coat. Bake uncovered 10 to 15 minutes or until toasted steering once. Transfer to paper towel to cool.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(19,'Sauces','Sauces --- Salsa','Gaye Smith','2 or 3 ----------- Bell pepper chopped fine\n2 or 3 ----------- onions chopped fine\n2 ----------------- Tablespoon jalopene pepper sliced fine\n1 ----------------- large can hunts tomato sauce 15 oz.\n2 ----------------- cans stewed mexacine tomatoes 15 oz\n2 ----------------- Tablespoon cumin\n2 ----------------- Tablespoon accent\n2 ----------------- garlic powder\n\nchopped everything fine  & cool before serving. This is good served with Tortilla chips.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(20,'Sauces & Gravies','Sauces --- Giblett Gravy','Faye Thompson','4 ----------- Cup chicken or turkey broth\n3 ----------- boiled eggs\n5 or 6 ----- Tablespoon flour, mix with water to make a \n                   paste, strain to get all lumps out\nsalt & petter to taste\nadd  cut parts of chicken or turkey . I use liver & small parts.Use a rich broth.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(21,'Bread','Bread --- Corn Bread','Fay\'s','1 1/2 -------- Cup corn meal mix ( Aunt Jemima self -\n                     rising white)\n1 -------------- Cup Flour ( W. R. Self -rising )\n1/2 ----------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ----------- Teaspoon soda\n2 ------------- eggs\n1 3/4 -------- Cup buttermilk\n3 ------------- Tablespoon shortening for baking skillet.\n\nMelt shortening in a 10 inch iron skillet until hot. Mix \ningredients above. Pour in skillet over hot shortening. Bake in 400 degree oven for 15 or 20 minutes until light brown on top.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(22,'Salad','Salad --- Deborah\'s Salad','Deborah','3 ---------- different types of loose leaf lettuce some \n                  that have red tips look very pretty in this \n                  salad.\n2 ---------- Cup chopped celery\n2 ---------- Cup  green onions chopped\n2 ---------- 6 oz cans mandarin  oranges well drained\n1 ---------- bottle of Briannas real French Vinaigrette\n                 dressing. Add 1 tablespoon sugar. Shake \n                  well.\n\nFirst cut bite size pieces of lettuce in a bowl, add celery, onions, mandarin  oranges, and almonds,just before serving Pour dressing on top. \n\n                 Sliced Almonds caramelized\n\nTo caramelize Almonds. Put about 11/2 cup of sugar in\na skillet, stiring concontinuous. When sugar is melted add almonds. About 8 ozs, cook until dark brown not burned, Pour on a sheet of wax paper, sprayed with Pam. When cool break into small pieces. I like to cook a large batch at one  time, and put them in small plastic bags, enough for 1 salad ( Freeze). This saves a lot of time when you get ready to make a salad. This is everyones favoriate salad.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(23,'Salad','Salad --- Peanut Brittle & Mandarin Orange Salad',NULL,'1/2 ---------- head iceburg lettuce\n1 ------------- head romaine lettuce\n2 ------------- 6 oz ounce cans mandarin oranges\n1/2 ---------- Cup chopped green onions\n1 ------------- Cup celery\n1/2 ----------  box smashed peanut brittle\n\nDressing\n1 -------------- egg\n1/2 ----------- Cup vinegar\n1/3 ----------- Cup granulated sugar\n1 -------------- Cup vegetable oil (Crisco)\n1/2 ----------- Teaspoon salt\n\nChill lettuce, Mandarin oranges, green onions, celery and peanut brittle briefly, but do not allow to sit around. Mix together the dressing ingredients and add to salad.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(24,'Salad','Salad --- Tomato & Cucumber',NULL,'3 or 4 ----------- tomatoes\n1 ----------------- red bell pepper\n1 ----------------- green bell pepper\n1 ----------------- large cucumber\n1 ----------------- red onion\nItalian dressing & Catalina dressing\n\npeel & slice v vegetables .\nUse more of the Italian dressing , and a small amount of the Catalina.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(25,'Dips','Dip --- Curry Dip For Vegetables','Southern Living Cook book','1/2 ---------- Cup mayonnaise\n1 ------------- Cup connercial sour cream\n2 ------------- Tablespoon freshly squeezed lemon juice\n                     salt & pepper to taste\n1 ------------- Teaspoon curry powder\n1/2 ---------- Teaspoon paprika\n2 ------------- Tablespoon minced fresh parsley\n1/2 ----------- Teaspoon dried tarragon, crushed\n2 ------------- Tablespoon grated onion\n2 ------------- Teaspoon prepared mustard\n1 ------------- Tablespoon minced chives\n                     several dashes tabasco sauce\n\nCombine mayonnaise, sour cream, and lemond juice. Blend with all other ingredients. Check seasonings  and chill  overnight before serving. Use as a dip for an assorment of raw vegetables ( caulifower flowerets, sliced raw yellow squash, cucumber slices,celery sticks, carrot sticks, ect.)',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(26,'Salad','Salad --- Popeye','Cecilia Ferguson','12 ----------  Cups  Leaf lettuce or bib spinach\n1 -- ---------  Cup green onions chopped\n1 ------------ Cup tomatoes chopped\n1 ------------ large cucumber chopped\n1 -- --------- Cup radishes chopped\n 1 ----------- Cup carrots chopped\n\nDressing\n1 ------------ Cup crisco oil\n1 ------------ Cup sugar\n1 ------------ Tablespoon salt\n1 ------------ Cup vinegar\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon celery seed\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon black pepper\n\nUse about 1/2 cup dressing to every 12 cups of greens. Put dressing on just before serving, and toss well.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(27,'Beverages','Beverage --- Hot Chocolate','Faye\'s','14 ---------- oz can Eagle Brand Milk\n1/2 --------- Cup Cocoa\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon salt\n\nmix above ingredients and heat. Stir often.\n\n6½ ---------- Cups hot water\n1/2 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 1/2 ------- Teaspoon vanilla\n\nMix with above ingredents, If this is not hot enough , heat until hot , but not boiling. Serve with Whip cream or 1 large  Marshallow per cup.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(28,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Potatoes Hidden Valley Ranch',NULL,'4-6 ---------- red potatoes ( white potatoes can also be \n                     used.)\n1 ------------- stick of melted butter\n1 ------------- pkg. original Hidden Valley salad dressing \n                     mix.\n\nWash potatoes; We like them peeled. Slice crossways. Layer in a casserole dish. Pour melted butter over potatoes and sprinkle with Hidden Valley mix. Cover; bake at 350°F for 1 hour.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(29,'Sauces & Gravy','Sauces --- Red Eye Gravy','Fay\'s','1/4 ---------- inch thick Ham ( several slices)\n1/2 ---------- Cup water\n1/2 ---------- Cup brewed coffee\n1/4 ---------- salt\n1/4 ---------- black pepper\n2 ------------ Tablespoon  shortening\n\nFry Ham on low heat in shortening, turning often to prevent sticking. Fry until brown on both sides. Take Ham out of pan, and add water, coffee, salt, & black pepper to drippings in skillet. Bring to rolling boil. Serve with grits, Hominy, rice or hot biscuits.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(30,'Salad','Salad --- Spinach',NULL,'2 ---------- Quart fresh torn spinach\n4 ---------- boiled eggs, chopped\n6 ---------- bacon strios, fried crisp and crumbled\n1 ---------- small red onion, thinly sliced into rings\n1 ---------- can water chetnuts, drained and sliced\n\nLayer in a large bowl, add dressing right before serving and gently toss.\n\nDressing\n1/2 --------- Cup packed brown sugar\n1/2 --------- Cup vegetable oil\n1/3 --------- Cup white vinegar\n1/3 --------- Cup ketchup\n1 ------------ Tablespoon worcestershire sauce\n\nCombine all ingredients in a jar with a lid, shake vigorously until well blended. Refrigerate until ready to add to salad. Will keep for several days.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(31,'Pies','Pies --- Peaches For Fried Pies','Faye Thompson','12 ---------- Lb. Peaches ( with peeling)\n8 ------------ Cup sugar                                       \n1 ------------ Pt. Cider vinegar\n                   Butter\n\nWash peaches remove seeds and slice. Add  sugar and vinegar. Soak for 4 hours. Cook  in the solution over  low heat-stirring occasionally for about 2 hours, or until thick. Than can or freeze in small batches to use for fried pies. The peeling  & vinegar gives  the same taste as dried peaches. You can also use only the peeling for this recipe. This is much better taste than fresh Peaches for fried pies.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(32,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Fantastic Potatoes',NULL,'2 ---------- Lbs. potatoes, washed and peeled\n1 ---------- stick butter or margarine seasoned salt to \n                 taste\n2 ---------- Cup sour cream\n1 ---------- pkg. Ranch style dressing mix\n1/2 ------- lb. grated cheddar cheese\n\nDice potatoes into a 2 Quart covered casserole. Slice butter over potatoes and sprinkle generously with seasoned salt. Cover and bake for one hour at 350°F degrees. Combine sour cream and dressing mix. Spread evenly over hot potatoes. Top with grated cheese. Return to over until cheese melts.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(33,'Sauces & Dressings','Sauces --- Honey Mustard Dressing','Houston\'s Restaurant','6 ---------- Tablespoon honey\n6 ---------- Tablespoon prepared mustard\n6 ---------- Tablespoon vegetable oil\n1 1/3 ----- Cup mayonnaise\n1 ---------- Teaspoon cider vinegar\n1 ---------- dash onion salt \n                  pinch of cayenne pepper\n\nMix and chill. Keep stored in Ref.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(34,'Miscelleanous','Miscellaneous --- Orange Halves',NULL,'6 ---------- Oranges  (cut  oranges cross into 12 halves \n                  cut out the sections)\n12 --------  Scoops of Vanilla Ice Cream\n1 ---------- Jar of caramel topping\n                  choice of nuts sprinkled on top.\n\nYou can serve sections of the orange on side of plate with a piece of green leaves.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(35,'Salad','Salad --- Strawberry Jello','Jane Thompson','1 ---------- Large 6 0z. strawberry jello\n2 ---------- Cup boiling water\n1 ---------- Cup pineapple juice drained from pineapple\n                 if not enough to make a cup finish with cold \n                 water.\nDesolve Jello in hot water. Add pineapple juice.            \nMix following ingredients and add to Jello mix.\n\n1 ---------- small can crushed pineapple (drained)\n1/2 ------- Cup cottage cheese ( small curds)\n2 ---------- Tablespoon mayonnaise\n\nRef. until firm. About 2 hours.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(36,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Potatoes --- Creamed','Cherrie','5 ---------- Lb. potatoes peeled and cut to boil\n                 cook until tender. ( drain)\n8 ---------- oz sour cream\n1 ---------- stick of butter\n                 salt & pepper to taste. If you don\'t like the \n                 pepper to show use white pepper.\n                 Enough milk to cream , be sure not to use to \n                 much , Start beating with electric mixer an \n                 add milk as needed.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(37,'Dips','Dip --- Olive Dip','Deborah Ferguson','1 ---------- Cup Mozzaiella grated cheese\n1 ---------- Cup sharpe cheddar cheese\n1 ---------- Cup mayonnaise\n1 ---------- Cup chopped green Olives\n1 ---------- Cup black olives chopped\n1 ---------- bunch chopped green onions\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon red pepper\n\nMix and bake 350°F oven 25 minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(38,'Salad','Salad --- Poppy Seed For Cold Slaw',NULL,'3/4 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 ------------ Teaspoon dry mustard\n1 ------------ Teaspoon salt\n1/3 --------- Cup vinegar\n1/2 --------- Cup grated onion\n1 ------------ Cup wessen oil\n1 1/2 ------- Teaspoon poppy seed\n\nBlend first  4 ingredients with electric mixer, Add onion & wessen oil, mix well. Beat in poppy seed. Store in ref. in a covered container. Stir before pouring over shredded cabbage.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(39,'Sauces & Dips','Dip --- Chocolate Fondue  Dip','Fay\'s','12 ---------- Ozs. Milk Chocolate ( make sure it\'s real \n                    chocolate made with a cocoa butter base.\n                    Check the ingredients label-some may \n                     contain other vegetable oil.\n1/2 --------- Cup heavy cream\n3 ------------ Tablespoons Grand Marnier instead of \n                   Grand Matnier  , you can use Brandy, Rum, \n                    Kirsch, Bourbon or your favorite liqueur. \n                    For non alcoholic add almond or\n                    coconut flavoring, or instant Coffee. \n\nIf using bars or squares of chocolate, break up. Melt chocolate and cream over low heat. I like to use a double boiler, I find this to stick real quick.Sterring constantly When ready to serve put in a small shafing pan, are any serving pan over hot water. Add the Grand Marnier. This is great with fresh Fruit.Apples, Bananas, Canelope, Marshallows, Strawberries, Pineapple, Pound Cake, Fresh Peaches. Doanuts rounds, Nothing is easier to make than chocolate fondue, And nothing\'s easier to custom-design to your own individual taste-the variations are endless. To keep The fruit from turning use the following receipt.\n\nSubstitute for Fruit Fresh\n\n2 ---------- Tablespoons vinegar\n2 ---------- Tablespoons salt\n1 ---------- Gal. Water\n\nPour over Fruit let set for few minutes and rinse. This keeps fruit from turning. Some people use lemon juice, But I find this not as strong.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(40,'Miscellanous','Miscellaneous --- Hand Cream',NULL,'1 ---------- Jar Vitamin E. Body cream\n2 ---------- Bottles Babby Lotion\n1 ---------- Large Jar Vasoline\n\nMix together. You can buy some cute little Jars or Bottles and have your own Cream. This is good cream, One of my workers diden\'t have much money , They gave this to me for Christmas one year. I thought it was one of the sweetest gifts.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(41,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Patio Beans','Jeanne Mc/Cutchen','4 ---------- slices bacon - cooked & crumbled\n1 ---------- Med. Onion chopped\n1 ---------- pound can Baked Beans in Tomato Sauce.\n1 ---------- pound can Kidney beans drained\n1 ---------- pound can lima beans drained\n1/4 -------  pound sharp cheddar cheese cubed\n1/2 ------- Cup light brown sugar\n1/3 ------- Cup catsup\n2 ---------- Teaspoon worchestershire sauce\n\nFry bacon until crisp.Saute onion in bacon drippings. Combine in large casserole the beans, cubed cheese brown sugar and seasoning; Stir in onion bacon sprinkle with grated parmeson cheese. Bake 350°Foven until bubbly/',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(42,'Candy','Candy --- Microwave Peanut Brittle or pecan',NULL,'1 --------- Cup sugar\n1/2 ------ Cup water\n1/2 ------ Cup light Karo\n7 --------- ozs. Dry-roasted peanuts or pecans chopped \n                fine. I perfer pecans\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla\n3/4 ------ Cup coconut, optional\n1 --------- Teaspoon baking soda\n\nstir sugar, water and Karo in 2-qt. casserole; cook in microwave 12 minutes. Stir in nuts; cook 2 minutes. Add coconut and vanilla; cook 1 minute. Add baking soda and stir until foamy. Spoon onto a greased cookie sheet 1/4 inch thick. Note: Better if cooked in corning ware. Raw peanuts may be used. Cook  peanuts 6 minutes before using. If you have peauts with salt, You can put them in a collander and run cold water over them to get all of the salt off. Let drain.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(43,'Pastery','Pastery --- Pie Pastery',NULL,'1 1/4 ---------- Cups shortening or pure Lard\n3 --------------- Cups  plain flour\n1 --------------- Teaspoon salt\n1 --------------- egg well beaten\n5 --------------- Tablespoons water\n1 --------------- Tablespoon vinegar\n\nCut shortening into flour and salt. Combine eggs Water and vinegar. Pour liquid into flour mixture Slowely.Blend with a Food Prosser. Until all flour is mixed. Be sure not to over mix.Take out and devide into 2 balls. It is better if you flatten the ball slightly in a round shape.This makes 2 -9 inch pie crust. I use the large glass pie plates.Ref. for about 1 hour. Roll the dough between two pieces of wax paper, Or spread a little flour on pastery sheet and roll size you need.You can take the extra pieces and patch the edges. If the edges are a little thicker that makes it easier to make the edges pinch to decorate.Put in freezer, and when cold put in a 2 gal zip lock bag and freeze until ready to use. All of the left over pieces of crust roll out and cut in cute little shapes bake until almost done, add your favoriate cheese. Cut the cheese with same cutter it fits the dough perfect. Put back in oven until cheese melts. This is a easy crust to handle and can be rerolled without toughening. Keep in ref. up to two weeks. Put dough in plastic bags, and store. When you get ready to bake crust, Bake in a 375°Foven until light brown. Take a fork and punch a few holes in the bottom of thr crust to take out all the air bubbles.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(44,'Sea Food','Sea Food --- Salmon Patties','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- can Pink Salmon\n1 ---------- Cup carnation milk\n                 pepper & salt to taste\n1 ---------- egg\n1/2 ------- Cup flour self-rising\n2/3 ------- Cup corn meal self-rising\n\nDeep fry in medium hot shortining until brown on both sides. These are good served with fresh peas.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(45,'Dips','Dip --- French Onion Dip',NULL,'2 ---------- 8 Ozs cream cheese\n1 ---------- med. Onion chopped fine\n2 ---------- Tablespoon mayonnaise\n1 ---------- 16 oz. parmason cheese\n\nMix ingredients together leaving a little bit of Parmason cheese to top when baking. Bake uncovered in a 350°F oven for 25 minutes. Serve\nwith Frito Chips.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(46,'Vegetales','Vegetables --- Stuffed Bell Peppers','Jane Thompson','10 ---------- Large green Bell Peppers\n2 ------------ Lb. Ground beef\n2 ------------ Cups cooked rice\n1 ------------ 15 oz can diced tomatoes\n1 ------------ large onion chopped\n                   salt & pepper to taste\n2 ------------ Tablespoons olive oil\n\nCut bottoms from peppers, and remove all inside. Put peppers in enough water to cover. Boil for 3 minutes drain and set aside. Brown ground beef in oil, take out and saute onions until tender. Mix other ingredients. Stuff peppers, bake 350°F degree oven 30 minutes . Options -- sprinkle your favorite cheese on top of pepper or buttered bread crumbs. This is good to serve as a meat dish without peppers.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(47,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Carrots','Deborah Ferguson','2 ---------- pkgs. Baby carrots\n1 ---------- Cup white sugar\n1 ---------- Cup light brown sugar\n1 ---------- stick of butter\n\nCover carrots with water, mix other ingredients, bring to a boil. Turn heat on low and cook for 45 minutes or until tender. Serve hot.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(48,'Dips','Dip --- Hot Dip',NULL,'2 ---------- cans whole tomatoes \n1 ---------- Onion\n2 ---------- Jalapeno peppers\n1 ---------- Tablespoon cumin seed\n1 ---------- Tablespoon accent\n1 ---------- Tablespoon garlic powder\n1 ---------- Tablespoon wesson oil\n\nChop tomatoes, onion and pepper. I like using food prosser. Add cumin, accent and garlic powder. Bring to a boil, boil for a few minutes, Add wesson oil. Add salt to taste.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(49,'Cakes','Cake --- Coconut Creamy',NULL,'2 ---------- Cups sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup shortening\n1/2 ------- Cup butter softened\n5 ---------- eggs. Separated\n2 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n1 ---------- Teaspoon soda\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ---------- Cup buttermilk\n2/3 ------- Cup flaked coconut\n                 pinch of cream of tarter\n\nCream shortening, butter and sugar. Add egg yolks and beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, stir in vanilla and coconut. Beat egg whites until frothy; Add cream of tarter and continue beating until egg whites are stiff, but not dry. Fold egg whites into batter. Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9 inch pans. Bake at 350°F degreees for 25 to 30 minutes. Store in refrigerator.\n\nFrosting for Creamy Coconut Cake\n\n1 ---------- 8 oz. pkg. cream cheese softened\n1/2 ------- Cup butter softened\n1 ---------- 16 oz. pkg. powdered sugar, sifted\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n                 dash salt\n1/2 -------- Cup flaked coconut\n1/2 --------  Cup chopped pecans\n\nBeat cream cheese and butter until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar, beating until smooth, Add vanilla.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(50,'Frosting','Frosting --- Seven Minute Frosting','Arkansas Garden cook book','2 ---------- egg whites\n3/4 ------- Cup sugar\n1/3 ------- Cup light corn syrup\n2 ---------- Tablespoon water\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon cream of tarter\n\nCombine all ingredients in top of double boiler over cold water. Bring to low boil; beat mixture constantly until frosting forms peaks. Yield: frosting for 8 or 9-inch round cake.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(51,'Sauces','Sauces --- Shrimp Cocktail Sauce',NULL,'1 ---------- bottle chili sauce (12 0z)\n1 ---------- Tablespoon prepared horseradish\n1 ---------- Tablespoon lemon juice\n\nCombine ingredients, mix well. Add salt and pepper to taste. Chill and serve with cooked shrimp. Make 1 2/3 cups. Refrigerate leftovers.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(52,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Cream Potatoes',NULL,'1 ---------- 5 lb. bag of red potatoes cut into 1- inch\n                 pieces.\n3/4 -------- Cup sour cream\n1/2 -------- Cup butter softened\n1 ----------- 3-ounce package cream cheese, softened\n2 ----------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 -------- Teaspoon ground black pepper\n\nIn a large dutch oven, combine potatoes and water to cover. Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat, and simmer for about 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender. Drain well. In a large bowl combine potatoes, sour cream, butter, cream cheese, salt, and pepper. Using a potato masher, mash potatoes to desired consistency. I use the electric hand mixer to finish. It make the potatoes much smother.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(53,'Deserts','Desserts --- Peach Desert','Loretta Lynn Café','1 ---------- large can sliced Peaches (15 oz heavy syrup)\n1 ---------- Cup flour (self rising)\n1 ---------- Cup milk\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup butter\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla\n\n\n2 ---------- Tablespoons Sugar\n1/4 -------  Cup butter\n\nPour Peaches in a 1 1/2 qt. Casserole. Mix flour, milk, sugar, vanilla and butter until smooth , use electric mixer. Pour in the middle of Peaches. Do not stir. Preheat oven 350°F. Cook until crust formes in about 15 or 20 minutes of cooking time,Take out  of oven sprinkle sugar and butter on top. Turn oven to 450°F finish baking  for about 30 minutes, until brown on top. This is not my favoriate cobble, But very good,quick and easy.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(54,'Salads','Salad --- Mixed Green Salad',NULL,'1 --------- 10 1/2 oz. Log Herbed goat Cheese\n2 --------- Egg whites, lightly beaten\n2 --------- Cups Panko bread crumbs\n                Vegetable oil for frying\n12 ------- Cup spring salad mix\n1 --------- (6-ounce) bag baby spinach, stems removed.\n2 --------- Anjou Pears, cored and thinly sliced\n1 --------- Cup sweetened dried cranberries\n1/2 ------ Cup sliced almonds Orange-Honey Dressing\n               (recipe follows)\n\nRoll goat cheese into 1/2 inch balls. Dip each ball in \negg white; dredge in bread crumbs. Cover, and freeze \ngoat cheese fritters for at at least 30 minutes.\n     In a large Dutch over or fryer, pour oil to a depth of 2 inches; heat to 375°F, Fry goat cheese fritters for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown; drain on paper towels.\n     In a large bowl, combine salad mix and spinach. Divide evenly among 12 salad plates. Top each evenly with pear slices, cranberries, and sliced almonds. Top with goat cheese fritters. Drizzle each salad with Orange-Honey Dressing. Serve immediately.\n\nOrange-Honey Dressing\n     makes about 2 cups\n\n3/4 --------- Cup white wine vinegar\n1/2 --------- Cup fresh orange juice\n1/4 --------- Cup honey\n1 ------------ Tablespoon chopped fresh parsley\n1/4 ---------  Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ---------  Teaspoon ground black pepper\n3/4 ---------  Cup vegetable oil',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(55,'Meats','Soup --- Roasted Chicken With Caramelized Onion',NULL,'2 ---------- Cups roasted Chicken cut into strips\n2 ---------- Tablespoons vegetable oil\n2 ---------- Medium Onions, halved and thinly sliced \n                 (about 1 cup)\n8 ---------- Cups Chicken Broth, It\'s better if you make\n                 your own.\n3 ---------- Teaspoons salt\n11/2 ------ Teaspoon black pepper\n2 ----------- medium Carrots, sliced\n2 ----------- stalks celery, sliced \n2 ----------- Cup uncooked trumpet-shaped pasta \n\nMakes 6 servings\n\nHeat the oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onions and cook until they begin to brown, Stirring occasionally. Reduce the heat to medium. Cook until the onions are tender and caramelized, stirring occasionally. Remove the skillet from the heat. \n     Heat the broth, salt, black pepper, carrots and cellery in a 4-qt saucepan over medium-high heat to a boil. Stir the pasta and chicken in the saucepan. Reduce the heat to medium. Cook for 10 minutes until the pasta is tender. Stir in the onions and serve immediately.\n\nIt\'s really nice to have Chicken broth in the freezer ready to use. Here is how you do this. Buy Chicken when it is on sale. I like to buy legs & thighs. Cover  chicken with water in large pot. Cook until tender.\nLet cool, take chicken off the bone, and throw skin and bones away. Strain the broth in plastic containers, and put in freezer until ready to use. Freeze pieces of chicken in separate plastic bags ready for use. You can\'t believe how much you will use both broth and chicken. This is what I use for Chicken and dumplins.\nThe chicken in this recipe can be chicken you buy at the market already roasted, and what I do is use the left over parts and freeze, or when I cook beer chicken use left over chicken. The recipe for beer chicken is in this book.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(56,'Bread','Bread --- Pastery For Bread Cups',NULL,'3 --------- Cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon soda\n1 --------- Tablespoon baking powder\n1/3 ------ Cup pure Lard\n1 --------- egg\n1 --------- Cup buttermilk\n\nCombine flour, soda and baking powder; cut in shorting until mixture resembles coarse meal. Combine egg and buttermilk; add to flour mixture. I use a food prosser. Sprinkle flour on wax paper and roll about 1/4 inch thick. To make a bread bowl, use a oven proof bowl or muffin pan turned upside down, This has to be a large muffin , are it woulden\'t be large enough to serve a main course. I like to serve my favorite Chicken & Dumplin receipt. After placing them around the Muffin pan, bake at 375°F oven until light brown 12 to 15 minutes. These can be cooked ahead of time and freeze, Take out of freezer and warm before serving.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(57,'Pies','Pies --- Maw Maw\'s Fried Pies',NULL,'3 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n3/4 ------- Cup Crisco or Pure Lard\n1 ---------- egg, lighty beaten\n1/2 ------- Cup cold water\n1 ---------- Tablespoon white vinegar\n\nMix together the flour and salt. Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender. Until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir together the beaten egg with the water and sprinkle over flour mixture. Sprinkle in the vinegar, Mixing lighty, until ingredients are well combined. From the dough into a ball and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for at least one hour. Yields 12 pies.\n\nPutting it all together\n\nRemove the pastery from the refrigerator and cut it into four equal pieces. You can then cut each of the four pieces into two equal pieces, leaving you with 8 golf-ball-size dough balls. If you want minature pies make the eight pieces into 16 pieces. On a lightly floured surface, roll each ball into a 5-to-6-inch circle. Or 4 inch for minatures.You can use plastic food containers to cut out pies. I find it hard to buy cutters larger than 3 inches. It\'s easy to find a glass or bowl to cut your circles.Your circles do not have to be perfect, and regged edges are okay. You can cut dough in squares with a pizza cutter or knife, fold over and finish the sane as round circles. Make any size you want. If you get to large they may be hard to handle when frying.\n\nPut 2 generous tablespoons of filling onto one side of the circle of dough.For minatures use 1 teaspoon of fruit. Seal the pie by wetting the inside edge of the dough with egg whites ( i use a pastery brush to brush on egg whites.) and then fold over the dough, making the familiar half-moon-shape pie. Make sure the edges of the dough are even, and press and crimp to insure a good seal. You can use a fork to give you a bit of a decorative edge if you like. You can also correct the more ragged edges during this step because the dough is pliable. Just make sure the filling is sealed in and any holes in the dough are crimped. When you are finished, take a fork and punch 3 times on top of the pie to let the steam excape.\n\nFrying\n\nI use two methods and both are good. To deep-fry, heat the oil in a deep pan with steep sides or a deep-fryer. Carefully lower the pies into the oil, I use Peanut Oil. You can use it to refry a lot more than any other oil without the taste transfuring to the food you are cooking. It also taste better. Drop one pie at a time, and fry until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes. You don\'t have to worry about cooking the filling since it\'s already cooked. The frying process merely cooks the dough.\n\nThe second method is panfrying. Fry the pies in about a half inch of oil in an electric frying pan set to 375°F. Pan frying takes a little longer and the pies have to be turned, but the end results will be every bit as good. Sprinkle the hot pies with confectioners sugar if you like that taste. Sometime I do and sometimes I don\'t.\n\nThe Filling\nFor dried apples, \n1 ---------- pkg. Dried apples\n2 ---------- Cups sugar\n3 ---------- Tablespoons butter\nMore than cover the apples with water, they swell to about 3 time the size of the original. Cook until tender with lid partely on. You will have to keep adding water until they  are done. About 2 hours. About 10 minutes before they are done add sugar and butter. Mash until well. You can freeze what part you do not use, and use later.\n\nFor dried peaches and apricot\nUse the same cooking method as above for apples, Except they do not swell like apples. I like to add a little butter and some vanilla extract it gives it extra flavor. When done sweeted to taste. Remember all dried fruit has to be really sweet, because they are going into a crust that is not sweet.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(58,'Bread','Bread --- Buttermilk Buiscuts','Faye Martin Thompson','11/3 ---------- cups buttermilk\n3 -------------- cups  self-rising flour\n1/4 ------------ cup shortening\n1 --------------- teaspoon baking soda\n3 ---------------Tablespoons shortening for coating\n                       biscuits in the pan before baking. \n\nMix flour, buttermilk, shortening, soda, Roll out on a floured dough board about 1/2 inch thick.  Cut with any size biscuit cuttter.  Melt shortening in baking pan and coat biscuits in the shortening before baking.  Bake in a 400°F oven for 15 to 20 minutes, are until  they are as brown as you like them. I like them better at slight brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(59,'Eggs','Breakfast --- Boiled Eggs In Color','Faye',' 6 ---------- Hard boiled eggs\n2 ----------- Tablespoons Mayonnaise or sour cream\n3/4 -------- Teaspoon prepared mustard\n1/2 -------- Teaspoon lemon juice, herb or seasoning\n                  blend\n1/4 -------- Teaspoon salt\n1/4 --------  Black pepper\n\nCut eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks and set whites aside. Put egg yolks and other ingredients in Food Processer, mix until smooth . Place yolk mixture in 1-quart food storage bag , push yolk mixture toward corner of bag. Snip off about 1/2 inch of bag corner. Squeezing bag gently, using about 1 Tablespoon of yolk mixture for each egg half. Chill to blend flavors.\n\nFor added pizzazz , try one of these garnishes;\n\nChopped green onion\nchopped chives\npimento strips\nparsley leaves\nfresh cilantro\ndill sprigs\ncrimbled bacon\npapriks\ndiced green or red pepper\nsliced green olives\ncapers\ncubed ham\n\nFor colored deviled eggs, peel chilled hard-cooked eggs and then dye the peeled eggs. Use pure food grade egg dyes and prepare as instructed. Dye the peeled eggs for 2 minutes. Remove from dye. Slice, fill and serve chilled.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(60,'Sauces','Sauces --- Dallas Poppy Seed Dressing',NULL,'1 1/2 ----- Cup sugar\n2 ---------- Teaspoon dry mustard\n2 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n2/3 ------- Cup vinegar ( I use apple cider vinegar)\n3 ---------- Tablespoon onion juice (grated from onion)\n2 ---------- Cups salad oil (never olive oil)\n2 ---------- Tablespoon Poppy Seeds \n\nMix sugar, salt, mustard, vinegar and onion juice. Add oil slowly , beating constantly, and continue to beat until thick. Add Poppy Seeds and beat for a few minutes. Store in a cool place or refrigerate, If it separates beat or mix well beforeserving. Good on any fruit.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(61,'Dips','Dip --- Fondue','Fay\'s','1 ---------- 14 oz. can sweetened condensed milk\n1 ---------- 6 oz. squares butterscotch morsels\n4 ---------- 1oz. Squares unsweatened chocolate\n1 ---------- 7 oz. jar marshallow cream \n1/2 -------- Cup milk\n1/2 -------- Cup flaked cocoanut\n1 ----------- Teaspoon vanilla extraxt (always use pure \n                   vanilla)\n\nCombine all ingredients in top of double boiler. Bring water to a boil. Reduce heat to low, and cook until chocolate melts, stiring constently.Pour into a Fondue Pot; place over Fondue burner. Thin Fondue with addentional milk, if necessary. Serve with Pound cake cubes and assorted fruit as dippers. Yields 3 1/2 cups.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(62,'Entree','Entree --- Macaroni and Cheese','Paula Deen','2 ---------- Cups uncooked elbow Macaroni (an 8 oz. \n                 Box isn\'t quite 2 cups)\n2 1/2 ----- Cups (about10 ozs.) grated  sharp cheddar \n                 cheese\n3 ---------- eggs, beaten\n1/2 ------- Cup sour cream\n1 ---------- 10.75-ounce can condensed cheddar \n                  cheese soup\n4 ----------- Tablespoons (1/2 stick) butter, cut in pieces\n1/2 -------- Teaspoon salt\n1 1/2 ------ Cup whole milk\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon dry mustard\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon pepper\n\nPreheat the oven to 350°F. Spray a 9 by 13 inch baking dish with vegetable oil cooking spray.\nBoil the macaroni in a 2 quart saucepan in plenty of water until tender, about 7 minutes. Drain. Return the drained macaroni to the saucepan and add 2 cups of the cheese. Stir until the cheese melts while the macaroni is still hot. Add the eggs, sour cream, soup, butter,salt, milk, mustard  and pepper and stir well.\nPour the macaroni into the prepared dish. Smooth the top and sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top. Bake for 40 minutes, until browned and bubbly.\n\nNote: The macaroni and cheese can be prepared earlier in the day or the day before and refrigerated unbaked, covered, until needed. Allow to come to room temperature before baking. Serves 12.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(63,'Salads','Salad --- Fresh Vegetable Salad',NULL,'3 ---------- Inches of Lettuce in bottom of bowl\n1 ---------- box frozen uncooked English Peas\n1 ---------- layer cauliflower (broken into small pieces)\n1 ---------- layer of  Broccoli (broken into small pieces)\n4 ---------- cooked sliced and crumbled bacon\n1 ---------- bunch of green onions top and all.\n\nSprinkle On Top\n1/2 -------- package good season Italian Salad mix\n\nSeal  over with mayonnaise\n Leave in refrigerator for 24 hours and then toss and top with shredded cheese.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(64,'Salads','Salad --- Sweet & Sour Cabbage Slaw',NULL,'1 --------- head cabbage\n2 --------- onions\n1 --------- cup sugar\n1 --------- cup vinegar\n1 --------- Teaspoon dry mustard\n1 --------- Teaspoon celery seed\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n3/4 ------- cup oil\n\nGrate cabbage and onion. Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over this. Let sit. Bring to a boil: vinegar, dry mustard, celery seed, and salt. Pour boiled mixture over cabbage, onion and sugar. Add salad oil. Let stand overnight. It keeps well in a covered container in refrigerator.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(65,'Bread','Bread --- W.R. Light Rolls','W R Flour Bag','1 ---------- pkg. dry yeast\n1/4 ------- Cup warm water\n1 ---------- Teaspoon sugar\n2 ---------- Cup milk\n1/2 -------- Cup sugar\n1/2 -------- Cup shortening\n2 ----------- Teaspoon salt\n2 ----------- eggs (well beaten)\n7 ----------- Cups W-R flour (all purpose)\n\nDissolve yeast in1/4 c. warm water to which 1 tsp. sugar has been added. Scald milk, add sugar, shortening, salt and cool to lukewarm. Add flour enough to make medium thick batter and beat well. Add beaten eggs and dissolved yeast and beat. Add remaining flour. When too thick to mix by spoon, pour onto floured board and knead until smooth and elastic. Put into greased bowl and place in warm place until dough doubles in size. Knead down and shape into light rolls. This is a basic recipe and may be used for cinnamon rolls, tea rings, ect. Bake in greased pan in 375 degree oven about 15 or 20 minutes, or until brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(66,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Sasuage Cassrole',NULL,'8 --------- eggs, slightly beaten\n6 --------- slices bread, cubed\n1 --------- pound sasuage, cooked, crumbled and \n                drained.\n2 --------- Cups milk\n1 --------- Cup cheddar cheese grated\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1 --------- Teaspoon mustard\n\nMix all ingredients and pour into buttered 9 by 13 inch pan. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350°F for 35 minutes. Serves 8.\n\nNote: May add 1 small can chopped geen chilies.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(67,'Candies','Candy --- Orange Balls','Bobbye Mullins','1 ---------- 12 oz. pkg. vanilla wafers\n1 ---------- box powered sugar\n1 ---------- stick margarine (softened)\n1 ---------- 6 oz. can orange juice (thawed)\n1 ---------- Cup finely chopped nuts.\n\nCrush vanilla wafers. Add other ingredients. Mix well with hands. Form in balls. Roll in coconut and chill.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(68,'Candies','Candy --- Chocolate Peanut Butter Fudge microwave','Nancy Daniels','1 ---------- 12 oz. pkg. chocolate sweet morsels\n1 ---------- 12 0z. Pkg. peanut butter morsels\n1 ---------- cup crushed peanuts\n\nWith the two pkgs. Mix together, Place in microwave for 2 minutes.Take out and stir. Place back in microwave  for 2 more minutes. Take out and add 1 cup crushed peanuts.Spray cookie sheet with Pam or Butter, Pour  onto cookie sheet and let stand until cool.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(69,'Meats','Breakfast --- Fancy Bacon','Jeannie Mc/Cutchen','12 ---------- Slices of thick Bacon cut in 1/2 \n3 ------------ Tablespoons finely chopped pecans\n2 ------------ Tablespoons brown sugar\n1 1/2 ------- Teaspoon ground black pepper (course)\n\nMix together and place on top of Bacon slices. Heat oven 400°F. Line cookie sheet with foil. Spray with Pam. Bake 22 - 25 minutes.\n\n\nOther  Bacon recipes\n\n1 ---------- Cup brown sugar\n1 ---------- Tablespoon cinnamon\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon nutmeg\n1 ---------- pound bacon, sliced\n\nPreheat the oven to 350°F degrees Combine the brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in a bowl. Coat the bacon slices generosly on both sides with the browm mixture Arrange on a broiler pan. Bake for 15 or 20 minutes or until the bacon is crisp. Serve warm or at room tempature.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(70,'Cakes','Cake --- Pineapple Upside Down','Forrestine Farris','2 ---------- sticks butter\n2 1/4 ----- Cups sugar\n1 1/4 ----- Cups buttermilk\n4 ---------- eggs\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla\n3 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n1/4 -------- Teaspoon salt\n2 ----------- Teaspoons baking powder\n\nBottom of cake pans\n\n3/4 --------- Cup brown sugar\n1/2 --------- stick of butter\n7 ------------ slices of pineapple.This recipe can be \n                    changed, and use peach or apricots.\n7 ------------ maraschino cherries\nRepeat for the second pan.\n\nTwo 10 inch iron skillets. Spray bottom of both skillets with flour based spray. Mix butter & brown sugar in a small pan, melt and pour in skillet. Add sliced pineapple over brown sugar, and maraschino cherries in the center of each pineapple. Combine melted butter,sugar, buttermilk, eggs, and vanilla, mix well. Add sifted flour, salt, and baking powder. Mix with dry ingredients, beat until mixed well. Pour into skillet with brown sugar and pineapple. Bake in a 350°F oven for 35 minutes. Cool on rack for 10 minutes. Remove to a cake plate and turn cakes upside down so the fruit will be on top. Stack one layer on top of the oher…',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(71,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Corn Pudding','Deborah Ferguson','2 ---------- Eggs beaten\n2 ---------- pkgs. Cream style corn (frozen and thawed)\n2 ---------- Tablespoons  flour\n3 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon salt\n                 dash of red pepper\n6 ---------- Tablespoons butter-melted (not hot)\n1 1/4 ----- Cup milk\n\nLet corn thaw, combine with eggs, Add dry ingredients Then butter and milk. Bake in a 325°F oven for 1 1/2 hours. Stir afte 15 minutes, to remove from sides.\n\nServes 8',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(72,'Salads','Salad --- Marinated Tomatoes',NULL,'3/4 -------- Cup vegetable oil\n1/2 -------- Cup red wine vinegar\n3 ----------- Tablespoons chopped fresh parsley\n1 ----------- Tablespoon sugar\n1 1/2 ------ Teaspoons garlic salt\n1 1/2 ------ Teaspoons seasoned salt\n3/4 --------- Teaspoon dried oregano\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon black pepper\n10 ---------- plum tomatoes (about 2 1/2 pounds)\n\nCombine vegetable oil and next 7 ingredients in a large zip-top plastic freezer bag.\nCore and cut each tomato into 4 wedges; add to marinade in plastic bag. Seal and shake to coat tomato wedges. Chill 4 hours; let stand 30 minutes at room temperature before serving with a slotted spoon.\n\nThis makes about 6 to 8 servings.\n\nOnce you have enjoyed all of the tomatoes, transform the leftover marinade into a quick and fresh vinaigrette by adding 1/4 Teaspoon Dijon muatard.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(73,'Entree','Entree --- Chili',NULL,'2 --------- Tablespoons olive oil\n2 --------- lbs. Ground beef\n1 --------- Med. Onion\n1 --------- 28 Ozs.Tomatoes (chopped fine)\n2 --------- 8 Oz.cans tomato sauce\n1 --------- can Ro-tel \n2 --------- Cups v-8 vegetable juice\n1 --------- pkg.chili seasoning (French\'s original Chili-O\n               seasoning mix)\n2 --------- Cups beans (optional) if you use beans use \n                pinto beans in a 15 oz. can.\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------- black pepper\n\nIn a large skillet, cook onion until tender. Add ground beef, cook until red is gone.Add other ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes with a lid on. This is a good place to use a slow cooker.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(74,'Salad','Salad --- Broccoli & Cauliflower Salad',NULL,'4 ---------- stalks fresh broccoli flowerettes only.\n8 ---------- large fresh mushrooms, sliced\n1 ---------- medium green pepper, chopped\n3 ---------- ribs of celery, chopped\n1 ---------- small head cauliflower, broken into \n                 flowerlettes\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n2 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 -------- Cup vinegar\n1 1/2 ------ Cups oil\n1 ----------- small onion grated\n2 ----------- Tablespoons poppy seeds\n\nCombine first five ingredients in a large container  with a tight lid. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour marinade over vegetables and toss; cover. Chill at least 3 hours. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(75,'Cakes','Cake --- Vanilla Waffer',NULL,'2 --------- sticks oleo\n2 --------- Cups sugar\n6 --------- eggs\n1 --------- 12 oz. Box vanilla wafers, crushed (Iuse a\n                 food processer).\n1/2 ------ Cup milk\n1 --------- 3 1/2 oz. Can cocoanut\n1 --------- Cup peacans or other nut, chopped\n\nCream oleo and sugar thoroughly. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add crushed vanilla wafers alternately with milk, beginning and ending with vanilla wafers. Add coconut and chopped nuts. Bake in well greased and floured tube pan, 2 hours at 275 degree oven,cool in pan. Can then be placed in cake holder or frozen.\n\n Icing (Optional).\n1 ---------- (8-ounce) package cream cheese\n1 ---------- stick butter\n12 --------  ounces powdered sugar\n\nCream sugar and butter; add sugar until creamy, Pour over cooled cake.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(76,'Salads','Salad --- Fresh Cucumber Salad',NULL,'7 ---------- Cups cucumbers sliced thin\n3 ---------- small diced onions\n1 ---------- green bell pepper, chopped\n1 ---------- Cup cider vinegar\n2 ---------- Tablespoons salt\n2 ---------- Cups sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon celery seed\n3 ---------- tomatoes chopped  (optional)\n\nMix all together and let sit over night. This will make 1/2 gallon and will last a long time. If you plan to store this do not add the tomatoe until ready to serve.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(77,'Cakes','Cake --- Coca Cola',NULL,'2 ---------- stickes of oleo or butter\n3 ---------- Tablespoons cocoa\n1 ---------- Cup coca cola\n2 ---------- Cups flour\n2 ---------- Cups sugar\n1/4 -------  Teaspoon salt\n1/2 -------- Cup buttermilk\n2 ----------- eggs\n1 ----------- Teaspoon soda\n1 -----------  Teaspoon vanilla\n1 1/2 ------ Cups miniature marshmallows\n\n\nBring Butter,Cocoa and coca cola to a boil, then pour over flour, Salt & sugar. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda,vanilla, and mix well. Add marshallows last and they will float to the top. Pour batter into well greased and floured oblong cake pan. Bake at 350°F  35 to 40 minutes. Ice cake while hot.\n\nIceing\n1 ---------- stick of oleo or butter\n3 ---------- Tablespoons cocoa\n6 ---------- Tablespoons coca cola\n1 ---------- box confectioner\'s sugar (16 ozs.)\n1 ---------- Cup pecans\n\nHeat to boil the oleo, and the coca cola.Then add the confectioner\'s sugar and pecans.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(78,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Hash Brown Potato Cassrole',NULL,'1 --------- 32 oz. pkg. shredded frozen potatoes\n1/2 ------ Cup melted butter\n1 --------- can cream of chicken soup (undiluted)\n12 ------- oz. grated american cheese\n1 --------- 8 oz. carton sour cream\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------- small onion chopped\n2 ---------- Cups crushed cornflakes\n1/2 ------- Cup melted butter\n\nPlace thawed  potatoes in a 9 by 13 inch baking dish. Mix together next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes. Top with crushed cornflakes and drizzle melted butter over all. Bake uncovered at 350°F for 45 minutes. Serves 12.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(79,'Pies','Pies --- Buttermilk',NULL,'1 1/2 --------- Cups sugar\n3 -------------- eggs\n1 -------------- Tablespoon flour\n1 -------------- stick butter or oleo melted. \n1 -------------- Teaspoon lemon juice\n1/2 ----------- Cup buttermilk\n1 -------------- Tablespoon vanilla\n1 -------------- Cup pecans (opeional)\n1 -------------- unbaked pie shell ( 9 inches)\n\nBeat eggs with sugar and flour until mixed. Add  butter, lemon juice, buttermilk and vanilla. Mix well then add pecans.Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350°F oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Cover the crust around the edges  with aluminum foil the last 15 minutes so it wan\'t get to brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(80,'Entree','Entree --- Irish Italian Spaghetti','Deborah','1 ---------- Onion chopped\n3 ---------- Tablespoons vegetable or olive oil (I use \n                 olive oil)\n1 ---------- Pound ground beef\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon lack pepper\n                 Dash of ground red pepper\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon chili powder\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon hot sauce (tabasco)\n1 ---------- (10 3/4 ounce) can cream of mushroom \n                  soup undiluted\n1 ---------- (10 3/4 ounce) can cream of tomato soup\n                  undiluted\n1 ---------- (8 ounce) package of spaghetti noodles\n1/2 -------- Cup grated parmesan cheese\n\nSaute onion in oil: add meat and seasoning: cook until light brown and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Add soup to meat mixture: simmer, covered. For 45 minutes. I use crock pot. Prepare noodles according to psckage directions: drain and rinse with hot water.\nBe sure to use regular size spaghetti.  \nArrange on hot platter: pour sauce over noodles and sprinkle with cheese. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.I mix sauce with spaghetti in a crook pot if I have to keep it warm for a while. Be sure you turn down on low and stir often, it will stick. Tablespoon',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(81,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Scalloped Potatoes',NULL,'3 ---------- Tablespoons Butter\n2 ---------- Tablespoons Flour \n3 ---------- Cups milk\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon pepper\n6 ---------- medium potatoes, sliced thin \n1 ---------- chopped onion\n\nMake white sauce of first 5 ingredients. Put half of potatoes into greased 2 Quart casserole; cover with half of onion and half of sauce, repeat layers. Cover and bake at 350°F for about 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and cover with grated cheese. Continue baking until cheese is melted and bubbly.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(82,'Breakfast Good','Breakfast --- Cheese Grits',NULL,'3 ---------- Cups chicken broth\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- Cup grits\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon garlic powder\n\ncook for 8 minutes, then add the followering.\n\n6 ---------- Oz mild chedder cheese cut in small pieces\n                  or shredded, so it will milt easly.\n1 ---------- stick butter\n1/4 ------- Cup milk\n3 ---------- eggs beaten well\n\nPour in a 8 by 10 inch cassrole and 2 inches deep.  Bake in a 350°F oven for 50 minutes. Let rest for 20 minutes before serving. Need to be warm when served.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(83,'Sandwiches','Sandwiches --- Cucumber Sandwiches','Fay\'s','16 ---------- Ozs softened cream cheese\n2 ------------ cucumbers (peeled seeded and shredded)\n1/4 --------- Cup sour cream or mayonnaise\n1 ------------ Tablespoon dillweed\n1 ------------ Teaspoon greek seasoning\n1 ------------ Teaspoon celery seed\n\nMix in a mixing bowl or food processer. Spread on trimed bread rounds You can leave off the top piece of bead and garnish with a thin cucumber slice.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(84,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Onion  Roasted Potatoes',NULL,'1 --------- envelope Lipton onion soup mix\n2 --------- pounds all-purpose potatoes, cut into large \n                chunks.\n1/3 ------ Cup olive oil or vegetable oil \n                Salt Pepper to taste\n\nPreheat oven to 450°F \nIn a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients. Close bag and shake, or toss in bowl, until evenly coated.\nIn a well greesed 9 by 13 inch pan,arrange potatoes; discard bag. Bake uncovered, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden.\nMakes 4 servings',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(85,'Soup','Soup --- Chicken Chowder',NULL,'4 --------- slices bacon\n1 --------- can (about 4 ozs.) sliced mushrooms, drained\n1/2 ------ Cup onion, chopped\n1/8 ------ Teaspoon thyme leaves, crushed\n1 --------- can campbell\'s cream of celery soup\n1 --------- can campbell\'s chicken vegetable soup\n1 --------- soup can water\n1 1/2 ---- Cups cooked chicken, diced\n1 ---------- can whole kernel corn, undrained (about 8 \n                 ounces)\n1/2 ------- Cup chopped canned tomatoes \n                 dash of pepper\n\nIn a saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble. Pour off all but 2 Tablespoons drippings. Brown mushrooms and cook onions with thyme in drippings until tender. Add bacon and remaining ingredients. Heat; stir occasionally. Recipe may be doubled. Makes 5 1/2 Cups.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(86,'Soup','Soup --- Clam Chowder Soup',NULL,'1 --------- large onion, chopped\n4 --------- Tablespoons butter\n2 --------- Teaspoons salt\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon pepper\n2 --------- cans minced clams\n1 1/2 ---- Cups half and half\n3 ---------  large potatoes, diced\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon basil\n2 ---------- Cups water\n4 ---------- Tablespoons flour\n1 ---------- Cup cream of celery soup (not diluted)\n\nSaute onion in butter until soft. Add potatoes, seasoning water. Add flour. Cover simmer 20 minutes. \nAdd clam and liquid.Simmer 10 minutes.Stir in soup half and half. Cover heat to boiling, but do not boil. Sprinkle dash of dried parsley or cayenne upon serving.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(87,'Salads','Salad --- Spring Chopped',NULL,'6 --------- Cups mixed salad greens\n2 --------- hard cooked eggs, chopped\n1 --------- can (15 ounce) pears sliced, and drained\n1 --------- large tomatoe, cut in wedges\n4 --------- slices bacon, cooked and crumbled\n1/3 ------- Cup blue cheese\n1/3 ------- Cup vinaigrette dressing\n\nArrange greens equally on four plates. Top each with one-fourth of the chopped eggs, sliced pears, tomato wedges, blue cheese and crumbled bacon. Drizzle dressing on top. Make 4 servvings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(88,'Salads','Salad --- Vegetable Salad',NULL,'1/2 --------- Cup almonds\n1/2 --------- stick butter add almonds cook until toasted\n6 ------------ Cups lettuce, of your choice\n1/2 --------- Cup green onions chopped\n1 ------------ Cup brockley chopped florettes. No stems\n1 ------------ pkg. ramen noodles \n\nMix first 6 ingredients, and sprinkle noodles on top.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(89,'Salads','Salad --- Vegetable','Jeanne Mc/Cutchen','8 --------- Cups red tip lettuce & one other type lettuce\n1/2 ------ Cup mushrooms sliced\n6 --------- stems of fresh asprigas cut in 3 inch strips\n1/2 ------ Cup parmeson cheese sliced thin. You can \n                slice with vegetable peeler.\n\nDressing\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon country dijon mustard\n1 ---------- Tablespoon lemon juice\n                  slowly add\n3 ---------- Tablespoon olive oil\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon pepper\n\nServes about 5 or 6 people',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(90,'Salads','Salad --- Kraut Salad',NULL,'1 ---------- Quart jar kraut drained\n1 ---------- large bell pepper chopped\n1 ---------- large red onion chopped\n1 ---------- Cup celery, diced\n1 ---------- jar pimentos chopped\n1/2 ------- Cup white vinegar\n1/2 ------- Cup sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup oil\n\nMix well. Let stand over night.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(91,'Pies','Frosting --- Meringue  For Cakes',NULL,'4 ---------- large egg whites\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon cornstarch\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon cream of tarter\n1/2 ------- Cup superfine sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n                 sprinkle of salt\n\nBeat egg whites until it formes a stiff peak. Add other ingredients and continue to beat. Do not over beat. The cream of tarter makes the egg whites less prone to overbeating.Make sure the meringue is spread to the edge of the crust. This prevents the filling from seeping out. Put in a 375°F oven until light brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(92,'Pies','Pies --- Brittings Restaurant Famous Pie','Britting\'s Café In Memphis','5 --------- egg yolks\n1 1/2 ---- Cups sugar\n1 ---------- Tablespoon flour\n1 ---------- Tablespoon corn meal\n2 ---------- Tablespoon grated american cheese\n1 1/4 ----- Cup  whole milk\n4 ---------- Tablespoon carnation milk\n2 ---------- Tablespoons butter\n1/4 -------- Teaspoon salt\n\nHeat milk. Add butter and cheese stirring until it melts and  is blended. Do not boil. Set aside to cool. Beat egg yolks by hand. Mix flour, sugar,and corn meal. Add to eggs. Add salt and carnation milk. Pour cooled milk over egg mixture. Stir well. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 350°F 35 or 40 minutes. It is done when top is browned except for the center about the size of a quarter.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(93,'Pies','Pies --- Key Lime Pie',NULL,'\n 1 ---------- 9 inch graham cracker crust  (deep dish).      \n6 ---------- egg yolks\n1/4 ------- Cup sugar \n1 ---------- can of Eagle Brand sweetened milk   \n 2 --------- Tablespoons lime zest               \n3/4 ------- Cup real lime juice \n                 green food coloring ( Optional)\n                 Whipping cream, stiffly whipped or whipped\n                 topping, Garnish with slices of limes.\n\nMix; pour in baked pie crust, put in refrigerate, Top with whipped cream.\n\nWipped cream\n\n1 ---------- Cup whipping cream\n1/4 ------- Cup sugar\n\nbeat until stiff peaks. Spread on top of cooled pie,.\n\nGraham pie crust\n1/1/2---------- Cups graham crackers crushed fine\n1/4 to 1/2 ---- Cup sifted confectioners sugar\n6 --------------- Tablespoons melted butter\n\nMix and pat in pie pan. An easy way to form, is after placing in pie pan, put another pie pan same size on top and press. Trim any excess that is forced to the top edge.Crust need not be baked before filling but, if used unbaked, must be first chilled thoroughly or the filling will immediately disintegrate the crust. If baked before filling, they require a 350°F oven for 10 minutes.It is best to cool the empty baked shell before filling.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(94,'Pies','Pies --- Lemon Meringue',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup sugar\n4 1/2 ----- Tablespoons flour\n                  few grains salt\n1 1/4 -----   Cups warm water\n4 ----------- egg yolks\n2 ----------- Tablespoons butter or margarine\n1/4 -------- Cup lemon juice\n2 ----------- Teaspoons grated lemon rind\n4 ----------- egg whites for maringue\n\nMix 1 cup sugar, 4 1/2 Tablespoons flour and few grains of salt, gradually add 1 1/4 Cups warm water. Mix well, add 3 beaten egg yolks. Cook over hot water, stirring until thick. Cover, cook 10 minutes. Add 2 Tablespoons butter or margarine, 1/4 Cup lemon juice and 2 Teaspoons lemon rind. Pour into 9 inch baked pastry shell, top with meringue. Bake in moderate oven at 325°. For 20 minutes. Cool before serving. Use margarine receipe listed in the Banana pudding,  in this cook book.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(95,'Pies','Pies --- Egg Custard',NULL,'6 ---------- eggs\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1 1/3 ---- Cups milk\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1/4 -------- Cup butter\n1 ----------- Teaspoon vanilla\n1 ----------- 8 inch deep dish pie crust\n\nBeat eggs, sugar, milk, butter, salt; mix well. Add vanilla. Stir until smooth and pour into pie crust. Bake at 300°F for 45. Turn oven to 350°F for 15 minutes more minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(96,'Dips','Dip --- Beau Monde','Veletta','1 1/2 --------- Cups sour cream\n1 1/2 --------- Cups mayonnaise (hellmans)\n2 -------------- Tablespoon s parsley flakes\n2 -------------- Tablespoons onion\n2 -------------- Teaspoons dill weed\n2 -------------- Teaspoons beau monde\n\nMix and refrigerate over night before serving. This is good on vegetables and potato chips.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(97,'Pies','Desserts --- Biscuit Bread Pudding','Guy Euila Thompson',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(98,'Sandwiches','Sandwiches --- Egg & Olive',NULL,'2 --------- boiled eggs\n12 ------- stuffed olives\n                Mayonnaise (hellmanns)\n                Roasted peanuts\n\nCombine 2 hard boiled eggs chopped 12 chopped stuffed olives and roasted peanuts, with enough mayonnaise to make a spread for sandwiches. This makes about 4 dozen assorted appetizers. I like to trim outside crust from bread and cut small size sandwitches.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(99,'Bread','Bread --- Yeast Biscuits Frozen',NULL,'5 ---------- Cups flour, save 1 Cup for kneading (any \n                 time you are using yeast always use All \n                 purpose flour)\n1 ---------- Teaspoon soda\n4 ---------- Teaspoons baking powder\n1 ---------- Cup cdisco\n2 ---------- pkg. dry yeast dissolved in 4 Tablespoons \n                 warm water\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n4 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n2 ---------- Cups buttermilk\n\nSift dry ingredients, cut in Crisco. Add  yeast and buttermilk. Mix, knead, roll out and cut into biscuits. Greese cookie sheet , put biscuits in pan and dip them in extra shortening in cookie sheet. Put them in the freezer and freeze well. When frozen put them in plastic bags and put them back in the freezer. As needed thaw overnight in ref. Let rise at room temperatureone or two hours before baking at 400°F for 10 or 12 minutes. I have taken them out of the freezer and put them in the oven. It takes a little longer to cook.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(100,'Frosting','Frosting --- Whipped cream',NULL,'2 --------- Cups  Whipping cream\n1 --------- Teaspoon sugar\n1 ---------  vanilla extract\n\nCombine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl; beat until stiff peaks form. Yiield: Enough for two 9 inch layers.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(101,'Desserts','Desserts --- Banana Pudding','Faye Thompson','1 --------- 5 ounce box of vanilla Jello-O (cook & serve) \n                pie & pudding mix be sure not to use instant.\n3/4 ------- Cup sugar\n3 ---------- Cups evaporated milk ( I use carnation)\n6 ---------- eggs\n2 ---------- Teaspoons vanilla extract\n1 ---------- 11 ounce package of jackson vanilla wafers.\n8 ---------- Bananas pelled and sliced\n\nMix pudding mix, sugar milk, egg yolks: cook over boiling water in a double boiler. Beat often wiath electric hand mixer. Add vanilla extract, Cook until thick. Put your vanilla wafers in a 9 by 13 oven proof casserole,Add sliced bananas. Add pudding mix. Be sure the pudding is mixed in well with the wafers and bananas, Take a spoon and let pudding run all through the wafers and bananas.\n\nMeringue for top of Pudding\n\n6 --------- egg whites\n1 --------- 7 ounce jar marshallow cream\n                pinch of salt\n\nBe sure eggs are at room tempature. Beat until they will peak, add salt beat a little more then add marshallow cream, beat again until mixed well. Do not over beat. Spread over pudding making sure it is covering all edges. Bake in a 350°F oven until brown on top.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(102,'Meat','Entree --- Chicken & Dumplins','Faye Thompson','5 ---------- Pounds chicken ( I use legs & thighs)\n5 ---------- Quarts of chicken broth.\n6 ---------- Cups self rising flour ( use W. R. )\n3 ---------- Cups hot broth\n1/2 ------- Cup water\n1/2 ------- Cup shortening ( use crisco)\n 3 --------- Tablespoons salt\n2 ---------- Tablespoons black pepper\n\nPut chicken in a large pot, cover with water enough to make 5 quarts of broth when done. Cook until tender enough it comes off the bone easy. Take chicken out to cool, and strain broth. Take chicken off the bone and throw away skin and bones, lay chicken on cutting board and chop in about 2 or 3 inch lengths. This is to keep the chicken from being stringy. Be sure to cook all the fat in the broth it needs to be a rich broth. In a mixing bowl add flour, water, shortening, and broth. Be sure the broth is boiling, This is what makes the dumpling have the right texture. The hot broth will melt the shorting in the flour.Salt and pepper the hot broth. Mix dough well and roll out  on a floured board about 1/4 inch thick, take a knife and cut strips about 1 1/2 to 2 inches wide. Drop in boiling broth, by the time you have droped all the dough in the broth they are done. Take a large spoon and stir a little after each few dumplins. Do not stir very much because it will mash the soft dough, and you want the dumplin to stay in tact.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(103,'Bread','Bread --- Crackeling Bread','Faye Thompson','2 --------- Cups cracklings ( you can buy them in most \n                southern meat markets)\n1 1/4 ---- Cups corn meal mix ( Aunt Jemima self-rising\n                white)\n3/4 ------- Cup flour ( W. R. self-rising)\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon soda\n2 ---------- eggs\n1 3/4 ----- cup buttermilk\n3 ---------- Tablespoons shortening for baking skillet\n\ncover cracklins with water. Bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Put in a collander and drain. Let  Cracklings cool. Melt shortening in a 10 inch iron skillet until hot. Mix ingredients above including cracklings. Pour in skillet over hot shortening. Bake in 425°F oven for 15 or 20 minutes until light brown on top.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(104,'Breakfast Food','Breakfast --- Scotch Eggs',NULL,'4 ---------- hard boiled egg \n                 little flour\n                 salt & pepper \n12 --------- ounces pork sasuage\n1 ----------- egg, beaten\n3 ----------- tablespoons dry bread crumbs\n                  peanut oil for deep frying\n\nWhen eggs are cool, coat each in a little seasoned flour. Divide the sasuage meat into four equal portions and press them out into squares on a floured board. Wrap a square of sasuage meat around each egg. Seal the edges and roll into a neat shape. Coat the egg in beaten egg and  then Bread crumbs. Deep fry the eggs until they are golden brown. Cool them, then cut in half Serve while hot. Serves 4.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(105,'Cakes','Cake --- Valcona',NULL,'1 ---------- Duncain Hines chocolate cake mix\n1 ---------- can 3.5 ounce can cocoanut\n1 ---------- Cup chopped pecans\n3 ---------- almond joy candy bars (cut in small pieces)\nSpray a 9 by 13 inch baking with crisco no stick spray with flour. Spread cocoanut in bottom of pan, spread pecans over cocoanut, Mix cake mix as directed on package. Stir in pieces of candy. Pour over cocoanut and pecans in baking pan.\n8 --------- ounce cream cheese (at room tempature)\n1 --------- stick of butter (at room tempature)\n2 --------- Cups confectioner sugar\nMix well, and take a spoon and drop spoons of mix on top of batter. When cooked each spoonfull of mixture will come out of the oven with a hole that looks like a Valcona hole. Bake in 350°F oven for about 40 minutes.\nAfter cake is cooked mix the followering.\n1/2 -------- stick of butter\n1/4 -------- Cup cocoa powder\n1/2 -------- Cup milk\n2 ----------- Cups confectioner sugar\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon almond extract\nCook until melted, beat until smooth. You want this mixture to be thin enough to pour over cake. Not spread. You can adjust this with confectioner sugar. A little more or a little less. You can serve with a little whip cream on top.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(106,'cakes','Cake --- Hummingbird',NULL,'combine:\n3 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n2 ---------- Cups sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon soda\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon cinnamon\n\nAdd\n3 ---------- beaten eggs\n1 ---------- Cup vegetable oil\n\nStir until  dry ingredients are moistened (do not beat)\n\n1 1/2 ----- Teaspoon vanilla\n1 ---------- 8 ounce can crushed pineapple, undrained\n1 ---------- Cup chopped pecans\n2 ---------- Cups chopped bananas (about 4 large \n                 bananas)\n\nSpoon butter into greased & flourred 9 inch round cake pans.(I use spray baking oil with flour, there are several on the market) Bake at 350°F  oven for 25 or 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely. Frost with cream cheese frosting.\n\nCream cheese frosting\n\n1 --------- 8 0unce package cream cheese room  \n                temperature\n1/2 ------ Cup butter or margarine, room tempature\n1 --------- (16 ounce) package powdered sugar, sifted\n1 --------- 1 Teaspoon vanilla\n1 --------- cup chopped pecans\n\nBeat cream cheese and buter until smooh. Add powdered sugar and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy. Enough frosting for three layers. Between. On sides and top. Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans on top.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(107,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Squash Casserole','Jane Thompson','6 ---------- Yellow squash sliced\n3 ---------- medium onions\n15 -------- crackers crumbled\n6 ---------- eggs\n3 ---------- cups chedder cheese\n12 -------- slices of bacon  cooked and crumbled\n                 salt and pepper to taste and a dash of\n                 red pepper\n1 1/2 ----- cup of chicken broth\n\nCut squash and cook for about 15 minutes until tender.\nBrown bacon and crumble.Take out of skillet and set aside. Chop onions and brown in bacon greese, Drain squash and add to onions. Add bacon back in the skillet. Cook for about 15 minutes. Mix in beaten eggs crackers cheese & chicken broth. Pour in a greased 9 by 13 cassrole and bake in a 350°F oven for about 30 minutes covered.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(108,'Bread','Bread --- Jennean Mc/Cutchen east Bread','Jennean Mc/Cutchen','3 --------- Packages yeast\n                A pinch of sugar\n3/4 ------ Cup warm water\n3 3/4 --- Cup milk\n1 1/2 ---  stick butter\n1 1/2 --- Cup sugar\n4 1/2 --- Teaspoon salt\n5 -------- pounds minus 2 Cups sifted all-purpose \n              flour\n\ncooking spray , 1 egg and 1/2 cup carnitation milk and 2 stick butter melted. \n\nMix yeast in warm water and the pinch of sugar. About 100 degrees. Heat milk until a film wrinkles on surface. Mix milk, butter, sugar and salt together. The hot milk will melt the butter and sugar. Cool until about 100 degrees, this is very important. If the mixture is to hot it will kill the yeast. Now mix in the yeast. Now its time to mix in the flour. I used a large Kitchen aid mixer, with the stiffer beater. After dough is getting thick use the dough kook to finish kneeding dough.Mix flour slowely.Work dough until it looks satiny. You will need a bowl or Pan about 3 times as large as the dough, spray with a little cooking spray. Take your dough out of mixer and make a ball, put this in the sprayed bowl. Spray a little cooking spray on top and cover with a damp cloth. Put in a warm place, about  85 to 95 degrees. Let rise for about 2 or 3 hours in until double in size. Take out of bowl punch down and divide into 8 parts. This will make 8 loaves.Use nonstick pans and spray with cooking spray,  I use 5 by 9 inch pans, Shape into loaf size to fit your pan. Cover with a damp cloth let rise in a warm place until double in bulk , about 2 hours. Preheat oven to 350°F. With my oven I have to put the rack high in the oven. Bake until it starts to brown. About 10 minutes. Beat 1 egg with 1/2 cup of carnation milk. With a pastery brush top of bread. Put back in oven until brown. About 8 minutes. Take out and put on a wire rack until cool. Place on a cutting board and slice with a serrated knife. Melt butter using a pastery brush and brush between each slice. Keep bread in loaf form and wrap in foil paper. This bread freezes well. When ready to serve leave in the foil, put in a 350°F until warm. Serve warm.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(109,'Breadfast','Breakfast --- Bacon With Maple Syrup',NULL,'2 ---------- Lbs. zeigler thick sliced bacon\n1/2 ------- Cup real mayple syrup\n\nPlace bacon on a rack in the 400°F oven. Cook until almost brown, about 10 to 15 minutes. Take out of oven brush on both sides of bacon with Mayple syrup. Put back in the oven bake until as brown as desired.\n\nAnother bacon recipe\n\n1 ---------- pound of bacon\n1/2 ------- Cup brown sugar\n1 ---------- Tablespoon black pepper coursly ground\n\nMix brown sugar and pepper. Roll bacon in mixture. Bake on a wire rack in a 375°F oven until brown.\nYou can also use this to coat chicken and pork chops.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(110,'entree','Entree --- Baby Back Ribs Bar-B-Qued','Fay\'s  Bar-b-cue Sauce','2 ---------- racks baby back ribs ( about 4 to 6  ribs per\n                 person)  There is a membrane on back side \n                 of ribs, peel by taking your hands and startig\n                 at one end and pull it off. Rub with salt & \n                 pepper.\n                 \n\nRub with dry rub ( see below for receipe.) Be sure to rub on both sides. Wrap in foil, place in a baking pan. Bake in a 350°F oven for 2 hours. Are until real tender. Take out of oven and brush on Barbecue sauce, both sides. ( see below for receipe.) This is where you can finish on a grill or finish in the oven. If you choose to finish in the oven, turn oven on broil and cook uncovered for 5 or 10 minutes just to brown on each side. Same with grill. They are already tender and you are getting them brown and brushing on the wet sauce.\nServe hot.\n\nDry rub\n1 1/2 --------- Cups paprika\n3/4 ------------ Cup sugar\n3 3/4 --------- Tablespoons onion powder\n\nstir ingredients in a small bowl. Any left overs can be stored in an air-tight container in a cool place. You can store for up to 6 months. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.\n\nBarbecue sauce\n\n2 ----------- Cups ketchup\n1 ----------- cup water\n1/4 --------- cup light-brown sugar\n1/4 --------- cup granulated sugar\n1 1/2 ------ Teaspoons freshly ground black pepper\n1 1/2 ------  teaspoons onion powder\n1 1/2 ------  teaspoons dry mustard powder\n2 ------------ tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n2 ------------ tablespoons worcestershire sauce\n1/2 --------- cup apple-cider vinegar\n2 ------------ tablespoons light corn syrup\n1 ------------ tablespoons of dry rub listed above\n2 ------------ tablespoons of hickory liquid smoke\n\nCombine all of the ingredients in a large pot . Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring enough to keep from sticking Turn on low heat , and simmer, uncovered for at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove from the heat, cool, and use as needed. Store in a tightly sealed container, this will keep in the Ref. for up to 2 months.Makes about 2 cups.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(111,'Bread','Bread --- With starter',NULL,'Starter\n\n1 --------- package of dry yeast (2 1/4 teaspoons)\n2 1/4 ---- cup warm water ( 85 to 100 degrees.)\n1/2 ------- cup instant potatoes flakes\n1/2 ------- cup sugar\n2 ---------- Teaspoons salt\n\nDissolve yeast in warm water until bubbly. Add potato flakes, sugar, and salt and stir to combine. Cover loosely with plastic wrap and leave the starter out at room temperature for 24 hours.\n\nFeeding your starter\n\nkeep starter in refrigerator. Take starter out every 3 to 7 days and feed.\n\n3/4 ---------- cup sugar\n3 ------------- Tablespoons instant potato flakes\n1 ------------- Cup warm water\n\nMix all 3 ingredients (with a wooden spoonn) well before adding to starter, then mix into starter. Let stand out of refrigerator all day (8 ti 12 hours) this will bubble. ( I keep starter in a quart jar with a paper towel rubber banded on as a lid)\nUse 1 cup for making bed & return remaining starter to refrigerator until time to feed again. If not making bread just return starter to refrigerator after time is up. You may build up as much as 4 cups of starter. After that, you need to use the extra starter or give it to a friend or throw some away. You can mix more than one batch of bread at a time, but in separate bowls. You muat feed starter continually in order to keep it active.\n\nExample of feeding baking schedule:\nMon. 8 a m feed starter, leave out all day. About 7 or 8 pm take out 1 cup starter & make bread mixture. (return remaining starter to refrigerator) Cover dough with towl & let rise till morning. Tuesday morning kneed & shape loaves & let rise till mid afernoon. (you will be able to tell when it\'s as high as you want it. If it gets too big it gets air holes in it.) Bake when ready.\n\nSourdough Bread\n\n1/2 ---------- cup sugar\n1/2 ---------- cup corn oil\n1 1/2 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ------------  cup starter\n1 1/2 -------  cups warm water\n6 ------------  cups bread flour\n\nMix all ingredients with a (wooden or plastic spoon) Well in large bowl (plastic or glass.) let stand over nigh or about 12 hours. Covered with a towl. Do not refrigerate. Punch down & pour onto floured board, knead a fe times. Divide into 3 equal parts. ( I cut with a knife) How you shape it determines how the bread looks after baking. Put dough in loaf pans, that have been sprayed with Pam. Brush tops with oil let rise 6 to 8 hours or until ready. ( weather & tempature have a lot to do with this.)Do not cover while rising this time. Bake in a 350°F oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Or until golden brown on top. Tops will be real hard when it comes out of the oven. Rub tops with butter. Tops soften as they cool. This bread freezes really well, cuts best after cooled, ise a serrated knife.\n\nCinnamon Rolls',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(112,'vegetables','Vegetables --- Green Fried Tomaoes',NULL,'2 ---------- Cups cornmeal\n2 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n1 ---------- Tablespoon salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon black pepper\n2 ---------- pinches of cayenne pepper\n1 1/2 ----  Cups sour cream, Buttermilk can be used \n                 instead of sour cream.\n1 ---------- egg white\n4 ---------- large green tomatoes, sliced 1/2 inch thick\n1/2 ------- Cup vegetable oil, or I like to deep fry in \n                 peanut oil.\n\nIn a large bowl, combine the cornmeal, sugar, salt, pepper, and cayenne. Put the sour cream or buttermilk, in a separate bowl. Pat the tomatoe slices with a paper towel to dry a little before coating.Then Coat the tomato slices in the sour cream or buttermilk, and egg white,  then dredge them in the cornmeal mixture, coating both sides well.Heat the oil in a large cast-iron skillet or deep fryer, ( is what I like to use), over medium heat. Fry the tomatoes, working in batches, until they are crisp and golden, 3 to 4 minutes per sides. Transfer them to a paper towel-lined plate to drain. Serve hot.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(113,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Green Tomatoes Baked',NULL,'1/2 --------- Cup yellow cornmeal, I use what ever \n                   cornmeal I have on hand\n1/2 --------- Cup panko (Japanese bread crumbs)\n1 ------------ Teaspoon creole seasoning\n1 ------------ egg white\n2 ------------ green tomatoes, cut into 1/2 inch thick \n                   slices\n                   Garnish: chopped red bell pepper, & \n                   chopped fresh parsley\n\nPreheat oven to 375°F, Line a rimmed baking sheet with aluminum foil. Spray foil with nonstick cooking spray. In a shallow dish, combine cornmeal, bread crumbs, and creole seasoning. In a separate shallow dish, lightly beat egg white. Egg white works like a glue makes bread crumbs stick better.Dip each slice of tomato in beaten egg white: dredge in meal mixture to coat Place on prefared baking sheet.Sprey each tomato with nonstick cooking spray. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned. Garnish with bell pepper and parsley, if desired.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(114,'Cakes','Cake ---  Arkansas Black Walnut Caramel Frosting',NULL,'2 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 ------- Cup solid vegetable sortening\n1 1/2 ---- Cups granulated sugar\n2 ---------- large eggs\n2 ---------- large bananas, mashed\n1/4 ------- Cup buttermilk\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ---------- Cup chopped black walnuts \n\nPreheat the oven to 350°F. Grease and flour two 9 inch cake pans. ( I like to use the baking spray in a can.) For the cake: In a medium bowl, stir together the flour and baking soda; set aside. In  a large bowl, using an electric mixer, cream together the shortening and sugar, about 2 to 3 minutes. Add the eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Mix in the mashed bananas, buttermilk, and vanilla. Add the flour mixture; mix until just combined. Stir in the black walnuts. Pour into the prepared pans and bake until a toothpick inserted in the centers of the cakes come out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in the pans on a cooling rack for 10 minutes. Remove the cakes from the pans and cool completely.\n\nFrosting\n\n1/2 ----------  Cup butter, softened\n1 -------------  Cup packed light brown sugar\n1/3 ----------  Cup heavy cream, plus more as necessary\n1 -------------  Tablespoon pure vanilla extract\n1 ------------- 16 ounce box confectioners sugar\n2 ------------- Cups finely chopped black walnuts, for \n                     garnish.\n\nFor the frosting: Melt the butter in a small saucepan. Add the brown sugar and cream. Cook over medium-low heat until the sugar is dissolved, about 2 minutes. Remove from the heat and add vanilla. Transfer to a large bowl. Using a electric mixer, beat in the confectioners sugar a little at a time until smooth. If frosting is too thick, add 1 tablespoon heavy cream at a time until the consistency is right. Sandwich the two layers together with the frosting. Frost the outside of the cake. Press the chopped Black walnuts on the sides of the cake, if desired. Do not substitute English walnuts for Black walnuts. The two most common types of walnuts are Black walnuts and English walnuts. Black walnuts are stronger tasting than English walnuts, and they are richer and smoky with a hint of wine. Look for them online or by mail order if you can\'t find them near you. Believe me they are delishious. We have them growing wild in Arkansas and we use to pick them out by hand. The shell is very hard and they are a pain to pick out by hand. Just go buy some at the store.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(115,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Collard Greens & Corn Dumplins',NULL,'1 to 1 1/2 ----- pounds smoked turkey wings or neck\n2 ---------------- quarts chicken broth or water ( I like \n                         chicken broth.)\n1 ---------------- Teaspoon hot sauce\n1 ---------------- Teaspoon seasoning at bottom of page\n1 ---------------- pound bunch collards, center ribs \n                         removed, leaves cut into 1/2 inch strips.\n                         You can buy the frozen collards already \n                          cut, I have tried them and they are good.\n4 ----------------- Tablespoons or 1/2 stick butter\n\nIn a laarge pot, combine the turkey, broth, hot sauce, and seasoning; simmer for 20 minutes. Add the collards and cook, stirring occasionally, until they are tender, about 20 minutes more. Stir in the butter. Using a sloted spoon or tongs, remove the turkey and discard; or eat it. Transfer the collards to individual serving bowls, cover them with foil, and keep warm. Reserve the cooking liquid in the pot.\n\nDumplings\n\n1 1/2 -------------- Cups cornmeal\n1/2 ----------------- Cup all-purpose flour\n1 -------------------- Teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 ------------------ Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------------------ Teaspoon pepper\n1/2 ------------------ cup buttermilk, plus more if needed\n2 --------------------- eggs, lightly beaten\n\nTo make the dumplins, combine the cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt, and pepper in a bowl. In a saperate bowl, whisk together the buttermilk and eggs. Stir the wet mixture into the dry until just combine to form a thick batter. If the batter seems too dry, add 1 or 2 tblespoons buttermilk.\n\nBring the broth back up to a boil and drop the dumblins batter into it. Be sure dumplins are not to large. I teaspoon at a time. Simmer until cooked through, 20 to 25 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the dumplings to the bowls of collards. Spoonsome of the broth over the collards and dumplings and serve hot.\n\n\nSeasoning\n\n1 ------------------ cup salt\n1/4 --------------- cup black pepper\n1/4 --------------- cup garlic powder\n\nCombine all the ingredients. Store in an airtight container at room tempature for up to 6 months.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(116,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Turnip Greens & Ham Hock',NULL,'4 --------- pounds of greens 1/2 turnip greens and 1/2 \n                broad leaf mustard and I like to add a little \n                kyle\n1 --------- smoked ham hock or 3 or 4 small chunks of \n                salt meat\n1 ---------- Tablespoon sugar\n2 ---------- Teaspoons  salt\n                 A little black pepper to taste\n3 ---------- purple top turnips  peeled and cut in large \n                pieces.\n\nRemove and discard the stems and ribs of the greens, place the leaves in a sink or large pot of cold water, and swish around to remove all the dirt and grit, repeating the procedure with more fresh water if necessary. Tear the leaves into several pieces each and set aside. Place the ham hock or salt meat in a large pot and add enough water to cover. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat to low, simmer for 15 minutes, and add the sugar, pepper and salt. Return to a boil and gradually add the torn leaves.and the turnips, Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer the greens till very soft and tender, about 1 hour. The broth in the pot is very good with corn bread.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(117,'Sauces','Sauces --- Bar-  B-Que Wet Sauce','Fay\'s','2 --------- Cups katchup\n1 --------- Cup water\n1/4 ------ Cup light-brown sugar\n1/4 ------ Cupgranulated sugar\n1 1/2 ---  Teaspoons freshly ground black pepper\n1 1/2 ---  Teaspoon onion powder\n1 1/2 ---  Teaspoons dry mustard powder\n2 --------- Tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n2 --------- Tablespoons worcestershire sauce\n1/2 ------ Cup apple-cider vinegar\n2 --------- Tablespoons light corn syrup\n1 --------- Tablespoon barbeque season\n\nCombine all of the ingredients in a large pot or a dutch oven. Bring to a boil over heat, stirring frequently to prevent sticking. Reduce the tempature to very low and simmer, uncovered, for at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Remove from the heat, cool, and use as needed. Stored in a tightly sealed container, this sauce will keep in the fridge for up to 2 months. I use a slow cooker. Makes it easier for me.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(118,'Entree','Entree --- Beer Chicken',NULL,'1 --------- Whole frying size chicken\n                Take off wraper, Wash with clear water. I save\n                 any extra fat and giblet and put in freezer for \n                 later use , in giblet gravy are just cook when \n                 cooking chicken for dumplins. Dry with a \n                 paper towl inside and out. \n1/2 -------  stick of butter melted, and rub all over inside\n                 and out. Then rub with seasoning that \n                 followers. \n1 ---------- 12 oz can of beer\n\nCut top off can beer. Pour out about 1/4 cup. They sell special holders for the can of beer. But if you don\'t have one you can cook it anyway. Hold the bird upright, with the opening of the body cavity at the bottom, and lower it onto the beer can so the can fits onto the cavity. Pull the chicken legs forward to form a sort of a tripod, so the bird stands upright. Use a baking pan to place the upright chicken in and cover it with foil. This saves a lot of clean up when the baking is finished. Place in a 350 degree oven and cook for 45 minutes. Take a piece of foil  to lay over top of chicken so it want brown to much. Cook another 45 minutes. Use a meat thometer and cook until 160 to 165 degrees. You can cook the chicken on the grill almost the same way, medium heat for 1 1/2 hours, using a piece of foil  half way through grilling ,Lay over the top to keep the chicken from browing to much on top.\n\nSeasoning\n\n1 ---------- Cup salt\n1/4 ------- Cup pepper\n1/4 ------- Cup garlic powder\n\nServes about 2 to 4 people',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(119,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Sheepherder\'s',NULL,'1 ---------- pound sliced bacon, diced\n1 ---------- medium onion, copped\n1 ---------- package (26 ounces ) frozen shredded hash \n                 brown potatoes, thawed\n7 ---------- eggs\n                 salt & pepper to taste\n2 ---------- Cups ( 8 ounce ) shredded chedder cheese,\n                  optional\n                  Chopped fresh parsley\n\nIn a large non stick skillet,About a 10 inch skillet. cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp. Drain all but 1/2 cup of the drippings. Add hash browns to skillet; Mix  well. Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, turning when browned. Make seven \"wells\" evenly spaced in the hash brown. Place one egg in each well. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with cheese if desired. Cover and cook over low heat for about 10 minutes or until eggs are set. Garnish with parsley; serve immediately. Yield: 7 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(120,'Sauces','Sauces --- Bar-B-Que Dry Mix','Faye\'s','1 1/2 ---------- Cups paprika\n3/4 ------------- Cup sugar\n3 3/4 ---------- Tablespoons onion powder\n\nStir together the ingredients in a small bowl. Store in an airtight container in a cool, dry place, this seasoning will last for up to 6 months. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(121,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Molasses Baked Beans','Faye\'s','1 ---------- Tablespoon olive oil\n1/4 ------- Cup diced green bell pepper\n1/4 ------- Cup diced onion\n1 ---------- 48 oz. can Bush\'s baked beans\n1/4 -------- Cup molasses\n1/2 -------- Cup light-brown sugar\n1 ----------- Cup Faye\'s Barbeque wet sauce in this \n                  cook book\n1/3 -------- Cup Faye\'s Barbeque dry mix in this cook \n                  book\n1/2 --------- Cup chopped pork Barbeque, If I don\'t have\n                   any on hand,  pick it up at a good Barbeque\n                   place.\n\nPreheat oven to 275 degree. Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.Add the bell pepper and onion, and saute them until they soften, 4 to 5 minutes. Add the baked beans, molasses, browm sugar, Faye\'s Barbeque wet sauce and Faye\'s Barbeque dry mix to the skillet, and stir all the ingredients to combine. Transfer the bean mixture to a 9 by 13 inch baking pan. Add the meat, and stir well to combine. Cover the pan with aluminum foil, and bake 45  minutes. Allow the beans to cool slightly, then serve warm, If I am serving a large group I put them in a slow cooker on low. This will keep them warm until ready to serve.This will serve about 10 to 12 people.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(122,'Bread','Bread --- Cheddar Pepper Crisps',NULL,'1 3/4 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 ------------- Cup corn meal\n1/2 ------------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 ------------- Teaspoon sugar\n1/2 ------------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 -------------  Cup cold butter\n1 1/2 ----------- Cups (6 ounce) shredded sharp \n                         chedder cheese\n1/2 -------------- Cup cold water\n2 ----------------- Tablespoons white vinegar\n                          coarsely ground  black pepper\n\nIn a large bowl, combine the first ingredients. Cut in butter until crumbly. Stir in cheese. Sprinkle with water and vinegar. Toss with a fork until a ball forms. I use a food prosser to mix this. Wrap tightly in plastic wrap; Refrigerate for 1 hour or until dough is firm. Divide dough into six portions. On a lightly floured surface, roll each portion into an 8 inch circle. Cut into eight wedges and place on greased baking sheets. Sprinkle with pepper; lightly press into dough. Bake at 375°F oven for 10 or 14 minutes or until golden brown and crisp. Cool on wire racks. Store in an airtight containers. This makes about 4 dozen. These are good to eat by themselves are with soups or dips.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(123,'Pastery','Pastery --- Pastry With Milk',NULL,'2 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon salt\n2/3 ------- Cup shortening\n2 ---------- Tablespoon butter or margarine\n1/2 ------- Cup milk\n\nCombine flour and salt. Cut in shortening and butter with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkly milk, 1 Tablespoon at a time, evenly over surface; stir with a fork until dry ingregients are moistened. I use a food prosser to mix this, it works fine. Divide in half and shape into 2 balls; cover and chill for 30 minutes. Roll each portation to 1/4 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface. Place pastery in 2 (9 inch) pie plates; crimp and trim off excess pastry. Bake 375°F oven for 10 to 12 minutes. I like to increase this recipe by 1/2 more to make extra dough for edges of pastry. It makes a much prettier pastry if the edge of the pie pastry is a little thicker. After you have made the pastry in the pan use extra dough around edges, and the thickness of the pastry will let you design edge the way you want to.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(124,'Salads','Salad --- Kenny\'s Wilted Salad','My Mother\'s Recipe','6 --------- Cups chopped tender lettuce\n6 --------- Cups chopped tender mustard greens\n6 --------- Slices of thick sliced bacon cooked and \n                chopped. Save bacon drippings.\n1 --------- Cup green onions chopped, with green parts.\n1 --------- Tablespoon vinegar\n1 --------- Teaspoon brown sugar\n                salt & pepper to taste\n\nMix in a large salad bowl lettuce, mustard greens, onions & bacon. Mix in a small bowl vinegar, sugar, bacon drippengs,(enough to coat sald, and bacon greese must be hot), salt & pepper. Pour immediately over salad. Toss to serve.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(125,'Salad','Salad --- Tomato',NULL,'5 --------- medium sized ripe tomatoes sliced 1/4 inch \n               thick.\n1/4 ------ Cup olive oil\n1/4 ------ Cup vegetable oil\n1 --------- Tablespoon wine vinegar\n1 --------- Tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n1 --------- clove garlic crushed\n1 --------- Tablespoon dried basil\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon pepper\n1 --------- bunch green onions, chopped\n1 --------- Tablespoon parsley\n\nArrange tomatoes slices overlapping on platter. Mix oil, vinegar, lemon juice, garlic, basil, salt & pepper. Spoon over tomatoes. Combine green onions and parsley. Sprinkle over salad. May be made ahead and refrigerated. Serves 4 to 6.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(126,'Salads','Salad --- Goat Cheese & Taangerine Vinaigrette',NULL,'2 ---------- tangerines\n2 ---------- Teaspoons cider vinegar\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon dijon mustard\n                 salt and black pepper\n2 ---------- Tablespoons olive oil\n1 ---------- Tablespoon chopped fresh chives\n8 ---------- Cups loosely packed mixed baby greens, \n                 such as romaine, arugula, and/ or spinach \n                 ( about 5 ounces)\n1/2 -------- Cup crumbled goat cheese ( 2 ounces)\n1/4 -------- Cup golden raisins\n\nFrom tangerines, grate 1 Teaspoon peel; place in small bowl. Cut remaining peel and pith from fruit. Holding tangerines, 1 at a time, over another small bowl, cut on either side of membranes to remove each segment, allowing fruit and juice to drop into bowl. Squeeze 3 tablespoons juice from membranes; add to bowl with peel. Whisk in vinegar, mustard, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/8 teaspoon pepper until mixed. In thin , steady stream, whisk in oil until vinaigrette is blended. Stir in tangerine segments and chives. Place greens on 4 salad plaates; sprinkle each with goat cheese and raisins. Drizzle with vinaigrette.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(127,' Dessert','Desserts --- Maringue Toped With Lemon Sauce',NULL,'8 --------- egg whites\n1 --------- Teaspoon cream of tarter\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla\n2 --------- Cups of sugar\n1 --------- Teaspoon vinegar\n\nBeat egg whites, add sugar and cream of tarter, then vinegar, and vanilla. Put in an ungreased spring-form 10 inch pan and bake in 275 degree oven for about 2 hours. Top with lemon filling, or other fillings you might like.\n\nLemon Fillimg\n\n5 ---------- egg yolks\n1/3 ------- Cup lemon juice\n1 ---------- Tablespoon butter\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n2 ---------- Tablespoons flour or cornstarch\n\nMix all ingredients together and cook in double-boiler until thick, cool a little and top the meringue with this filling. Ice the whole dessert with whipped cream ( 1 pint). Serves 10 - 12.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(128,'Pies','Pies --- Fresh Strawberry Pie',NULL,'1 1/2 ---------- Cups sugar\n1 1/2 ---------- Cups water\n1/4 ------------- Cup cornstarch\n1 ---------------- Quart fresh strawberries\n1 ---------------- ( 4 ounces) box strawberry Jell-o\n1 ---------------- ( 9 inch) pie crust\n1 ---------------- small container cool whip or make your\n                         own whipped cream, That\'s what I \n                         perfer.\nBring sugar, water and cornstarch to a boil. Remove from stove. Add Jell-o and cool, when cool, add sliced berries to a 9 inch cooked pie crust. Top with whip cream.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(129,'Cookies','Cookies --- Hershey Delight',NULL,'1 ---------- ( 8 ounce) Hershey bar with almonds\n1/3 ------- Cup milk\n1 ---------- Tablespoon cocoa\n20 --------  large marshallows, cut up\n1 ---------- (9 ounce ) contaiiner cool whip\n1 ---------- graham cracker crust. You can find this under\n                 pie pastry.                                                           \n\nBreak candy into pieces; add cocoa to milk, put candy, milk mixture and marshallows in double boiler to melt. Cool. Add cool whip and pour into graham crackers crust. Refrigerate overnight.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(130,' Desserts','Desserts --- Sweet Potatoe Cups',NULL,'6 ---------- small sweeet potatoes ( about 2 3/4 lb)\n8 ---------- large navel oranges\n1 ---------- ( 14 ounce) can sweetened condensed milk\n3 ---------- Tablespoons melted butter\n2 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n2 ---------- Teaspoon orange zest\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon ground nutmeg\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon ground allspice\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1 ---------- Cup miniature marshallows\n\nPreheat oven to 425°F . Place sweet potatoes on an aluminum foil-lined baking sheet. Bake at 425°F for 45 minutes until tender. Let ,stand 20 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°F. Meanwhile, cut oranges in half crosswise. Scoop out pulp using a spoon, leaving peel intact. Reserve orange pulp for another use. Peel sweet potatoes, and place potatoes pulp in a large bowl. Add sweetened condensed milk and next 7 ingredients. Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth, stopping occasionally to remove any tough fibers, if necessary. Spoon about 1/2 cup mixture into each orange cup. Place orange cups in a 13 by 9 inch baking dish. Bake at 350°F for 20 minutes. Remove from oven, and top with marshallows, pressing lightly to adhere. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until marshallows are melted and golden brown.\nOrange cups and sweet potatoes can be made 1 day ahead. Chill scooped orange cups and baked sweet potatoes in separarte zip-lock plastic bags until ready to assemble.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(131,'Pickles','Pickles --- Sweet Pickles','Faye\'s','Make pickles in an old timer crock churn. To make brine, Mix enough salt in water to float an egg. Put whole cucumbers in salt water to cover. Let set for 10 days. Wash cucumbers and crock with clear water.Let set in cold water for 3 days. Be sure all cucumbers are covered. Take out of crock. For each gallon of vinegar, 1 small box of alum. Pour over cucumbers and let set for 3 more days.Take out of crock, do not wash. Slice cucumbers 1/4 inch thick.For each gallon of sliced pickles, use 4 pounds of sugar. Put in layer of pickles and then 1 layer of sugar. Pour1 box pickling spice on top. Then 1 ( 12 ounce) bottle Heinz tarragon vinegar. These pickles do not have to be sealed or refrigerated. This is a little trouble ,but after they set 2 or 3 days I do not like the pickeling spice all over the pickles, so I take them out and ricse in clear water to get all the spices off, strain the liquid on the pickles and get all the spices off then put the pickles back in the jar. Then you do not have all of the spices on the pickles.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(132,'Cakes','Cake --- Orange','Aunt Lyla Martin','1 ---------- Cup crisco\n2 ---------- Cups sugar\n1 ---------- Cup milk\n3 ---------- eggs\n2 ---------- Cups self-rising flour\n                 Add 1 or 2 drops food color\n\nMix all ingredients above and pour into two 8 inch cake pans ( well-greased and floured ). Bank in 350°F oven until light brown. About 30 minutes. Cool on rack.\n\nIcing\n\n2 --------- Cups sugar\n1 --------- Cup water\n1/2 ------ Cup white karo syrup\n1 --------- large apple, peeled and cored\n2 --------- Oranges  unpeeled\n\nCook sugar, karo syrup and water intil medium soft ball stage. Grind oranges with peeling and add apple, peeled-grind small. Mix with cooked syrup. It can be mixed while still warm. For extra moist cake, pierce cake with knife several times and pour iceing between layers and over top of cake.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(133,'Piea','Pies --- Strawberry Meringue',NULL,'1/3 ---------- finely crushed saltines ( about 12 crackers)\n                    divided\n3 ------------- egg whites\n1/4 ---------- Teaspoon cream of tartar\n1/8 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ------------- Cup sugar\n1 ------------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1/2 ---------- Cup chopped pecans, toasted. ( Put \n                    pecans on a cookie sheet in a 350 degree \n                    oven, only takes a few minutes, watch them\n                    real close).\n1 ------------- package ( 4 ounces) Milk chocolate\n2 ------------- Tablespoons butter\n4 ------------- Cups fresh strawberries, halved\n1 ------------- Cup heavy whipping cream\n2 ------------- Tablespoons confectioners sugar\n\nSprinkle 2 Tablespoons of cracker crumbs into a greased 9 inch pie plate. IN a mixing bowl, beat egg whites, cream tartar and salt until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff peals form. Fold in vanilla, pecans and remaining\ncracker crumbs. Spread meringue onto the bottom and up the sides of the prepared pan. Bake at 300°F for 45 minutes. Turn off oven and do not open door; let cool in oven overnight. In a microve bowl melt chocolate and butter,about 1 minute. Drizzle over meringue. Let stand 15 minutes or until set. Top with berries. Whip cream and confectioners sugar until soft peaks form; spoon over berries. YIIELDS 6 to 8 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(134,'Salads','Salad --- Strawberry Pear Gelatin',NULL,'1 --------- Can ( 29 ounce ) pears\n1 --------- Package ( 6 ounce) strawberry gelatin\n1 --------- Package ( 8 ounce) cream cheese, cubed\n1 --------- carton ( 8 once ) frozen whipped topping \n                thawed\n\nDrain pears, reserving juice. Chop pears and set aside. Add water to the juice to measure 3 cups. Place in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Transfer to a large bowl. Add gelatin and stir until dessolved. Whisk in cream cheese untill smooth. Refrigerate until slightly thickened. Whisk in whipped topping until smooth. Add chopped pears. Transfer to a 9 by 13 inch dish, and 2 inche deep. Cover and refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares. Garnish with mandarin orange, and a mint leaf. Serves 12 to 16 serving.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(135,'Cakes','Cake --- Coconut Pound',NULL,'6 ---------- eggs\n2 1/2 ----- Cups sugar\n2 ---------- Cups butter\n3 ---------- Cups self-rising flour\n1 ---------- Cup milk\n1/2 -------- Cup sour cream\n1 ----------- Teaspoon vanilla\n1/2 -------- Cup cocoanut cream\n\nBeat eggs well; add sugar, butter, flour, milk, sour cream, vanilla, and coconut cream. Mix well. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350°F oven 1 hour.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(136,'Pastery','Pastery --- Flaky Pie or Tart Dough',NULL,'1 ---------- stick of buttter cut in 1/2 inch pieces\n4 ---------- Tablespoons cold water\n1 1/4 ----- Cups all purpose flour\n1 ----------- Tablespoon sugar\n1/4 -------- Teaspoon salt\n\nMix flour, sugar and salt in a food prosser and mix well. Add butter and water mix until you can form a ball. Wrap in plastic and put in ref. for 1 hour. Take out of ref. and sprinkle a little flour on a sheet of wax paper, roll out to about 1/8 inch thick and place over pie plate. This is for 9 inch pie.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(137,'Pastery','Pastery --- What You Should Know',NULL,'Combine ingredients for crust and chill dough for ten minutes in the refrigerator. This reduces the amount of flour needed when rolling crust. (Excess flour toughens crust.)\nToo much moisture in the dough will make the crust tough and cause the pie to steam rather than bake. Handle dough as little as possible after adding water, and use a pastry cloth and stockinet covered rolling pin when rolling the crust. Besides creating a tender, flaky crust, you will use less flour and fewer strokes.\n\nPastry may be rolled between two sheets of wax paper. Peel off the top paper and flip the bottom into the pie pan. Removeing the paper. When placing a crust in the pan, be sure it covers the surface smoothly. If air is trapped beneath the surface, it can push the crust out of shape when baking. For a two crust pie, fold the top crust over the lower crust before crimping it. This will keep the juices in the pie. \nTo prevent a soggy bottom crust, brush surface with well beaten egg white before adding the filling and cool pie on a rack after baking. When baking a pie shell, place another pie pan on top of crust to prevent \"bubbling\" of the crust. Bubbling may also be prevented by pricking crust all over with fork.\n                             Fruit Pies\nFruit pies are especially tempting during the summer months when fresh fruit is at its peak. To save time when cooking the fruit, add sugar after the cornstarch (or flour) has been added to the hot juice.\nA few pieces of large macaroni inserted though the top crust or drinking straws (cut into short pieces) place in the slits of the crust will prevent juices from running out and will allow steam to esccape. (If the juice does run over in the oven, shake salt on it. This causes it to burn to a crisp so it is easily removed.)\n                             Custard Pies\nThere are many types of custard pies ranging from pumpkin to refigerator. Custard pies may be baked and frozen or may be made ahead and frozen unbaked. A frozen 8 inch pie will bake in one hour at 400°F 400°F. When baking a custard pie that has not been frozen, bake at a high temperature for ten minutes; then finish baking at a lower temperature. This prevents a soggy crust. A layer of marshmallow placed in the bottom of a pumpkin pie before the filling makes an excellent topping because the marshmallows rise to the top. Always remove a pie from the refrigerator 20 minutes before serving to remove the chill from the crust.\n                          Crumb Crust Chart\nGraham Crackers (18) --------- 1 1/2 cups \nSugar--------------------------------- 1/4 cup\nButter -------------------------------- 1/2 cup\n\n                       Vanilla Wafer Crust\nVanilla Wafers (38) --------------- 1 1/4 cups\nButter ---------------------------------- 1/2 cup\n\n                        Ginger Snaps\nGinger Snaps (24) ----------------- 1 1/4 cups\nButter ----------------------------------- 1/3 cup\n\n                          Chocolate Wafers\nChocolate Wafers ------------------- 1 1/4 cups\nButter ------------------------------------ 1/3 cup\n\nMix ingredients well and press into a 9 inch pie plate. Bake approximately 10 minutes at 375°F.\n\n                           General Tips\nPie crust will stay together better if one tablespoon lemon juice is added to the crust as it is mixed.\nTo avoid tough pie pastries, do not use all butter.\nTo measure shortening, fill the cup with water less the amount desired. Add the shortening then pour out the water.\nTo keep a pie from being soggy do not pour the filling into the pastry shell until just before baking.\nBrushing the top pie crust with milk before baking will make it brown and glossy.\nThere is a difference in pie pans. Shinny metal pans do not bake bottom crust well. Use aluminum pans with a dull finish or heat proof glass pie plates. When baking fruit pies, place a sheet of aluminum foil directly under pie plate on the bottom of the oven to catch the drippings from the pie.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(138,'Pastery','Pastery --- Crust Basic',NULL,'1 --------- Cup all-purpose flour\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon salt\n1/3 ------ Cup shortening\n3 --------- Tablespoon cold water\n\nSift flour and salt together. Cut in shorting with pastry blender until mixture resembles small peas. Sprinkle water over mixture while tossing lightly with a fork until particles stick together. Form into a smooth ball. Wrap in wax paper and chill. Lightly roll pastry into a circle 1-inch larger than pie plate. Lift into pie plate, pat out air, fold edges under and crimp. Prick crust thoroughly. Bake approximately 12 minutes at 450°F or until golden brown. Cool and fill. Yields 1  8 or 9 inch crust.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(139,'Pies','Pies --- English Pie',NULL,'1 --------- 9 inch Graham pie shell\n2 --------- can sweetened condensed milk\n3 --------- Bananas sliced\n1 1/2 ---- Cups whipping cream\n1/3 ------- Cup confectioner sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla\n1----------- package sugar substitute\n\n                   Pie Shell\n1 1/2 ----- Cups graham crackers about (18).\n1/4 -------- Cup sugar\n1/2 -------- Cup softened butter\nMix well, press in a 9 inch pie plate.Bake approximatly 10 minutes at 375°F degrees.\n\nYou will need 2 baking pans for baking. Pour condensed milk in a 9 by 13 inch pan covered with foil. Place in a larger pan with enough water to cover 1/2 up sides of pan. Place in a 300°F for 1 1/2 hours. Take out of oven and pour 1/2 in baked pie shell, Then slice bananas and place over baked milk. Pour the other half over bananas.\n\n                          Whipping Cream\nWhip Cream until soft peaks, and add confection sugar, vanilla and substitute sugar. Beat until stiff peaks. Spread over top of pie.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(140,'Frosting','Frosting --- Non-Weeping Meringue',NULL,'3 ---------- egg whites\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon cream of tarter\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon baking powder, optional\n3 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nBeat eggs with cream of tarter until foamy. Add 1/2 Teaspoon baking powder if extra high meringue is desired. Gradually add sugara until peaks are stiff and glossy. Spread meringue on pie and seal all edges. Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned, at 400°F oven. Cool away from drafts.\n\nMeringue will not shrink if spread on the pie so that it touches the crust on each side. Bake meringue in a moderate oven. Cool baked meringue slowly away from drafts. Tears form if meringue is cooled too quickly.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(141,'Bread','Bread --- Rich Dinner Crescent Rolls',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup milk\n1/4 ------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------- Cup butter or margarine\n1/2 ------- Cup warm water (105 - 110 degrees)\n2 ---------- packages of yeast\n2 ---------- eggs beaten\n5 1/2 ----- Cups all purpose flour. I mix dough with \n                 a Kitchen - Aid mixer. Save about 1/2 cup  \n                  of flour to knead on board. I make 2 recipes\n                  at one time, This is a easy way to measure \n                  the flour, take 4 1/2 cups out of a 5 pound\n                  bag, and this measures 11 cups.\n\nScald milk; stir in sugar, salt and butter. Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water into large bowl. Sprinkle in yeast. Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and two cups of flour. Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough. Turn onto floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl, turning to greasetop.  (I use spray Pam). Cover; let rise in warm place free from draft until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour Punch down. Turn into lightly floured board. Divide into 3 equal pieces, roll into a circle 12 inches in diameter. Brush with melted butter. Cut into 8 pie shaped pieces. A pizza cutter works great . Roll tightly, beginning at wide end. Seal points firmly. Placce on greased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart. Cover; let rise in warm place, about 30 minutes. Brush with melted butter. Bake at 400°F oven for 12 minutes. Makes 24 large rolls.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(142,'Candy','Candy --- English Toffee',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup butter or margarine\n1 1/3 ---- Cups sugar\n1 ---------- Tablespoon light corn syrup\n2 ---------- Tablespoons water\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla\n1/2 -------- Cup milk chocolate chips\n1/3 -------- Cup finely chopped nuts\n\nCombine butter, sugar, corn syrup and water in a deep 2 quart bowl. Microwave, uncovered on full power for 4 minutes. Stir. Microwave 6 minutes, stirring the last few minutes. Stir in vanilla. Pour onto ungreased 9 by 13 inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips over toffee and spread evenly. Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate. When cool, break into pieces.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(143,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Quiche',NULL,'1 ---------- 9 inch pie crust\n1/4 ------- Cup sliced green onions\n1 ---------- Tablespoon butter\n6 ---------- eggs\n1 1/2 ----- Cups heavy whipping cream\n1/4 -------- Cup unsweetened apple juice\n1 ----------- pound sliced bacon cooked and crumbled\n1/8 -------- Teaspoon salt\n1/8 -------- Teaspoon pepper\n2 ----------- Cups (8 ounces) shredded swiss cheeese\n\nLine 9 inch pie plate with pastery; trim and flute edges. Set aside. In a small skillet, saute green onions in butter until tender. In a large bowl, whisk the eggs, cream and juice. Stir in the bacon, salt, pepper and green onions. Pour into pastry; sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350°F oven for 50 minutes or unatil a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting. In the last half of the baking cover the edges so they want get to brown. Serves 6.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(144,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Night Before Mashed Potatoes',NULL,'10 ---------- potatoes peeled\n8 ------------ ounces cream cheese, softened\n1 ------------ Cup sour cream\n                    salt & pepper to taste\n                    butter\n                    seasoned salt\n\nBoil and drain potatoes.Whip hot potatoes adding cream cheese and sour cream. Continue beating until fluffy and smooth. Add salt and pepper. Place in a buttered 9 by 13 inch baking dish. Dot generously with butter and sprinkle with seasoned salt. Cover with foil and refrigerate. Potatoes can be frozen at this stage and thawed before bakeing. Bake, covered with foil, 15 minutes at 325°F  continue baking, uncovered, 20 minutes. Serves 10 to 12 people. A pinch of baking soda added to mashed potatoes will make them fluffer.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(145,'Cookies','Cookies --- Toffee Almond Sandies',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup butter\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- Cup confectioners sugar\n1 ---------- Cup vegetable oil\n2 ---------- eggs\n1 ---------- Teaspoon almond extract\n3 1/2 ----- Cups all-purpose flour\n1 ---------- Cup whole wheat flour. If you don\'t have \n                 whole wheat , use all-purpose flour.\n1 ---------- Teaspoon baking powder\n1 ---------- Teaspoon cream of tarter\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n2 ---------- Cups chopped almonds\n1 ---------- Cup english toffee bites. I buy  Heath candy \n                 chopped .\n                 Additional sugar. I do not use this.\n\nIn a mixing bowl, cream buttter and sugar. Add oil eggs and extract; mix well. Combine flours, baking soda, cream of tarter and salt; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in almonds and toffee bits. Shape into 1- inch balls; roll in sugar. Place on ungreased baking sheets; flatten with a fork. Bake at 350°F oven for 12 - 14 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove to wire rack to cool, Yields about 12 dozen.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(146,'Pies','Pies --- Honey Pecan Pie',NULL,'4 --------- eggs\n1 --------- Cup chopped pecans\n1 --------- Cup light corn syrup\n1/4 ------ Cup sugar\n1/4 ------ Cup light brown sugar\n2 --------- Tablespoon butter, melted\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------  unbaked pastery shell (9 inches)\n\nTopping:\n\n3 --------- Tablespoons butter\n1/3 ------ Cup packed light brown sugar\n3 --------- Tablespoons honey\n1 --------- Cup chopped pecans\n1/2 ------- Cup pecan halves\n\nIn a large bowl, combine the eggs, pecans, corn syrup, sugars, butter, vanilla and salt. Pour into pastery shell. Bake at 350°F oven for 30 minutes. In a small saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Stir in the brown sugar, honey  and pecans until combine. Spoon over pie. Bake 15-20 minutes longer or until bubbly and golden brown. Cool completely on a wire rack. Refrigerate leftovers. Yields 8 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(147,'Sauces','Sauces --- Cranberry Cream Cheese',NULL,'1 --------- 8 ounce container whipped cream cheese\n2 --------- Tablespoons mayonnaise\n1/2 ------ Cup finely chopped pecans\n2 --------- 16 ounce cans jellied cranberry sauce, chilled\n\nMix the cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy. Add the pecans and stir until well mixed. Remove the lids from the cranberry sauce cans. Run a knife around the inside of the cans to loosen the sauce. Slide the cranberry sauce whole from each can. Slice the cramberry sauce into 1/4 inch rounds (you will get about 7 to 8 slices per can). Spread the cream cheeese mixture on half the rounds and place another round on top, like a sandwich. Cut each round in half and place on a pretty white dish. Cover with plastic wrap. Keep in the refrigerator until ready to serve. This can be made several hours in advance.Serves 14 to 16.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(148,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Green Beans In A Bundle',NULL,'2 ---------- pounds fresh green beans, trimmed or use \n                 whole green beans in a can\n1/2 -------  pound bacon, cut in half crosswise\n1 ---------- Cup firmly packed brown sugar\n1 ---------- Tablespoon soy sauce\n1/2 ------- Cup butter\n\nPreheat oven to 350°F. Line a rimmed baking sheet with heavy-duty aluminum foil.\n\nIn a large Saucepan, combine beans and water to cover. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat; reduce and simmer 3 minutes. Drain; plunge beans into ice water to stop the cooking process, and drain again.\n\nWrap about 5 beans in 1 slice bacon. Place seam side down on prepared baking sheet. Repeat process with remaining beans and bacon.\n\nIn a small bowl combine brown sugar, soy sauce and butter. Spoon mixture over green bean bundles. Bake 30 to 40 minutes, or until bacon is crisp. Serve immediately. Serves 10 to 12. I make ahead and freeze until ready to serve. Thaw, then bake.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(149,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Viking Tomatoes --- Baked',NULL,'This recipe is from the Viking cooking school.\n\n3 ---------- (1 pound) cans diced tomatoes drained well\n                 zest of one lemon\n4 ---------- cloves minced garlic\n1----------- Cup chopped parsley\n4 ---------- Cups fresh bread crumbs, whole wheat \n                 prefered\n2/3 -------- Cup light brown sugar\n2/3 -------- Cup butter, melted\n                  Salt & pepper to taste\n\nPreheat oven 350°F \n\nBe sure tomatoes are drained well. Combine the garlic, lemon zest, and parsley. Arrange the tomatoes in a 9 by 13 inch baking dish. Combine the bread crumbs and sugar. Add melted butter and mix well. Distribute evenly over the tomatoes. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. Bake for 25 minutes, or until hot and bubbling. You can make your bread crumbs, chopped in a  food processer.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(150,'Cookies','Cookies --- Chocolate Chips',NULL,'2/14 cup all purpose flour\n1 teaspoon baking soda\n1 teaspoon salt\n1 cup butter, softened\n3/4 cup sugar\n3/4 cup packed brown sugar\n1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n2 eggs\none bag chocolate chips\n1 cup chopped nuts (optional)\n\nPreheat oven to 375.\nIn small bowl, mix flour, baking soda and salt, set aside.\nIn large bowl, mix butter, sugar, b sugar, vanilla extract.\nBeat until creamy.\nBeat in eggs.\nGradually add flour mix.\nMix well.\nStir in chips and nuts.\nDrop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.\nBake 375 degrees 8-10 min.\nMakes 100 cookies.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(151,'Bread','Bread --- Creaps',NULL,'These are the thin, French pancakes.\nMakes about 12.\n1 cup flour\n2 teaspoon sugar (for sweet crepes)\n2 extra large eggs\n2 tablespoon melted butter\n\nMake batter and let stand for 20 min.\nBatter should be consistency of heavy cream, without lumps.\nHeat an 8 in pan over med.\nWhen water sizzles on pan immediately, it is ready to cook.\nGrease pan with butter/margarine/oil.\nLadle or pour 3-4 tablespoon batter into pan.\nQuickly tilt and rotate pan so batter spreads evenly and covers most of pan.\nCook until crepe is set and small holes appear, 30-45 sec.\nShake pan back and forth to loosen crepe, then turn or flip over.\nCook other side 30 sec.\nStack cooked crepes until ready.\n\nTraditionally, English eat before lent on \"pancake day\" (shrove or fat Tuesday, Mardi Gras), in Order to clear house of flour, sugar and eggs before fasting. We have pancake races where You run in a race while flipping pancakes. \n\nFilling:\nTraditional English \"pancakes\" are covered with fresh squeezed lemon juice and sugar at time of eating, one at a time.\n\nAnother recipe for crepes:\n4 oz flour\nPinch salt\n1 egg\n1/4 pint milk\n1/4 cup water\n\nNutella is outstanding (in store next to peanut butter).\n\nAlso good with bananas, real maple syrup, jam, apple sauce, etc',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(152,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Glazed Pecans','Faye Thompson','1/4 cup butter or margarine\n1/4 cup light corn syrup\n2 tablespoon water\n1 teaspoon salt\n1 lb pecans\n\nHeat oven 250.\nLine baking sheet w/ foil.\nCombine butter, corn syrup, water and salt in saucepan.\nBring to a boil.\nAdd pecans.\nCompletely coat nuts.\nSpread nuts evenly on lined baking sheet.\nBake 1 hr stirring every 10 min.\nCover and serve.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(153,'Salad','Salad --- Vegetable Layered Salad',NULL,'Head of lettuce\nBunch of spinach\nBunch of broccoli\nHead of cauliflower\nLarge onion\n1/4 cup sugar\n1/2 cup parmesan cheese\n1lb bacon, crumbled\n2 1/2 cup mayonnaise\nMix greens/veggies in large bowl.\nSpread mayo (not salad dressing) over top, then cheese, then sugar, then bacon.\nCover completely and chill overnight.\nWhen ready to serve, toss completely.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(154,'Salad','Salad --- Autumn Salad',NULL,'1 head red leaf lettuce\n1 head iceberg lettuce\n1 cup water cress leaves\n2 red delicious apples \n3/4 cup glazed pecans\n3/4 cup blue cheese crumbles\n\nDressing:\n1/2 cup walnut or vegetable oil\n1/4 cup cider vinegar\n2 tablespoon shallot mince\n2 tablespoon lemon juice fresh sq\n1 tablespoon maple syrup\n1/2 teaspoon salt\n1/4 teaspoon fresh pepper\n\nGlazed orange pecans\nCook sugar and hot water until it spins a thread. Add orange juice, rind, and salt.Cook for 1 minute. Beat and add pecans. Pour on oil paper and break into pieces when cool.\n\nCandied Pecans\n1/4 -------------- Cup butter \n1/2 -------------- Cup brown sugar\n1 ----------------- Teaspoon cinnamon\n1/4 --------------  Teaspoon ground cloves\n2 ----------------- Cups pecans halves.\n\nMelt butter in a quart casserole dish for 30-45 seconds. Stir in sugar and spices. Cook on high for 1 to 2 minutes until sugar is dissolved. Stir in nuts until well coated. Cook for 4 to 5 minutes on high. Spread on waxed paper to cool.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(155,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Ham Pie',NULL,'3 tablespoon chopped onion\n1/4 cup chopped green pepper\n1/4 cup fat\n6 tablespoon flour\n10 oz can condensed chicken soup\n1 1/3 cup milk\n1 1/2 cup diced cooked ham\n1 tablespoon lemon juice\n1 recipe cheese biscuit dough\nSauté onion and green pepper in fat.\nStir in flour, add soup milk and cook till thickened.\nAdd ham and lemon.\nMix and pour into greased baking dish.\nRoll out dough on floured board, cut with doughnut cutter.\nArrange on top of ham mix.\nBake 450 for 15 min.\nReduce to 425 and bake 10 more.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(156,'Pastery','Pastery --- Sour Cream Pastery','Mary Alice','2 1/2 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour, more for rolling \n                        out the dough\n1 ---------------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------------- Teaspoon granulated sugar\n1/2 ------------- Cup butter, chilled and cut into small \n                        pieces\n1/2 ------------- Cup shortening, chilled and cut into small\n                        pieces\n1 ---------------- Tablespoon sour cream\n4 or 5 ---------- Tablespoons ice water\n\nPlace the flour, salt, and sugar in the bowl of a food processor fitted with the steel blade and pulse to combine. Add the butter to the flour mixture and give the food processer 5 short pulses. Add the shortening and give it another 5 short pilses. Add the sour cream and give it 5 final short pulses. Turn the mixture into a large bowl.\nSprinkle 3 tablespoons of ice water over the mixture. Using a rubber spatula, press down on the dough until it sticks together. Add more ice water if needed, 1 tablespoon at a time. Divide the dough in half, shape each piece into a ball with your hands, and then flatten into a disk. Dust each half lightly with flour, wrap in plastic, and refrigerate at least 30 minutes before rolling out.\nTo roll out the dough, lightly flour a rolling pin and the countertop. Using 1 disk (half of recipe), roll the dough into a circle that is 2 inches larger than the pie pan. Lightly flour the top of the roller dough using a pastery brush. Fold the dough in half, then in half again. Place the folded dough in the prepared pan and unfold. Trim the excess dough to 1/2 inche and fold under around the edges. After shaping, chill the dough for at least 30 minutes  before filling or baking.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(157,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Sasuage Ring With Scrambled Eggs',NULL,'Sausage Ring\n\n2 ---------- eggs\n2 ---------- Tablespoons grated  onion\n1 ---------- Cup fine dry bread crumbs\n1/4 ------- Cup chopped parsley\n1 1/2 ----  pounds bulk pork sausage\n8 ---------  eggs scrambled\n\nBeat 2 eggs in large bowl. Add onion, bread crumbs, parsley and sausage. Mix thoroughly. Pack mixture into a greased 8 1/2- inch ring mold. Bake 20 minutes at 350°F oven. Remove from oven and drain off fat. Bake 20 minutes longer. Drain; turn out onto heated platter and fill center with scrambled eggs. Serve with Spanish Sauce on the side so guest can spoon over the eggs and sausage.\n\nSpanish Sauce\n\n3 --------- Tablespoons vegetable oil\n1/3 ------ Cup chopped onion\n1/4 ------ Cup chopped green pepper\n3/4 ------ Cup sliced mushrooms \n1 --------- Tablespoon cornstarch\n1 --------- (16 ounce) can diced tomatoes\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n               dash of pepper\n2 --------- Teaspoons sugar\n                dash of cayenne pepper\n\nHeat oil; add onion, pepper and mushrooms. Cook until lightly browned. Combine cornstarch with 2 tablespoons of juice from the tomatoes. Add to vegetable mixture with the tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar and cayenne. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently about 15 minutes until thickened. Make 3 cups. Yield: 8 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(158,'Salad','Salad --- Hot Chicken',NULL,'4 ---------- Cups cooked chicken cut in snall pieces use \n                 fresh cooked chicken. Do not use canned.\n                 Brest of chicken is better.\n2 ----------- Cups chopped celery\n2 ----------- Teaspoons lemon juice\n6 ----------- diced hard boiled eggs\n1 ----------- Cup grated sharp cheese\n1 ----------- Tablespoon minced onion\n2 ----------- Teaspoons salt\n1 1/2 ------ Cups Hellman\'s mayonnaise\n2/3 --------- Cup slivered almonds,  I like them toated\n1 1/2 ------ Cup crushed potato chips\n\nMix all ingredients (except cheese and chips) and leave in refrigerator overnight. When ready to bake, sprinkle cheese and potato chips over top. Bake 375°F oven for 25 minutes. Allow to stand 10-15 minutes after removing from oven before cutting.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(159,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Casserole',NULL,'12 --------- slices white bread\n1 ----------- pound bacon, fried\n1 ----------- bunch green onions (about nine), sliced\n3 ----------- Cups finely shredded extra-sharp chedder \n                  cheese\n12 ---------  eggs, beaten\n4 ------------ Cups half-half\n1 ------------ Teaspoon salt\n1 ------------ Teaspoon white pepper or black pepper, \n                    white looks a little better\n1/2 --------- Cup shredded parmesan cheese\n                   butter, enough to coat a 9 by 13 baking dish\n\nGenerously butter a 9 by 13-inch baking dish. Line the bottom with 6 pieces of bread. Crumble half the cooked bacon over the bread. Sprinkle half the onion and half the chedder cheese over the bacon. Mix the eggs, half-and-half, salt, and pepper until blended. Pour half of it evenly over the bread-cheese layers. Repeat the layering with remaining bread, bacon, onoin, and  chedder cheese. Pour the remaining egg-cream mixture over the top. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. \n\nBring casserole to room tempature.  \n\nPreheat the oven to 325°F. Bake casserole uncovered for 40 minutes, or until set. Serves ten.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(160,'Entree','Entree --- Chicken & Dressing','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- (10 inch) iron skillet of cornbread, crumbled\n                 Uses Corn Bread receipt in this book.\n1/2 -------- large loaf bread, 14 slices toasted and \n                  crumbled\n1/2 --------  bunch of celery, chopped fine\n1 ----------- large onion, chopped fine\n4 ----------- eggs, uncooked\n1 1/2 ------ Tablespoons black pepper\n1 ----------- Tablespoon salt, the reason for less salt \n                   than pepper, the corn bread is  salted, I use\n                   Rich broth from a roasted turkey or chicken.\n                   Do not use a broth that has been spiced up \n                   with a lot of extra spices. This will ruin the \n                   taste of your dressing. \n1 ------------ Tablespoon sage\n\nCover onion and celery with rich chicken stock, cook until tender. Mix corn bread, toasted bread, eggs, onion, celery and the stock onion and celery was cooked in, pepper, salt, sage and enough broth to make the mixture a little thinner then corn bread. Be sure broth is rich, this makes a better dresseng. If the broth is not rich enough add butter. We do not add chicken to our dressing, but you can if you like it. Bake uncovered in a 350°F oven for about 1 hour, or until it begings to brown around the edges. This serves about 20 people. You can make ahead and freeze. When ready to cook let thaw and cook by directions.Serve with giblett gravy, and cranberry sauce ( jelled type).\nGravy receipt in this book.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(161,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Speckled Butter Beans & Cornbread','Faye\'s','6 ---------- Cups chicken broth\n2 ---------- (16-oz.) bags frozen butter beans\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon pepper\n1 ---------- large sweet onion, diced\n1 ---------- poblano chile, diced\n1 ---------- Tablespoon olive oil\n                 cornbread crust batter listed below\n\nBring first 4 ingredients to a boil in a large saucepan over medium- high heat. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmmer 25 minutes or until beans are tender. Remove from heat.\nSaute onion and chile in hot oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat 2 minutes; remove from heat, and stir into beans. Spoon bean mixture into a lightly greased 9 by 13 inch baaking dish. Spoon cornbread crust battter over mixture, spreading to edge of dish. Bake 350 degree oven for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.\nServes 6 to 8.\n\nCornbread Crust Batter:\nmakes 3 cups\n\n2 ---------- Cups cornmeal mix\n1 ---------- Cup buttermilk\n1/2 -------  Cup sour cream\n2 ---------- large eggs, lightly beaten\n\nStir together all ingredients.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(162,'Dip','Dip --- Onion Soup',NULL,'1 ---------- package Lipton onion soup mix\n1 ---------- pint sour cream\n\nBlend contents of onion soup mix sour cream. Chill. Serve with potato chips or vegetables.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(163,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Miniature Quiche',NULL,'1 --------- minature muffin pan .(I use a 24 muffin size)\n4 --------- slices of fully cooked ham. Chopped in real \n               small pieces.\n1 --------- Tablespoon of Colby & Monterey \n                Jack cheese shredded.\n8 --------- eggs scrambled\n                salt & pepper to taste\n\nSpray muffin pan with cooking spray or butter. Put about 1 Teaspoon of chopped ham in muffin pan . Then your cheese, and then scrambled eggs. Cook in a 350°F oven for about 15 minutes or until done. \nServe hot, with biscuits.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(164,'Misscelanous','Miscellaneous --- Tomato Fertilizer','Faye Thompson','1 --------- 5 gallon bucket, mix the following\n12 ------- ounces of beer. (cheaper the better)\n4 --------- ounces of molasses\n4 --------- ounces of baby shampoo. ( inexpensive)\n3 --------- Tablespoons of miracle-grow)\n\nFill can with water and mix well. Apply one half gallon to each tomato plant including leaves. Water plants immediately. Repeat every 14 days.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(165,'Dips','Dip --- Fruit',NULL,'12 ---------- ounces caramel candy\n2/3 --------- Cup evaporated milk\n1/2 --------- Cup marshmallowa, small\n\nMix and heat until meltd. Serve as a dip for fresh fruit. Almost all dips have to be kept heated with a water base under them, are they will burn.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(166,'Dips','Dip --- Chocolate Dip for Fruit','Faye\'s','12 --------- ounces milk chocolate bars or morsels\n1/2 -------- Cup heavy cream\n3 ----------- Tablespoond Grand Marnier\n\nIf using bars or sq;uares, chop or break. Melt chocolate in cream over low heat, stirring constantly. Add Grand Marnier just before serving. It\'s easy to make dip in advance. Reheat when you\'re ready to serve. Then add the Grand Marnier. Serve hot with fresh fruit, squares of angel food cake, pound cake, lady fingers or doughnut rounds, cut for holes.\nInstead of Grand Marnier, you may perfer Brandy,Rum, Kirsch, Bourbon or your favorite liqueur. For delicious nonalcoholic dip, add almond or coconut flavoring, or instant coffee. This dip needs to be kept hot over a hot water base, so it want burn.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(167,'Sauce','Sauces --- Horseradish',NULL,'1/4 ---------- sour cream\n1/4 ---------- prepared horseradish\n                    salt and pepper\n\nCombine the sour cream and horseredish in a small bowl. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve with the skillet steaks. Make 1/2 cup.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(168,'Cookies','Cookies --- Worlds Easiest',NULL,'1 ---------- box Duncan Hines yellow cake mix, regular, \n                 not pudding\n2 ---------- Cups chopped nuts\n1 ---------- Cup white sugar\n1 ---------- Cup oil\n2 ---------- eggs\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla\n2 ---------- Cups rolled oats\n\nDump everything in a large bowl. Stir well. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake in a  350°F oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(169,'Sandwitches','Sandwiches --- Bar-B-Que Pork',NULL,'1 ---------- Boston Butt cooked until tender. I  buy them\n                 already cooked on the grill,and put them in \n                 the freezer until ready to use. \n\nTake out of freezer 2 or 3 days before using, and let thaw in ref. Leave wraped in foil and heat, 350°F oven until warm all through, about 2 or 3 hours. Take our of wrapper and chop in small pieces. Put in bowl and sprinkle dry bar-b-que seasoning on top to taste, and mix well.\nServe on a heated bun with wet bar-b-que sauce in this cookbook. Dry seasoning is in the book also. Serve with slaw in this cookbook.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(170,'Pies','Pies --- Pumpkin','Alice Collier','3 1/2 ---------- Cups fresh or canned pumpkin\n2 --------------- Cups sugar\n1 --------------- Teaspoon salt\n4 --------------- Teaspoons ground cinnamon\n2 --------------- Teaspoons ground ginger\n1 --------------- Teaspoon ground nutmeg\n4 ---------------  eggs, lightly beaten\n3 --------------- Cups milk (I use carnation milk).\n                        Butter and corn meal\n\nCombine pumpkin, sugar, salt, and spicces. Combine eggs and milk; add pumpkin mixture. Butter pie pans and sprinkle with corn meal until completely coated. Pour filling into pie pans. Bake in 450°F oven for 10 minutes; reduce to 350°F and bake for 1 hour or until filling is firm and dark ring in center disappears. This forms its own crust. Glass or pottery pie plates are preferred. You can also pour mixture in uncooked pie pastery, and bake 350°F oven for 1 hour or until firm. About half way through baking cover crust with foil to keep from browning to much. Do not cover whole pie just the crust showing.My grandchildren like  the small tart shells. You can buy them in frozen food markets, Are make your own, using a good pastery recipe. If you use these bake for about 30 minutes in 350°F oven. Do not spill filling on sides of pie crust, It will brown faster than the crust, and you will have burned spots on the crust.\n\n\nHow To Make Pumpkin Puree\n\n     Bake:  Heat the oven to 350 degrees, Cut sugar or pie pumpkins in Quarters and remove all the seeds and fibers. (Save seeds for roasting, if desired.) Place the quarters flesh-side down on a lightly oiled baking sheet. Roast about 45-50 minutes or until the flesh Is tender.\n     Puree: Scoop away tender pumpkin flesh from the skin. Puree it in a food processor or mash it by hand until smooth. Cooked pumpkin can have a lot of moisture. To remove it, line a colander with cheesecloth or coffee filters. Place the flesh in the colander and press on it to remove excess moisture.\n     Store: Place it in a plastic sealable freezer bag and squeeze out the air. Press the bag so it will store flat, label, date and freeze. You can keep the puree about 6 months. Thaw before using.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(171,'Entree','Entree --- Meat  Balls & Rice in Consomme',NULL,'1 ---------- pound ground beef\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon pepper\n1/4 ------- Cup green pepper, chopped\n2 ---------- Tablespoons celery and leaves, chopped\n1 ---------- small onion, chopped\n2/3 ------- Cup rice\n1 ---------- can condensed consomme\' (If desired, 3 \n                 bouillon cubes dissolved in 3 cups of hot \n                 water may be substituted for the canned\n                 consomme\'\n1 ---------- can water\n\nMix ground beef, salt and pepper, and shape into 12 balls. Brown slowly on alll sides in skillet, using a small amount of fat, if necesaary. Add green pepper, celery and onion, and cook 5 minutes longer. Add rice, consomme\' and water. Bring  to boil; cover, and simmer gently, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Serves 4.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(172,'Cookies','Cookies --- Cocoons',NULL,'2 ---------- sticks butter\n4 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n                 pinch of salt\n1 ---------- Tablespoon sherry\n2 1/2 ----- Cups sifted all-purpose flour\n1 ---------- Cup chopped pecans\n\nCream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add  salt and sherry. Continue to work until sherry disappears. Add flour gradually. Add nuts. Roll marble size pieces in hands and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 275 degree oven for about 45 minutes. Variations: these may be rolled into log shapes or crescent shapes. Roll in powdered sugar while hot. I use a sifter and sprinkle generously.These can be frozen ahead of time. Makes 85 cocoons.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(173,'Entree','Entree --- Fried Chicken','Faye Thompson','Dip for cChicken\n2 --------- Eggs\n1 --------- Cup butter milk\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon black pepper\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon ground cayenne pepper\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon ground garlic\n\nDry  Mix for Chicken\n1 --------- Cup flour\n1/2 ------ Cup corn starch\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon black pepper\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon ground cayenne pepper\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon garlic\n\nPeanut oil for frying\nIn a medium bowl mix eggs, butter milk, salt, black pepper, cayenne pepper and ground garlic.\nIn another medium bowl mix flour, corn starch, salt, black pepper, cyanne pepper and ground garlic.\n\nFirst wash the chicken and let it dry on paper towl. Next dip chicken in wet dip. Coat well. Put in flour mix and coat well. You are ready to fry chicken. I use electric deep fryer, but you can use a deep heavy pot. Be sure oil is deep enough to cover chicken. Do not cook to much at one time. Give chicken plenty of room to cook on all sides. Have oil heated before you put the chicken in the oil, about 325°F to 350°F. Drop chicken in oil and cook for about 10 minutes. Take out and drain on a paper towl. Do not use anything but peanut oil. This makes about 10 pieces of chicken.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(174,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Garlic Seasoned Fresh Broccoli',NULL,'3 ---------- stalks fresh broccoli (about 2 lbs.)\n3 ---------- cloves garlic , minced\n3 ---------- Tablespoons olive oil\n1 ---------- Tablespoon lemon juice\n2 ---------- Tablespoons butter\n                 salt & pepper to taste\n\nCut largest stalkes of broccli and throw them away. Cut the more tender stalkest into one inch pieces.Set aside the tops. Brown the garlic in oil in a large heavy skillet with lid. Place stalks in the oil and steam, covered, for 5 minutes. Add the broccli tops, stir and steam, covered, for another 5 minutes. ( Be sure to time precisely.) Toss with salt, pepper, butter and lemon juice. Serve hot or chilled. Serves 3 to 4.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(175,'Soup','Soup --- Taco Soup',NULL,'1 ---------- pound ground beef\n1 ---------- can Bushe\'s hot chili beans ( you can use \n                 pinto beans if you perfer) \n1/2 ------- can regular rotel\n1 ----------15 ounce can diced tomatoes\n1 ---------- can whole cournal corn\n1 ---------- can water\n1 ---------- package taco mix\n1 ---------- package hidden valley ranch dressing\n                Option -- cheese for top when serving.\n\nBrown ground beef and drain off grease. Combine beef with beans,rotel,tomatoes,corn,water,taco mix and hidden valley mix. Do not drain any of the can goods.cook on low heat for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers, cornbread or corn chips. Top with shredded cheeese if you perfer. This soup is freezable for later use.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(176,'Miscellanous','Miscellaneous --- Colored sugar',NULL,'                 Make your own colored sugar\n\nMaking your own colored sugar to decorate your cakes is easy. You\'ll need 1 cup of sugar and 1 teaspoon of food coloring. Just combine 1 cup sugar and food coloring in a metal bowl. Mix with a wire whisk until sugar turns the color you are useing. Transfer sugar to a resealable plastic bag.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(177,'Cookies','Cookies --- Cashew Crunch Cookies','Joan Mc/Knight','1 ---------- Cup butter\n1 ---------- Cup firmly packed light brown sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- egg\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 3/4 ----- Cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 -------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 -------- Teaspoon cream of tarter\n1 1/2 ----- Cups finely chopped cashews or pecans\n\nBeat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer; gradually add sugars, mixing well. Add egg and vanella; beat well. Combine flour,soda, and cream of tarter; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing after each addition. Stir in cashews or pecans. Drop dough by rounded teaspoofuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets; bake at 350°F oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield: 7 dozen.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(178,'Cake','Cake --- Red Velvet Southern Style',NULL,'Nonstick vegetable cooking spray for pans. \n\n2 --------- Tablespoons unsweetened coca powder, \n                plus more for dusting\n5 --------- Cups cake flour (not self rising)\n2 --------- Teaspoons salt\n3 --------- Cups sugar\n3 --------- Cups canola oil\n4 --------- eggs\n4 --------- Tablespoons red food coloring (one 2-ounce\n                bottle)\n2 --------- Teaspoons pure vanilla extract\n2 --------- Cups well-shaken buttermilk\n1 --------- Tablespoon baking soda\n5 --------- Teaspoons distilled white vinegar\n1 --------- recipe cream cheese frosting (recipe follows)\n\nPreheat the; oven to 350°F. Generously spray three 9 by 2 inch round cake pans with nonstick cooking spray, and line with parchment paper. Spray the lining; dust with coca, tapping out any excess. Set aside. Whisk together the flour, salt, and coca in a medium bowl; set aside.\n     Mix the sugar and oil at medium speed in a bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment until combined. Add the eggs, one at a time; mix well after each addition. Mix in the food coloring and vanilla. Add the flour mixture in three batches, alternating with the buttermilk, mixing well after each addition. Scrape down the sides of bowl as needed.\n     Stir together the baking soda and vinegar in a small nonreactive bowl. Add the baking-soda mixture to the batter, and mix at medium speed for 10 seconds. Divide the batter equally among the pans. Tap the pans on the counter to remove bubbles. Bake until a cake tester inserted in the middle of the cake comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Cool the pans on a rack for 5 minutes. Invert the cakes onto wire racks to cool completely.\n     To assemble, place one layer top-side down on a cake stand. Using an offset spatula, spread with a 1/4-inch-thick layer of frosting. Repeat with the remaining layers. To frost the top and sides of the cake, work from the center toward and over the edge, making sure to coat evenly. The cake can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 1 week. This makes one 3-layer 9-inch cake.\n\nYou can make cup cakes from this recipe, Bake 325°F\noven for 20 to 22 minutes.\n\nCream Cheese Frosting\n\n3 --------- 8-ounce packages cream cheese, sofened\n5 --------- Cups sifted confectioners sugar\n1 1/2 ---- Cups unsalted butter, softened\n1 1/2 ---- Teaspoons vanilla extract\n\nIn a standing electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, or with a handheld electric mixer in a large bowl, mix the cream cheese and butter at low speed until incorporated. Add the sugar and vanilla. Increase the speed to high, and mix until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes, scraping down the sides of the bowl with a rubber spatula as needed.\n     Store in the refrigerator before using, until it is somewhat stiff, about 15 minutes. The frosting may be stored in the refrigerator for 3 days. This makes enough frosting for a 3 layer 9 inch cake.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(179,'Cookies','Cookies --- Lace Cookies','Alice Collier','1 --------- Cup regular oats, uncooked\n3 --------- Tablespoons flour\n1/4 ------  Teaspoon baking powder\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1 --------- Cup sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup chopped english walnuts\n1/2 ------- Cup butter, melted\n1 ---------- Tablespoon vanilla flavoring\n1 ----------  egg, beaten\n\nCombine oats, flour, baking powder , salt, sugar and nuts. Add butter, vanilla and egg; mix thoroughly. Chill overnight. Drop 1/2 Teaspoonfuls dough about 3 inches apart on foil-lined baking sheet. Bake at 325°F for 11 minutes. Lift foil from sheet; cool. Be sure cookies are cool before removing from foil. Cookies will be very crisp and lace-like. Yield: 5 to 6 dozen.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(180,'Entree','Entree --- Dinner In A Pumpkin',NULL,'1 --------- medium pumpkin\n1/4 ------ Cup honey\n2 --------- Tablespoons brown sugar\n2 --------- Tablespoons butter, melted\n3/4 ------- pound lean ground beef\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon pepper\n1/3 ------- Cup chopped onion\n1/3 ------- Cup chopped red and green pepper\n3 ---------- stalks celery, chopped\n1/4 ------- Cup soy sauce\n1 ---------- Cup orange juice\n2 ---------- Tablespoons parsley flakes\n1 ---------- (4 ounce) can sliced mushrooms, drained\n1 ---------- (10 3/4-ounce) can cream of mushroom \n                  soup, diluted\n1/2 -------- Cup sliced reasted almonds, divided\n1/2 -------- Teaspoon ground ginger\n1 ----------- (6 1/2- ounce) package long grain and wild \n                  rice\n\nCut top from pumpkin; Remove strings and seeds. Combine honey, sugar and margarine; brush mixture on inside of pumpkin; set aside. Cook meat, seadoned with salt and pepper, until brown; drain excess fat; set meat aside. Combine onion, pepper, celery, soy sauce and orange juice in saucepan; simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Combine meat and vegetable mixture and remaining ingredients, reserving 1 tablespoon almonds. Spoon mixture into pumpkin cavity; replace pumpkin top. Brush outer surface of pumpkin with oil; place on baking sheet. Bake, on lowest oven rack, At 375 degrees for 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle with remaining almonds just before serving. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(181,'Pies','Pies --- Hershey Pie',NULL,'6 ---------- small Hersheys bars with almonds\n16 -------- large marshallows\n1/2 ------- Cup whole milk\n8 ---------- ounces whipping cream\n1/4 ------- Cup shredded paraffin \n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n\nChop Hershey bars, put in double boiler with milk, marshallows, salt and paraffin. Cook until completely melted. I use a hand mixer to make sure it is mixed completely. Let cool thoroughly. Whip the cream and blend all together. Pour mixture into cooled baked pie shell. Chill before serving.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(182,'Hush Puppies','Bread --- Hush Puppies','Elizabeth Martin','2 ---------- Cups self-rising meal\n1 ---------- Cup self-rising flour\n1 ---------- Tablespoon salt\n1 ---------- Tablespoon sugar\n2 ---------- eggs\n                 Butter milk\n1 ---------- onion, finely chopped\n\nMake batter thicker than corn bread. Add enough buttermilk until mixture is thick enough to form soft ball. Drop from tablespoon in deep fat ( 325°F). Cook until light brown. If you have fresh oil from frying cat fish this makes the hush puppies taste better. I like to use peanut oil for frying.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(183,'Dips','Dip --- Hot Sauce For Hot Wings',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup mayonnaise\n2 ---------- green onions, chopped with green tops\n2 ---------- Tablespoons prepared horseradish\n1/4 ------- Cup chili sauce (such as Heinz)\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon cayenne pepper\n\nMix all the ingregients together in a small bowl, and refrigerate until needed.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(184,'Entree','Entree --- Hot Chicken Wings',NULL,'Spicy Chicken Seasoning\n\n1 --------- Barbeque seasoning ( In this book)\n1 --------- Tablespoon crushed red - pepper flakes\n2 --------- Teaspoons black pepper\n2 --------- Teaspoons cayenne pepper\n2 --------- Teaspoons poultry seasoning\n1 --------- Teaspoon lemon pepper\n12 -------  whole chicken wings, cut apart at the joint\n\nSpicy Chicken Batter\n\n3 --------- eggs\n2 --------- Tablespoons hot sauce\n1 --------- Tablespoon crushed red-pepper flakes\n1 ---------  Teaspoon black pepper\n 1 --------- Teaspoon cayenne pepper+ 1 \\/2 --------- Cups all-purpose flour\n                peanut oil for deep-frying\n\nIn a small bowl, whisk together the barbeque seasoning, red-pepper flakes, black pepper, cayenne, poultry seasoning, and lemon pepper. Reserve 2 tablespoons of thes mixture in a seperate bowl.\n     Rinse the chicken wings in cold water, and then place them in a shallow baking dish and pat them dry with paper towels. Sprinkle the wings evenly with the spicy chicken seasoning, cover the dish with plastic wrap, and chill for 1 hour.\n     Whisk the eggs, hot sauce, red-pepper flakes, black pepper, and cayenne together in a medium mixing bowl. Place the flour in a shallow pie plate.\n     Heat the oil in a deep fryer or a deep Dutch oven (1 1/2 inches deep) over medium-high heat until it reaches 350°F on a deep-fat thermometer.\n     Dip the ciicken wings in the egg mixture, shaking off the excess, then in the flour. This process will be neater if you can keep one hand dry. Place half the wings in the hot oil and fry for 8 to 10 minutes, turning occasionally, until they are cooked through and golden brown. Use tongs to transfer the wings to a paper towel-lined tray. Allow the oil to return to cooking temperature before adding the next batch. For extra hot results, sprinkle the cooked wings with the reserved seasoning. Serve with Horseredish dipping sauce under Dips in this cook book.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(185,'Pastery','Pastery --- Pastery',NULL,'Two 10 Inch Pie Crusts\n\n12 ---------- Tablespoons very cold unsalted butter\n3 ------------ Cups all-purpose flour\n1 ------------ Teaspoon salt\n1 ------------ Tablespoon sugar\n1/3 --------- Cup very cold vegetable shortening. I prefer \n                   Crisco shortening, that has been stored in \n                    the refrigerator.\n1/2 --------- Cup ice water\n\nplace flour, salt, and sugar in the bowl of a food processor fitted wiath steel blade and pulse a few times to mix.\n   Add the butter and shortening. Pulse 8 to 12 times, until the butter is the size of peas. With the machine running, pour the ice water down the feed tube and pulse the machine until the dough begins to from a ball.\n     Dump out on a flowered board and roll into a ball. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Cut the dough in half. Roll each piece on a well-floured board into a circle, rolling from center to the edge, turning and flouring the dough to make sure it dosen\'t stick to the board. Fold the dough in half, place in a pie pan, and unfold to fit the pan. Repeat with the top crust.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(186,'Sauces','Sauces --- Cocktail Sauce',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup katchup\n1 ---------- Teaspoon worchestershire sauce\n1 ---------- Tablespoon red wine vinegar\n2 ---------- Tablespoons prepared horseredish\n1/2 -------  lemon  ( squeeze juice )\n                 dash of hot sauce\n\nCombine all ingredients in a bowl, serve chilled. This looks pretty in a large glass container. Put sauce in bottom and hange shrimp and lemon slices over the edge, with shrimp tails hanging on outside.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(187,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Cream Style Corn',NULL,'20 ---------- Fresh ears of peaches and cream corn\n1/2 --------- Cup butter\n8 ------------ Tablespoons sugar\n3 ------------ Tablespoons salt\n2 ------------ Cups water\n\nPick out fresh corn, one way to tell is the shuck should be fresh green, and when you peel back the shuck, take your finger nail and stick one of the kernels and it should be milkey inside. The peaches and cream is the best sweet corn you can buy. It will have different colored kernels, like white and yellow. After you have selected your corn, shuck the ears and use a brush to get all the silkes off. Trim and wash. Now you are ready to trim the kernels from the cob. Be sure not to cut to deep in the ear. After you have trimed all the kernels scrape the milk from the cob. Repeat until all the ears are scraped.\n     I use a 9 by 13 by 2 inch pan. Pour the corn in the pan, then cut butter in small chunks and spread over corn, then water, and sprinkle sugar and salt. Put in a 350°F oven for 1 hour. Take out and cool, now it is ready for the freezer. Do not fill the container full, leave avout 1 1/2 inches to expand. This corn keeps fresh all year. When ready to serve take out of freezer and heat to serve. Enjoy.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(188,'Salad','Salad --- Sweet  Spicy Slaw For Bar-B-Que',NULL,'1 ---------- small head green cabbage\n1/2 ------- small head red cabbage\n4 ---------- carrots\n1 ---------- medium yellow onion\n1/2 ------- Cup mayonnaise\n1/4 ------- Cup prepared yellow mustard\n2 ---------- Teaspoons apple-cider vinegar\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon cayenne pepper \n                 kosher salt\n\nCut the cabbage into quarters and remove the cores. Peel the carrots and onion, and slice them into pieces that will fit through the feeding tube of a food processor. Fit the food processor with the large-holed grater attachment., and push the cabbage, carrots, and onion through the feed tube to grate. In a large bowl, toss the grated cabbage, carrots, and onions to combine.\n     In a medium bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, mustard, viegar, sugar, black pepper, and cayeanne \n(whisk until the sugar is dissolved). Toss the dressing with the coleslaw, and season with salt and additional pepper to taste. Cover the slaw with plastic wrap, and chill for at least 2 hours before serving. Serves 6 to 8.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(189,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Spinach Souffle',NULL,'2 ---------- (10 ounce packages frozen chopped spinach\n1 ---------- Tablespoon finely chopped onion\n3 ---------- butter or margarine\n1 1/2 ----- Tablespoons all-purpose flour\n1 ----------- Cup milk\n1 1/2  ----- Teaspoon salt\n1 ----------- Teaspoon black pepper\n4 ----------- eggs, separated\n1 1/2 ------ Cups (6 ounces) shredded sharp chedder cheese\n\n     Cook spinach according to package directions; drain and press dry. Set aside.\n     Saute onion in butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat until tender. Blend in flour, stiring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stiring constantly. Gradually stir in salt and pepper.\n     Beat egg yolks. Add one-fourth of hot white sauce to yolks, stirring well; (This keeps the yolks from turning into scrambled eggs) return yolk mixture to white sauce. Add spinach and cheese; stir well.\n     Beat egg whites ( at room tempature) until stiff but not dry. Fold into spinach mixture. Spoon into a well-greased 2 quart casserole. Bake uncovered  at 350°F for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Yield 6 to 8 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(190,'Cookies','Cookies --- Ghirardelli Brownie',NULL,'One of the best brownies I have eaten is a co. Call Ghirardelli Double Chocolate Brownie Mix. Its better if you use a Brownie pan that has dividers.\n\n\nThis is another recipe you can make with this mix.\n\nSeven Layer Brownie Bars\n\n1/2 ---------- Cup or 1 stick of butter\n1 ------------- box Ghirardelli Double Chocolate Brownie \n                     Mix\n1 ------------- Cup shredded cocoanut\n1 ------------- Cup butterscotch chips\n1 ------------- Cup Ghirardelli semi-sweet chocolate\n                     chips\n1 -------------- Cup chopped pecans\n1 1/4 --------- Cups (14 oz can) sweetened condensed \n                      millk\n\nPreheat oven to 350°F. Coat bottom of 9 by 13 by 2 inch pan with melted butter. Sprinkle briwnie mix over butter. Top with coconut, butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and pecans. Drizzle with sweetened condensed milk. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until edges are bubbly. Cool thoroughly before cutting. Makes 24, 2 inch bars.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(191,'Sauces','Sauces --- Bacon & Chicken gravy','Faye Thompson','4 --------- strips bacon or other Meat you may be frying \n                using drippings and small pieces left in pan.\n2 --------- Tablespoons all-purpose flour\n1 --------- (10.5-ounce) can Campbell\'s chicken broth or \n                home made chicken broth. I like better\n1 --------- Cup whole milk\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon ground black pepper\n\nIn a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon, reserveing drippings in pan. Crumble bacon, and set aside.\nWisk flour into hot drioppings until smooth. Cook over medium high heat, wisking constantly, for 2 minutes or until lightly browned. I like it pretty dark brown. Gradually whisk in chicken broth and milk: cook over medium heat, wisking constantly, for 2 or 3  minutes or  until thickened and bubbly. Stir in salt and pepper. Top with crumbled bacon.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(192,'Vetetables','Vegetables --- Asparagus With Bacon Dressing',NULL,'9 ---------- strips bacon\n6 ---------- Tablespoons sliced shallots\n3 ---------- Teaspoons dijon mustard\n6 ---------- Tablespoons white wine vinegar\n1 1/2 ----- Teaspoons grated lemon zest\n1/4 -------- cup olive oil\n1 ----------- teaspoon salt\n1 ----------- teaspoon black pepper\n1 1/2 ----- pound fresh asparagus, trimmed \n\n\n     In a large, skillet, cook bacon over medium heat, about 10 minutes, or intil crisp, turning once. Remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet. Drain bacon on paper towls; cool, crumble, and set aside\n     Add shallots to bacon drippings, and cook over medium-high heat until tender. Remove from heat, and cool slightly. In a medium bowl, combine shallots and bacon drippings, mustard, vingar,lemon zest olive oil, salt and black pepper, whisking until blending.\n     In a large deep skillet, add enough water to fill to within 2 inches of rim; bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Add asparagus, and cook for 3 minutes or until crisp- tender. Drain well. Serve asparagus with warm dressing, and top with crumbled bacon',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(193,'Desserts','Desserts ---Candied  Sweet Potatoes',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup butter, melted\n1 1/2 ----- Cup firmly packed brown sugar\n1 ---------- Tablespoon salt\n1 ---------- Tablespoon vanilla\n4 ---------- pounds sweet potatoes, peeled and cut \n                     into 1/4- inch round slices\n\npreheat oven to 400°F. In a large bowl, stir together butter, brown sugar, vanilla and salt intil blended. Add potatoes, and toss gently to coat. Place potatoes in a single layer in a rimmed baking pan, uncovered- and bake for 45 minutes or until tender. Stir every 15 minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(194,'Miscellanous','Miscellaneous --- Seasoning Paula Deen',NULL,'1 --------- Cup salt\n1/4 ------ Cup garlic powder\n1/4 ------ Cup pepper\n\nThis seasoning goes with juat about anything.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(195,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Succotash',NULL,'2 ---------- Quarts lima beans cooked no seasoning\n2 ---------- Quarts  peas (black eyes or purple hull do no \n                 use crowder peas). Cooked no seasoning\n2 ---------- Quarts corn cut of cobb and scrape cobb( be\n                 sure to use peches and cream corn this is a \n                 sweet corn)\n2 ----------- Quarts fresh tomatoes cooked and cut fine.\n                  You can use Hunts diced tomatoes in a can.\n1 ----------- Quart onions cut fine\n1 ----------- Quart okra cut cross about 1/2 inch thick\n1 ----------- Quart bacon fried and cut in small pieces.\n                  I buy ends and pieces in 5 lbs. Boxes it\'s\n                  cheaper that way.\n1 ----------- or 2 pods of hot pepper. Cut in small pieces\n                  Salt and black pepper to taast\n\nFry bacon drain cut in small pieces, I use a food processer. Use about half of bacon greese to fry cut onions. Cook until tender. Use the other half of bacon greese to fry cut okra. Be careful not to cook to long just until tender. Be sure to cook everything separate.When cooking the corn cut off the cobb and scrape to get all the liquid from the cobb. Place in a 9 by 13  by 2 inch side pan. Cover with a little water until you can see on top. Sprinkle about 3 Tablespons sugar and 3 Tablespoons salt and 1 stick of butter. Place in a 350°F oven for 1 hour. It takes about 20 ears of corn to fill this size pan. Now that you have every thing cooked get a large pot and mix all ingredients season to taste. This is ready to eat, or put in the freeezer.\n\nThere is another way to serve this vegetable mix. Red bell pepers, halved lengthwise, seeds and membranes removed. Stuff with succotash and ( optional a few buttered breadcrumbs). Place peppers on prepared baking sheet: Sprinkle evenly with breadcrumbs. Bake 30 minutes. Serve immediately.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(196,'Entree','Entree --- Glazed Ham With Dr Pepper','Faye Thompson','1 --------- (8 pound) bone-in, fully cooked ham half. I like\n               the E Z Cut ham By John Morrell only sold at \n               Holidays\n1 --------- (12 ounce) can Dr Pepper soda (not diet)\n2 --------- Cups firmly packed light brown sugar\n1/4 ------ Cup orange juice\n3 --------- Tablespoons dijon mustard\n\nPreheat oven to 325°F. Line a roasting pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil. Remove skin from ham, and trim fat to 1/4 inch thickness. Make shallow cuts in fat 3/4 inch apart in a diamond pattern. Place ham, fat side up, in prepared pan.\n\nIn a saucepan, bring soda, brown sugar, orange juice, and mustard to a boil over to medium-low, and cook 1 or 2 minutes or until sugar dissolves. Let cool slightly.\n\nPour soda mixture over ham. Cover with heavy-duty aluminum foil. Bake on lowest oven rack for 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally with pan drippings. Uncover ham, and bake for 30 minutes to 1 hour longer or until a meat thermometer inserted in tickest portion registers 140 degrees. I do not like to uncover the ham. It makes it to brown for me , I leave it covered for the whole time. Place ham on a serving platter, reserving pan drippings. Let ham stand 15 minutes. Cut into thin slices to serve.\n\nPour reserved pan drippings into a saucepan, and cook over medium heat 10 minutes or until slightly reduced. Serve with ham. If you get the sauce to thick just pour a little water and thin it a little.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(197,'Tyropitakia','Appetizers --- Tyropitakia','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- box phyllo pastry\n1 ---------- pound feta cheese\n8 ---------- ounces cream cheese\n1/4 -------  cup parmesan cheese\n1 ---------- egg\n\nSpften cream cheese with egg. Add crumbled feta cheese and parmesan, mix well. Cut phyllo into 2 inches strip - working with one strip at a time. Keep reminaining strips covered with a damp cloth. Brush strip with melted butter. Place 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture at base of strip. Fold right bottom corner over it into a strip. Repeat process with remaining phyllo and cheese mixture. Place seam side down on ungreased baking sheets. Brush tops with melted butter. Bake at 350°F for 12 minutes.\n\nYou can use this recipe with the same ingredients, But use phyllo cups you buy in the frozen foods dept.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(198,'Ice Cream','Ice Cream --- Butter Pecan',NULL,'1 ---------- Tablespoon butter\n2/3 ------- Cup chopped pecans\n1 ---------- 13 ounce can evaporated milk\n1 ---------- 3 3/4- ounce package instent French vanilla \n                 pudding mix\n3/4 ------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ---------- Cup half & half cream\n2 ---------- Cups whole milk\n\n     Melt the butter in a small saucepan. Cook the pecans over low heat until they are browned, about 3 minutes. Place on paper towls to drain and cool.\n     In an 8-cup glass measuring cup with a spout, combine the remaining ingredients. Whisk until the sugar is dissolved. Pour the mixture into an ice cream maker and freeze according to manufacturer\'s instructions, adding the pecans during the final 10 minutes of freezing. Serve immediately or store in the freezer in a plastic container with a snap-on lid.Makes about 10---- 1/2 cup serving.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(199,'Ice Cream','Ice Cream --- Peach',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- pound ripe peaches, peeled and mashed \n                 with a fork or potato masher\n1 1/4 ----- Cups half-and-half cream\n1 1/4 ----- Cups whipping cream\n1 1/4 ----- Cups whole milk\n1/8 -------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ----------- Teaspoon vanilla exttract  \n   Sprinkle 1/4 Cup of the sugar over the peaches and seat aside.\n     Bring the remaining 3/4 Cup Sugar, the half-and-half, cream, milk, and salt to a boil in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Let cool until the mixture reaches room temperature, then add the vanilla extract. Pour the mixture into an ice cream maker and freeze according to manufacturer\'s instructions, adding the peaches during the final 10 minutes of freezing. Serve immediately or store in the freezer in a plastic container with a snap- on lid. Makes about 10 --- 1/2-cup serving.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(200,'Cookies','Cookies --- Deborah\'s Butter Cookies','Deborah\'s recipe','3 ---------- Cups all purpose flour\n1 ---------- Teaspoon baking powder\n1 ---------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1 1/2 ----  Cup sugar\n1 ---------- Cup butter\n2 ---------- eggs\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon lemon extract\n\n     Cream togetther sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and lemon extract. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Mix together. Refrigerate for 1  hour. Roll out  thinner then pie crust, and cut with desired cookie cutter. Bake in a 350°F oven until light brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(201,'Bread','Bread --- Herbed Cheese Crescent Rolls',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup whole milk\n1 ---------- Cup Butter\n2 ---------- packages  active dry yeast\n1/4 ------- Cup sugar\n1/4 ------- Cup warm water (105 to 115 degrees)\n3 ---------- eggs\n1 ---------- Tablespoon salt\n5 to 6 ---- Cups bread flour, divided\n1 ---------- (5.2 ounce) package pepper Boursin cheese\n\n     In a small saucepan, heat milk over medium-low heat, until bubbles just begin to form around edge of pan, about 6 minutes. Remove from heat; add butter, and set aside until butter is melted.\n     In a smalll bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/4 cup warm water; let stand for 5 minutes. \n     In a largebowl, beat eggs, salt, and milk mixture at medium-low speed with a mixer until combined. Add yeast mixture, beating until combined. Gradually add 4 cups bread flour, beating until smooth. Add enough remaining bread flour to make a soft dough. I use a Kitchen Aid mixer.\n     On a lightly floured surface, turn out dough. Knead dough for 6 to 8 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.. Place dough in a lightly greased bowl, turning to grease top. I spray Pam in the bowl and on top. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85 degrees) free from drafts, for 1 hour or until dough is doubled in size. Divide dough in half. \n     Spray Pam in baking pan.\n     On a lightly floured surface, roll one half of dough into a 15- inch circle. I like to devide in 3 parts and make smaller circles. Roll dough in circle.Spread 3 circles with 1 package of cheese divided, leaving a 1/4 inch border. Using a sharp knife or pizza cutter, cut dough into 8 triangles. Starting at long end, roll up each triangle and form into a crescent shape. Repeat procedure with remaining half of dough and Boursin. Place rolls 2 inches apart on prepared baking pans. Spray Pam on top of rolls, and cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, for 1 hour or until doubled in size. Preheat oven to 350°F. Bake for 15 to 18 minutes in middle rack of the oven until golden brown. Brush butter on top of roll and Serve warm.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(202,'Vegetable','Vegetables --- Asparagus',NULL,'12 ---------- fresh Asparagus spears\n1 ------------ Box frozen Felo dough ( you want need all\n                   the felo dough, but you can freeze left overs)\n1 ------------ 8 ounce package grated parmesan cheese\n1/4 ---------  stick buttter\n\nBreak ends off the asparagus wash and dry with a paper towel. Thaw felo dough, and saperate, useing 1 sheet of dough. Cut dough in half, and brush each piece of dough with melted butter. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Put 2 pieces of asparagus in each sheet of dough and roll up. Place in a lightly greese paking pan. Sprinkle parmesan cheese over lightly. Place in a 375°Foven 15 minutes. These are good served on Roman lettuce leaves. Sprinkle a little salt and pepper on the lettuce and a little olive oil.I like to put the Roman lettue on a hot grill or hot skillet for just a few se You can serve them on a plate or in a glass standing up.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(203,'Bread','Bread --- Sour Cream Muffins',NULL,'2 ---------- Cups self rising flour\n8 ---------- ounces sour cream\n2 ---------- sticks melted butter\n\nMix together and put in a regular 12 muffin pan ungreassed. Bake in a 350°F oven for 25 to 30 minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(204,'Miscellaneous','Miscellaneous --- Buttermilk',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup whole milk\n1 ---------- Tablespoon vinegar\n\nMix -  let set for a few minutes, and you will have buttermilk.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(205,'Miscellaneous','Miscellaneous --- Sour Cream',NULL,'3/4 ---------- plain yogurt\n1/2 ---------- Cup melted butter\n\nMix - and you have sour cream',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(206,'Cookies','Cookies ---  Red Velvet  Whoopie Pies',NULL,'1 ---------- ounce semisweet chocolate, chopped\n1/2 -------  ounce milke chocolate, chopped\n12 -------- Tablespoons butter, melted\n1/2 ------- Cup sour cream\n2 ---------- large eggs\n1 1/2 ---- Teaspoons apple cider vinegar\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ---------- Tablespoon red food coloring\n2 1/4 ----- Cups all-purpose flour\n1 ---------- Cup granulated sugar\n1/4 ------- Cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n2 ---------- Teaspoons baking powder\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon salt\n\nFor the filling\n8 ---------- ounces cream cheese at room temperature\n3 ---------- Tablespoons butter, at room temperature\n2 1/2 ---- Cups confectioners sugar, sifted\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nPreheat oven 375°F degree. Line 2 large baking sheets with parchment paper. Combine the semisweet and milk chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl and micowave at 50 percent powder until melted, about 2 minutes. Wisk until smooth.\nWisk the melted butter, sour cream, eggs, vinegar, vanilla and food coloring in a bowl until combined. In another bowl, wisk the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda and salt. \nAdd the flour mixture to the batter mixture in four equal batches, wisking each batch completely before adding the next. Stir in the melted chocolate.\nScoop heaping tablespoons of batter onto the prepared baking sheets and smooth the tops with a damp finger. Bake until the cookies spring back when lightly pressed, 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes on the baking sheets, then transfer to racks to cool completely.\nMeanwhile, make the filling: Beat the cream cheese and butter with a mixer until smooth. Beat in confectioners sugar and vanilla. Sandwitch a heaping tablespoonful of filling between 2 cookies; repeat with the remaining cookies and filling. Refrigerate 30 minutes before serving.\nDo not use red velvet cake mix, The dough is to soft.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(207,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Potato Bacon Chowder',NULL,'2 ---------- Cups peeled, cubed potatoes\n1 ---------- Cup water\n8 ---------- bacon strips chopped\n1 ---------- Cup chopped onion\n1/2 ------- Cup chopped celery\n1 ---------- (10.75 ounces) condensed cream of\n                 chicken soup, undiluted\n1 3/4 ----- Cups milk\n1 ---------- Cup sour cream\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon salt\n                 dash pepper    I like more salt & pepper\n1 ---------- can mixed vegetables\n1 ---------- Tablespoon minced fresh parsley\n\nIn a covered 3 qt. Saucepan, cook potatoes in water until tender. Meanwhile, cook bacon in a skillet until crisp; remove to paper towels to drain. In the same skillet, saute onion and celery in drippings until tender; drain. Add to undrained potatoes. Stir in soup, milk, sour cream, salt pepper and mixed vegetables. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until heated through (do not boil).Crumble bacon; set aside 1/4 cup. Add remaining bacon to soup along with parsley. Sprinkle with reserved bacon.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(208,'Sauces','Sauces --- Sasuage Gravy',NULL,'1/3 ---------- pound regular sausage\n1 ------------- Tablespoon shortening\n1/4 ---------- Cup all-purpose flour\n2 ------------- Cups milk\n                     salt & pepper to taste\n\nCrumbble and cook sausage in large skillet over medium heat until browned. Add shortening, Stir in flour until dissolved. Gradually stir in milk. Cook gravy until thick and bubbly. Season with salt and pepper. Serve hot over biscuits.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(209,'Cake','Cake --- Caramel-Pecan Cheesecake Bars',NULL,'2 ---------- Cups graham cracker crumbs\n1/2 ------- Cup butter, melted\n4 ---------- (8 ounce) packages cream cheese, softened\n3/4 ------- Cup sugar\n1/4 ------- Cup all-purpose flour\n3 ---------- large eggs\n1 ----------Tablespoon vanilla extract\n                Quick caramel-pecan frosting ( recipe below)\n\nStir together graham cracker crumbs and butter; press into the bottom of a lightly greased 9 by 13 inch baking pan.\n\nBake at 350°F for 8 minutes. Remove from oven, and cool on a wire rack.\n\nBeat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Combine sugar and flour; gradually add to cream cheese, beating until blended.\n\nAdd eggs, 1 at a time, beating until blended after each addition. Stir in vanilla. Pour mixture over prepared crust, spreading evenly to edges of pan.\n\nBake at 350°F for 40 minutes or until set. Remove from oven, and cool on a wire rack.\n\nPour warm quick caramel-pecan frosting over cheesecake, spreading evenly to edges of pan. Cover and chill 8 hours. Cut into 2 dozen bars.\n\nQuick Caramel Frosting\n2 ---------- (14 ounce cans sweetened condensed milk\n1/2 ------- Cup firmly packed light brown sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup butter\n1 ---------- teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nPlace all ingredients in a heavy 3-quart sauce pan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, over medium-low heat. Cook, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes or until mixture reaches a pudding-like thickness. Remove from heat.\n\nQuick caramel-pecan frosting: Prepare Quick caramel frosting as directed; remove from heat, and stir in 1 1/2 cups chopped toasted pecans.\n\nQuick Caramel-Cocoanut-Pecan Frosting: prepare quick caramel frosting as directed: stir in 1 1/2 cups sweetened flaked cocoanut and 1 1/2 cups chopped toasted pecans.\n\nFor perfect results every time, just follow the tips below. \nCook the caramel mixture in a heavy saucepan, and stir with a wooden spoon rather than a wisk. A balloon wisk won\'t reach the edges of the pan, and the mixture will scorch.\n\nOnce the caramel mixture is removed from the heat, it cools down quickly---so go ahead and use it while it;s still warm. If you\'d like a thinner caramel, whisk in hot water, a tablespoon at a time, until it reaches the desired consistency. \nThis topping can be used on other desserts.\nI top my muffins and cakes with a generous coating of caramel, but if you perfer less, just refrigerate any leftovers, Store in an airtight container up to 2 weeks.\nIf the caramel mixture starts to harden before you\'re ready to use it (or if it\'s been stored in the refrigerator), just warm over low heat for a few minutes or microwave at high for 15 seconds intervals until soft. \nYou can spoon quick caramel frosting over hot apple pie, or sandwitch it between chocolate wafers and roll the edges in finely chopped pecans.\nTo make cutting caramel-pecan cheesecake bars extra easy, line the baking pan with  lightly greased heavy-duty aluminum foill, allowing seversl inches to extend over sides. After baking and chilling, freeze for several hours. Lift from pan using foil; press foil sides down, and cut while partially frozen into desired sizes and shapes',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(210,'Desserts','Cobbler --- Fruit Cobblers',NULL,'1---------- quart of fruit, like blackberries, peaches or \n                cherries. You can use fresh or frozen.\n1 --------- quart water\n                sugar to taste the more tart the fruit the \n                more sugar you will need. I use about 3 cups \n                in blackberries. You want this real sweet.\n1 --------- package of pie crust. There are 2 pie crust in \n                each package.\n1 --------- stick of butter\n                extra sugar to sprinkle on top.\n\n     Put fruit in a sauce pan with the water. Bring to a boil.Add sugar cook until sugar is desolved.Remove from heat and pour 1/2 of fruit mixture in a 9 by 13 inch baking dish. Use 1 pie cruse, you will have to cut it to fit the baking dish. Put on top of fruit mixture. Add 1/2 of the butter on top and sprinkle sugar on top of the butter. Be sure to take a fork and punch a few holes in the crust for air to escape. Put in a 400°F pre heated oven. Bake until medium brown. Take out of oven. Pour the other half of fruit mixture over cobbler and the other half of the pastery, butter, and sugar. Punch more holes for air to escape. Put back into the oven. Cook like the first layer, until brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(211,'Pies','Pies --- Karo Pecan Pie','Faye Thompson','3 --------- Eggs, slightly beaten\n1 --------- Cup Karo light or dark corn syrup\n1 --------- Cup sugar\n2 --------- Tablespoons butter, melted\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla\n1 ---------- Tablespoon flour\n1 1/2 ---- Cups pecan halves, or broken pieces, I like to\n                use broken pieces inside the pie and add\n                halves on top. This make the pie look better.\n1 --------- unbaked ( 9 inch ) pie shell.\n\nMix together in a large bowl, first six ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.  When making pecan or other high-sugar filled pies sprinkle both sides of crust with flour before placing in pie plate. Bake in a 350°F oven 50 or 55 minutes. Check about half way through baking place a ring of foil over outside of pie so it will not burn the crust. Do not bake any longer than minutes called for.Cool. Serves 8. Preparation time: 10 minutes.· ',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(212,'Cookies','Cookies --- Gingerbread Men',NULL,'3 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n2 ---------- Teaspoons ground ginger\n1 --------- Teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1 --------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon ground nutmeg\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon salt\n1 1/2----  sticks butter sofened\n3 /4 ------- Cups firmly packed brown sugar\n1/2 ------ Cup molasses\n1 --------- egg\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nMix flour, ginger, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg and salt. Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Add molasses, egg and vanilla; beaat well. Gradually beat in flour mixture on low speed untail well mixed. Press dough into a thick flat disk. Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.\nRoll out dough to 1/4 inch thickness on lightly floured work surface. Cut into gingerbread men shapes with 5- inch cookie cutter. Place 1- inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.\nBake in preheated 350°F oven 8 to 10 minutes or until edges of cookies are set and just beginning to brown. Cool on baking sheets 1 or 2 minutes. Remove to wire rack; cool completely. Decorate as desired. Makes 2 dozen.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(213,'Entree','Entree --- Wasetti',NULL,'1 ---------- pound ground beef\n1/2 ------- pound pork sasuage\n2 --------- Tablespoons olive oil\n\nStir ove medium heat until red is gone.\n\n1 ---------- (10 ounce) package egg noodles, medium \n                 width, cooked as directed on package\n1 ---------- can cream of mushroom soup\n1 ---------- can tomato soup\n6 ---------- slices american cheese\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon black pepper\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt \n\nSpray cooking oil in a 9 by 13 inch casserole   Mix meat and soup. Drain noodles and mix with meat..Place in a baking dish. Lay cheese slices on top of mixture. Cover and cook in 350°F oven for 30 minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(214,'Bread','Bread --- Pancakes','Faye\'s','Dry Ingredients\n\n2 ---------- Cups self rising flour\n1 ---------- Teaspoon baking powder\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1 1/2 ---- Tablespoons sugar\n\nWet Ingredients\n\n2 ---------- egg yokes\n1 1/2 ----- Cup butter milk\n\n2 ---------- egg whites beaten to a stiff peak\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n\nvegetable oil for frying\n\nOptional--- fried bacon crumbled or fried sasuage crumbled.After you get the pancakes in the skillet put a little of either one on top of the pancake and cook as directed. \n\nMix dry ingredients with wet ingredients. Fold in beaten egg whites.The batter is a little thick. Drop spoonfull of mixture in medium hot oil.Cook until it bubbles and light brown, then turn and brown on the other side. You can make this the night before, and ref.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(215,'Pies','pies --- Mile-High Lemon Meringue Pie',NULL,'1 ---------- 9 inch pie crust. Baked and cooled ( I like \n                 the pie crust in this book with sour cream)\n\n1/4 ------- Cup cornstarch\n2/3 ------- Cup sifted cake flour\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1 1/4 ---- Cups sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup lemon juice\n2 ---------- Cups water\n5 ---------- egg yolks\n2 ---------- Tablespoons lenon zest\n4 ---------- Tablespoons butter, cut in pieces\n                 1 or 2 drops of yellow food color\n1 ---------- recipe meringue ( use the recipe in this book \n                 with marshallow cream).\n\nCombine cornstarch, cake flour, salt, sugar, lemon juice and 2 cups of water in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Bring mixture to a boil, whisking constantly, then cook until it becomes very thick and almost translucent, 2 to 3 minutes.\nRemove pan from heat. Whisk in egg yolks one at a time. Return pan to low heat and cook for 5 minutes, stirring. \nRemove pan from heat and whisk in the lemon zest and butter. Transfer to a bowl set over ice water and let mixture cool, stirring occasionlly. Pour into cooled crust; cover and chill until firm about 1 hour.\nPrepare meringue then pile on top of pie and spread evently so that it touches crust all around. Broil until brown, about 2 minutes, watching constantly to avoid burning. Serve at room temperature. Serves 8 to 10.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(216,'Cupcakes','Cupcakes --- Red Velvet Cupcakes',NULL,'2 1/2 --------- Cups flour\n1/2 ----------- Cup cocoa powder\n1 -------------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 ----------- Teaspoon salt\n1 -------------- Cup butter, softened\n2 -------------- Cups sugar\n4 -------------- eggs\n1 -------------- Cup sour cream\n1/2 ----------- Cup milk\n1 -------------- bottle (1 ounce) red food color\n2 -------------- Teaspoons pure vanilla extract\n                      Vanilla cream cheese frosting\n\nMix flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt. Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed 5 minutes or until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Mix sour cream, milk, food color, and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture on low speed just until blended. Spoon batter onto paper-lined muffin cups, filling each cup 2/3 full. Bake in preheated 350°F oven 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pans 5 minutes. Remove from pans; cool completely. Spread with frosting. Make30 cupcakes.\n\nVanilla Cream Cheese Frosting:\n Beat 1 package (8 ounce) softened cream cheese, 4 Tablespoon softened butter, 2 Tablespoons sour cream, and 2 Teaspoons pure vanilla extract in large bowl until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in 1 box (16 ounce) confectioners sugar on medium speed until smooth.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(217,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Cheddar Grits Souffle',NULL,'2 1/2 ---------- Cups extra-sharpe chedder cheese. This \n                        is (6 1/2 ounces)\n2 ---------------- Cups water\n2 ---------------- Tablespoons butter\n1/2 ------------- Teaspoon salt\n2 1/2 ---------- Cups whole milk\n1 --------------- Cup quick-cooking grits\n1/4 ------------ Teaspoon freshly grated nutmeg\n1/8 ------------ Teaspoon cayenne (ground red pepper)\n6 --------------- eggs, seperated\n\nPreheat heat oven to 375°F. Greese 3-quart souffle dish and sprinkle 2 Tablespoons shredded chedder onto side.\nIn a 4-quart saucepan, heat water, butter, salt, and 1 1/2 cups milk to boiling on medium-high. Whisk in grits. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer 5 minutes or until thick. Whisk well, then whisk in nutmeg, cayenne, remaining 1 cup milk, and remaining chedder. Whisk in 3 egg yolks; save the other 3 for another recipe. Transfer to bowl and cool to room temperature. \nIn a large bowl, with mixer on medium high speed, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Be sure  egg whites are room tempature. Add one-third whites to grits mixture; beat until blended. Fold in remaining whites. Transfer to souffle dish. \nBake 45 to 50 minutes or until puffed and golden brown on top.This will crack on top, and does not have to be cooked in water bath.\nThis makes about 8 side-dish servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(218,'Cake','Cake --- Old Fashioned Chocolate Cake',NULL,'3 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n2 ---------- Cups sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup unsweetened coco powder\n2 ---------- Teaspoons baking soda\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n2 ---------- Cups hot water\n3/4 ------- Cup vegetable oil\n2 ---------- Tablespoons distilled white vinegar\n1 ---------- Tablespoon instant coffee granules\n1 ---------- Tablespoon vanilla extract\n\nPreheat oven 350°F with rack in the center. Spray two 8 by 2 inch round cake pans with nonstick spray.\nWisk together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, and salt in a large mixing bowl.\nCombine water, oil, vinegar, instant coffee, and vanilla in a measuring cup. Add to the dry ingredients and whisk just until combined- a few lumps are ok, Divide batter between pans, then bake until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 35-40 minutes. Cool cake on a rack for 15 minutes, then invert them onto the rack. Leave cakes upside down (this flattens domed cake) to cool completely.\n\nFlossy Chocolate icing\n1 ---------- stick buttter (8 tbsp.)\n1 1/2 ---- Cups sugar\n1 1/4 ---- Cups unsweetened cocoa powder\n                pinch of salt\n1 1/4 ---  Cups heavy whipping cream\n1/4 ------  Cup sour cream\n1 --------- Teaspoon instant coffee granules\n2 --------- Teaspoons vanilla extract\n\nMelt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.\nStir in sugar, cocoa, and salt. Mixture will be thick and grainy.\nCombine heavy cream, sour cream, and instant coffee in a large measuring cup, mixing until smooth. Gradually add cream mixture to chocolate until blended and smooth. Cook until the sugar has dissolved and the mixture is smooth. And hot to touch, 6-8 minutes. Do not boil.\nOff heat, add vanilla. Cool icing at room tempature until spreadable, 2-3 hours. (icing may be chilled until completely cold, then warmed gently in microwave until spreadable. Heat at high power in 20-second intervals, stirring well after each interval.) \nThis makes about 4 cups.\nTo ensure the icing sets up, use heavy whipping cream, which contains 36% or more milk fat.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(219,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Boursin Creamed Spinach',NULL,'1/2 ---------- Cup diced onion\n1 ------------ Tablespoon butter\n2 ------------ Tablespoons all-purpose flour\n1 ------------ Cup milk\n1/2 --------- Cup heavy cream\n1 ------------ pkg, boursin garlic & fine herbs cheese \n                   (5.2 ounces)\n1------------- pkg. Frozen chopped spinach, thawed and\n                   squeezed dry of excess moisture (10\n                   ounces) Be sure spinach is chopped fine.\n2 ------------Tablespoons grated parmesan cheese\n1 ------------Teaspoon minced lemon zest\n1/4 ---------Teaspoon cayenne pepper\n1/4 -------- Teaspoon nutmeg\n1/4 -------- Teaspoon black pepper\n                  pinch of salt\n\nFor the crumb topping\n\n2/3 -------- Cup coarse fresh bread crumbs (made from \n                  2 slices firm white bread)\n1 ----------- Tablespoon butter, melted\n1 ----------- Tablespoon olive oil\n                  salt & pepper to taste\n\nPreheat oven to 425°F. Coat a shallow 2 quart baking dish with nonstick spray; set aside.\nSaute onion in 1 Tablespoon butter in a saucepan over medium heaat unntil soft, 5 minutes. \nAdd flour snd stir to coat onions. Cook about 1 minute\nGradually whisk milk and cream into onion mixture, stirring constantly to prevent lumps Simmer sauce for1 minute.\nStir in Boursin, a little at a time, until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth. Remove saucepan from heat. \nAdd spinach, parmesan, zest, cayenne pepper, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Transfer spinach mixture to prepared baking dish.\nCombine crumbs, 1 Tablespoon butter, oil, salt and pepper. Top spinach with crumbs, pressing them to adhere. ( Dish may be covered and chilled at this point to be baked later.) Place dish on a baking sheet; bake until crumbs aare golden and sauce is bubbly, about 20 minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(220,'Sauce','Sauces --- Stuffed Cranberry Sauce',NULL,'1 ---------- 8 ounce container whipped cream cheese\n2 ---------- Tablespoons mayonnaise\n1/2 ------- Cup finely chopped pecans\n2 ---------- 16 ounce cans jellied cranberry sauce, chilled\n\nMix the cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy. Add the pecans and stir until well mixed. \nRemove the lids from the cranberry sauce cans. Run a knife around the inside of the cans to loosen the sauce. Slide the cranberry sauce whole from each can. Slice the canberry sauce into 1/4-inch rounds (you will get about 7 or 8 slices per can)\n.Spread the cream cheese mixture on half the rounds and place another round on top, like a sandwich. Cut each round in half and place on a pretty white dish. Cover with plastic wrap. Keep in the refrigerator until ready  to serve. This can be make several hours in advance. Serves 14 to 16.\n\nAnother way to serve cranberry sauce. Melt a can of jelled cranberry sauce, pour in a greased fancy mold. Chill until jelled and turn on a pretty plate.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(221,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Turnips with Gruyere Cheese',NULL,'4 --------- turnips sliced thin\n6 ---------Tablespoons butter\n1 1/2 --- Teaspoon minced garlic\n1/2 ------ Cup chicken broth\n1/2 ------ Cup heavy cream\n2 -------- Cups gruyere grated cheese\n               salt & pepper to taste\n\nMelt 3 Tablespoons buttter in a ovenproof skillet. Add a single layer of turnips, overlapping them slightly. Sprinkle 1/3 of the garlic, then dot with 1 Tablespoon butter. Add 1/3 chicken broth and 1/3 cream, then 1/3 of the gruyere cheese. Repeat layers twice more. Season with salt and pepper. Bake in a 375°F oven for about 35 minutes until golden and bubbly. Serves 4 to 6 .',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(222,'Cookies','Cookies --- Toffee Bar','Faye Thompson','35 --------- saltine crackers, Nabisco Premium \n1 ----------- Cup butter\n1 ----------- Cup firmly packed brown sugar\n1 ----------- (6 ounce) bag milk chocolate \n                  morsels\n1/2 -------- Cup toffee bits, Heath Bits \'O brickle\n\nPreheat oven to 400°F. Line a 10 by 15 inch jelly-roll pan with aluminum foil; Spray foil with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange crackers in a single layer in prepared pan. \nIn a small saucepan, place butter and sugar. Bring to boil, stirring frequently, over medium high heat. Reduce heat to low, and boil for 3 minutes (do not stir). Immediately spread butter mixture over crackers.\nBake for 5 to 7 minutes. Immediately sprinkle chocolate morsels over top let stand for 2 minutes or until melted. Sprinkle with toffee bits. Let cool completely (about 1 hour). Break into pieces.This makes 35 bars.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(223,'Salad','Salad --- Apricot Salad',' Deborah Head','1 ---------- 8 ounce can pineapple, crushed\n1 ---------- small package of jello, apricot flavored\n1/2 ------- Cup sugar\n3 ---------- small containers of baby food- apricot flavor\n1 ---------- 8 ounce package of cream cheese ( room \n                 temperarure).\n1 ---------- 8 ounce container of cool whip\n\nHeat pineapple, and juice, to just before boiling. Add sugar and disssolve. When sugar is dissolved, add jello and dissolve.\nRemove from heat and add the babby food and cream cheese. Leave some of the cream cheese in \"little\" chunks, if desired; adds texrure to salad. I like to use electric mixer to finish mixing. Place in refrigerator and cool. When cool, add cool whip and serve. \nLast several days in the refrigerator.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(224,'Seafood','Sea Food --- Shrimp Hot and buttered',NULL,'1 --------- pound of shrimp peeled with tail left on.\n1/4 ------ Cup Old Bay seasoning for seafood\n1/2 ------ Cup butter\n\nPut in a 9 by 13 inch baking pan. Sprinkle seasoning and butter over shrimp. Cook until heated thuroughly, on a 400°F oven.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(225,'Cupcakes','Cupcakes --- Black Walnut Cupcakes',NULL,'3/4 ---------- Cup butter, softened\n2 ------------- Cups sugar\n1 ------------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n2 3/4 -------- Cups cake flour\n2 1/2 -------- Teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 ----------- Teaspoon salt\n1 -------------- Cup whole milk\n4 -------------- egg whites\n1/2 ----------- Teaspoon cream of tartar\n1 -------------- Cup chopped black walnuts\n                      Brown Sugar-Cream Cheese icing \n                      (recipe following).\n                      Garnish with chopped  black walnuts.\n\nPreheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 (12-cup) muffin pans with paper liners.\nIn a large bowl, beat butter and sugar at medium speed with a mixer until fluffy. Beat in vanilla.\nIn a medium bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, and salt. Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture, beating just until combined after each addition.\nIn a medium bowl, beat egg whites at high speed with a mixer until soft peaks form. Add cream of tartar to egg whites, and beat until stiff peaks form. Fold egg whites into batter until well combined. Stir in walnuts. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, filling 2/3 full. Bake for 16 to 18 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean; cool completely. Spread brown sugar- cream cheese icing evenly over each cupcake. Garnish with chopped black walmuts, if desired. Makes 2 dozen cupcakes.\n\nBrown Sugar-Cream Cheese Icing\n\n1/2 ---------- Cup firmly packed dark brown sugar\n2 ------------- Tablespoons water\n1/2 ---------- Cup plus 2 tablespoons butter, softened\n                    and divided\n1 ------------- ( 8-ounce) package cream cheese, \n                    softened\n4 ------------- cups confectioners sugar\n\nIn a small saucepan, combine brown sugar, water, and 2 taglespoons butter over medium heat. Cook for 3 or 4 minutes, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Cool completely.. \nIn a large bowl, beat cream cheese and remaining 1/2 cup butter at medium speed with a mixer until smooth. Add brown sugar mixture, beating until combined. Gradually beat in confectioners sugar until smooth.\nMakes about 3 cups.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(226,'Entree','Entree --- Hot Tamales','Faye Thompson','Tamale Dough\n\n1 ---------- pound maseca flour\n4 1/2 ---- Cups fo lukewarm broth from the cooked\n                 pork at the bottom recipe.Or chicken broth.\n1 ---------- cup softened lard\n1/2 ------- cup bacon greese\n3 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon cayenne pepper\n2 ---------- Teaspoon chili powder\n1 ---------- Teaspoon oregano\n1 ---------- teaspoon comino\n1 ---------- teaspoon paprika\n1 ---------- teaspoon black pepper\n2 ---------- garlic cloves mashed\n\nCombine Masa, cayenne pepper, chili powder, salt, cumino, oregano, paprika, black pepper and garlic in a bowl, Use an electric mixer to do the heavy work of forming the dough, and I like to let the dough rest at some point so the dry ingredients can thoroughly absorb the moist ones. As a general rule of thumb you can test for masa dough doneness by dropping a little dough into a bowl of water. If it floats, it is light and ready to use, if it sinks, mix some more. To test wheather the dough is too wet or too dry, make the following obseration; Ideally, it should not crack at the edges, also indicating the perfect ratio of dry ingredients to fat and water\' The dough is best made 30 to 60 minutes before preparing the tamales, and no less; the dough will absorb the moisture while it is resting, making it the right airy consistency--- not heavy. Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and leave at room temperature for this time (30 to 60 minutes), or for up to 2 hours. Then put the refrigerator, if nessessary, for up to 2 days; after that,  it will ferment and turn \"sour.\"The dough is best used fresh, rather than frozen. However, it can be frozen, like tamales, in an airtight container or double bag, and kept (ideally) for no more than 1 month. Prepare tamale filling with the followering recipe. \n\nTamale Meat Mixture.\n\n2  -------------- pound boneless pork loin or (country \n                       backbone). You can mix part chicken\n4 ---------------Tablespoons chili powder\n4 ---------------Tablespoons paprika                                   \n4 ---------------Garlic cloves mashed\n2 ---------------Teaspoon black pepper\n2 ---------------Teaspoons ground comino\n1 ---------------Teaspoon oregano\n1 ---------------Teaspoon cayenne pepper\n1 ---------------Teaspoon salt\n11/2 ---------- Cup stock\n1/2 ------------ cup bacon greese\n\n                      corn husks or parchment paper.\n\nCover meat with water, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until done, about two hours. I like to use a slow cooker. When tender,  grind the meat . Add chili powder, paprika, , garlic, black pepper, comino, oregano, cayenne pepper, and salt. Soak corn husks in warm water for 30 minutes and rinse well. Spread masa 2 to 4 inches  and 1/8 thick over corn husks or parchment paper, 4 by 6 inches, place a tablespoon of meat mixture in the center, fold over each end, I like to put 3 tamales together, place one tamale with ends up and another on top with ends turned down. Place on top of other two. Tie a string around each end, to hold together. I think the trick is to carefully enclose the filling inside the masa dough so that it does not leak out or cook too quickly and dry out. Place in a steamer, cover, and steam for 1 hour. If you don\'t have a steamed put a collender over a pot of hot water do not let tamales touch water. Use a led that fits the collander. You can freeze these tamales.you can take them out of the freezer and steam without thawing them out. Be sure to steam when you warm them, they are better steamed than they are in a microwave. Tamales are not good cooked anyother way. Let the tamales sit for 5 minutes or so after they have cooked to let the texture and flavors set up. The steaming process  releases saltiness from the tamales, so bear in mind when seasoning the dough.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(227,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Cheese Grits Casserole','Faye Thomposn','4 ---------- Cups Water\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- Cup Quick Grits\n6 ---------- ounces ( 1 1/2 cups   ) shredded sharp \n                 cheddar cheese\n1/2 ------- Cup butter\n1 ---------- Cup whole milk\n4 ---------- eggs, beaten\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon ground red pepper (cayenne)\n\nHeat oven to 350°F. Greese 2-quart glass baking dish. I use a enamel cast iron bowl. In large saucepan, combine water and salt. Bring to a boil. Gradually stir in grits. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. \nRemove from heat. Add 1 cup of the cheese and the butter; stir until melted. Add milk, eggs, and pepper; mix well. Pour mixture into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. \nBake at 350°F. For 1 hour or until golden brown. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 8 servings. \n\nVariations\nGarlic cheese grits casserole: Prepare casserole as directed above, except stir in 1/2 Teaspoon garlic powder with pepper. \nSausage and cheese grits casserole: Stir in 6 ounces mexican pasteurized prepared cheese product with jalapeno peppers, cubed, with cheddar cheese.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(228,'Cake','Cake --- Italian Cream Cake',NULL,'1/2 --------- Cup butter\n1/2 --------- Cup crisco\n2 ----------- Cups cake flour\n1 ----------- Cup buttermilk\n1 ----------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n5 ----------- eggs whites, stiffly beaten\n2 ----------- Cups sugar\n5 ----------- egg yolks\n1 ----------- Teaspoon soda\n1 ----------- small can coconut\n1 ----------- Cup chopped pecans\n\nCream  butter and crisco until light and fluffy; add sugar, gradually, and beat well. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir together the flour and soda and add alternately with the buttermilk, beating well.\nStir in vanilla, then the coeonut and pecans. Fold in beaten egg whites. Grease and flour 3 (9 inch) round cake pans. Bake in 350°F oven for abour 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Frost with cream cheese frosting.\n\nCream Cheese Frosting\n\n1 --------- package (8 ounce) cream cheese\n1 --------- box confectioners sugar\n1 --------- Cup chopped pecans\n1/4 ------ Cup butter\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla\n\n Mix all ingredients together until smooth. Spread between layers and over top of cake.\n\nItalian Cream Squares\n\nThis cake batter can be baked in a 11 by 15 inch pan, Or 2 smaller pans 8 by 8 inch. Bake at 350°F oven for 25 to 35 minutes. Use the same frosting. Cut into squares.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(229,'Cdake','Cake --- Milky Way Cake',NULL,'8 --------- milky way candy bars\n1 --------- Cup butter (2 sticks)\n2 --------- Cups sugar\n4 --------- eggs, separated\n2 1/2 --- Cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon baking soda\n1 1/4 --- Cups buttermilk\n1 -------- Cup chopped pecans\n\nMelt candy bars with 1 stick butter over boiling water. Cream sugar and remaining butter. Add candy mixture  to this and stir. Add egg yolks then add flour, soda, and buttermilk alternately, ending with flour. Add nuts. Fold in stiffluy beaten egg whites. Bake in greased, floured tube pan at 325°F for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool and frost. This cake will not look like other cakes when you check to see if it is done, it will be sticky when inserting pick. But it\'s o.k. I thought I had ruined this cake when I first make it. It also fills the tube pan all way to the top, But the final product is delicious.\n\nFrosting:\n\n3 --------- milky way candy bars\n1 --------- stick of butter\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla\n2 --------- Cups powdered sugar\n                milk if necessary to thin\n\nMelt milky way candy bars and margarine in double boiler. Add vanilla and powdered sugar. Mix until melted and smooth.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(230,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Pineapple Wraps',NULL,' 1 --------- Can of chunk pineapple\n                 Bacon and ham strips for each chunk\n\nWrap strips of bacon or ham around pineapple chunks and secure with toothpick. Boil until meat is crisp. Serve hot.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(231,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Sausage Balls',NULL,'1 --------- pound sausage, hot or mild\n1/2 ------ Cup grated sharp cheddar cheese grated\n3 --------- Cups bisquick\n\nHave sausage and cheese at room temperature. Thoroughly combine sausage, cheese, and bisquick, form into small balls. Bake in a 400 degree oven for 15 minutes. These freeze well baked  or unbaked.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(232,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Sweet And Sour Meatballs',NULL,'2 ---------- pounds ground chuck ( be sure to use very \n                 lean meat)\n1 ---------- onion, chopped\n3 ---------- eggs\n2 ---------- slices bread, crumbled\n12 -------- ounces chili sauce\n10 -------- ounces orange marmalade\n1 ---------- lemon, juiced \n\nCombine meat, onion, eggs and bread to form 1 1/2 inch meatballs, Make sauce from remaining ingredients. Simmer in the sauce for 1 hour.Serve hot from a chafing dish. Serves 36.\nYou can freeze these meatballs in the sauce, until ready to use.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(233,'Bread','Bread --- Kent\'s French Toast',NULL,'1 ---------- Loaf of bread ( texas toast)\n2 ---------- eggs beaten\n1/2 ------- Cup evatoriated milk ( I use carnation)\n                 butter for frying\n\nBeat eggs well, then add milk and beat again. Dip bread in mixture and fry in hot butter. Brown on both sides. Serve hot.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(234,'Cookies','Cookies --- Macadamia Macaroons','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- (7 ounce) package sweetened flaked \n                coconut\n1 ---------- Cup dry-roasted macadamia baking pieces,\n                 Mauna Loa.\n1 ---------- (14 ounce) can sweetened condensed milk\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n30 -------- saltine crackers, finely crushed, \n3 ---------- egg wites\n1 ---------- (16 ounce) package white chocolate baking \n                 squares, Baker\'s\n\nPreheat oven to 350°F. Line a 10 by 15 inch jelly-roll pan with parchment paper. Spray additional baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray. Spread coconut and macadamia pieces in a single layer in prepared jelly-roll pan. Bake stirring frequently for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly toasted.\nIn a large bowl, beat egg whites at high speed with and electric mixer until stiff peaks form. Gently stir into coconut mixture. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto prepared baking sheets.\nBake for 12 to 14 minutes, or until edges of cookies are lightly golden. Remove to wire rack; cool completely (about 1 hour). Melt chocolate according to package directions; drizzle over cookies. Chill until chocolate is set (above 30 minutes). This makes about 30 cookies.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(235,'Candy','Candy ---','Faye Thompson','1 --------- Cup firmly packed  light brown sugar\n1/2 ------ Cup  light corn syrup\n1/2 ------ Cup (14- ounce) can sweetened condensed \n               milk\n1/2 ------ Cup butter\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon cream of tartar\n1/2 ------ Cup sweetened flaked coconut\n1/2 ------ Cup chopped macadamia nuts\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nLine an 8 inch square baking pan with wax paper, allowing paper to extend over sides of pan. Grease wax paper. Set aside.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(236,'Cookies','Cookies --- Macadamia & Coconut Caramels','Faye Martin Thompson','1 --------- Cup firmly packed light brown sugar\n1/2 ------ Cup light corn syrup\n1/2 ------  (14 ounce) can sweetened condensed milk\n1/2 ------ Cup butter\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon cream of tartar\n1/2 ------ Cup sweetened flaked coconut\n1/2 ------ Cup chopped macadamia nuts\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nLine an 8-inch square baking pan with wax paper, allowing paper to extend over sides of pan. Grease wax paper. Set aside.Be sure to have 5-inch squares of wax paper cut and ready for wrapping caramel pieces. Lift the refrigerated caramel block out of the pan using the extended ends of wax paper. Cut into bite-sizes. If the caramel  block becomes  too soft to cut, return it to the refrigerator.\nIn a 2 quart, heavy stainless-steel saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, sweetened condensed milk, butter, and cream of tartar over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves. Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches 242 degrees on a candy theromoeter (about 15 minutes) and is a light caramel  color. Remove pan from heat, and stir in  coconut, macadamia nuts and vanilla.\nPour mixture into prepared pan. Let stand at room temperature to cool completely , and refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Lift caramel from pan using wax paper as handles, and cut into bitesize pieces. Wrap each in a 5 inch square of wax paper,',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(237,'Soup','Soup --- Potato Soup',NULL,'2 ---------- large potatoes (cut in small pieces 1 1/2 inch)\n2 ---------- large carots (cut in small pieces)\n2 ---------- blade of celery ( cut in small pieces)\n1 ---------- large onion ( cut in small pieces)\n8 ---------- ounces of chicken broth ( home made is \n                 better)\n1 ---------- stick of butter\n2 ---------- Cups milk\n                 salt & pepper to taste\n\nCook vegetables in a very small amount of water, Just enough where it want stick, on medium heat for 25 minutes. When done take a potato masher and mash a little. Not as much as mash potatoes. Add chicken broth and butter. Stir until melted. Add milk and seasoning. Bring to a boil and serve.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(238,'/Bread','Bread --- Sourdough Biscuits',NULL,'1 --------- Package dry yeast\n1 --------- Cup warm water\n1/4 ------  Cup sugar\n2 --------- Teaspoon salt\n6 --------- Cups all-purpose flour\n4 --------- Teaspoons baking powder\n1/4 ------  Teaspoon baking soda\n2 --------- Cups buttermilk\n3/4 ------  Cup corn oil\n                Enough butter to butter baking pan and top of \n                biscuits.\n\nDissolve yeast in warm water. Add other ingredients as listed. Turn onto floured board. Knead just a little. Cut into biscuits. Place in warm buttered pan and let rise for 15 minutes. Bake in 400°F oven. You can refrigerator 2 or 3 weeks. Spoon out the amount you want for a meal. Do not cover tightly.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(239,'Cookies','Cookies --- Praline Grahams',NULL,'1 --------- Cup butter\n1 --------- Cup light brown sugar\n                Dash salt\n1 --------- Cup pecans (chopped)\n24 -------  Graham crackers\n\nMix butter, brown sugar and salt, boil for two minutes only. Remove from heat and stir in pecans. Place graham crackers close together on greased cookie sheet. Pour cooked mixture over crackers. Bake at 350°F for 10 minutes. Watch carefully. Yield: 2 dozen.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(240,'Miscellanous','Miscellaneous --- No burn butter',NULL,'When frying something in butter, mix a little cooking oil in with butter and you will still have the taste of butter but the butter want burn at fast.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(241,'Desserts','Desserts --- Caramel Layered Dessert','Faye Thompson','Crust:\n1 1/4 ----- Cups graham cracker crumbs\n1/4 -------- Cup sugar\n1/3 -------- Cup melted butter\n\nTopping:\n1/4 -------- Cup butter\n7 ----------- ounces flaked coconut\n1/2 -------- Cup chopped pecans\n\nFilling:\n8 ----------  ounces cream cheese, softened\n1 ----------  (14 ounce) can sweetened \n                  condensed milk\n1 ----------  (16 ounce) carton frozen topping,\n                  thawed\n1 ----------  (16 ounce) jar caramel ice cream \n                  topping\n\nBlend first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of 9 by 13 inch glass baking dish. Bake at 375°F for 8 minutes. Set aside. In skillet melt butter. Add pecans and coconut. Cook until golden, stirring frequently. Cool. Beat cream cheese and milk until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Spread 1/2 of mixture over crust. Drizzle with 1/2 of caramel sauce and sprinkle with 1/2 of topping mixture. Repeat layers. Place in airtight container and freeze.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(242,'Candy','Candy --- Microwave Divinity',NULL,'3 --------- Cups sugar\n1/2 ------ Cup white karo \n2/3 ------ Cup hot water\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon salt\n2 --------- egg whites (room tempature)\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon vanilla\n1 --------- Cup chopped pecans\n\nIn a 3 quart microwave bowl, cook sugar, karo and water for 12 1/2 minutes on high in microwave. Add salt to egg whites and beat on high until stiff. Slowly pour cooked syrup in a thin stream into egg whites beating constantly until mixture loses its sheen and thickness. Stir in vanilla and nuts if desired. Drop by teaspoons at once on waxed paper. Makes about 30 pieces of candy.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(243,'Candy','Candy --- Microwave Pralines',NULL,'1 1/2 -------- Cups packed brown sugar\n2/3 ---------- Cups half and half cream\n1/8 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n2 ------------- Tablespoons butter\n1 1/2 -------- Cups chopped pecans\n\nCombine sugar, milk and salt in a deep casserole. Mix well. Stir in butter. Microwave on high for 7 to 91/2 minutes or until mixture reaches soft ball stage, use candy thermometer, stirring once. Stir in nuts. Cool about 1 minute. Beat by hand until mixture is creamy and begins to thicken (about 3 minutes). Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Yield:2 dozen.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(244,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Fried Okra',NULL,'1 ---------- pound fresh okra ( you can use frozen, not as \n                 good)\n2 ----- ---- cups buttermilk milk\n1 1/2 ----- cups self-rising corn meal\n1/2 -------- cup self-rising flour\n1/4 -------- cup corn starch\n1 ---------- Tablespoon salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\n1 ---------- Teaspoon creole seasoning\n                 peanut oil for frying\n\nCut off the tips and stem ends of the okra. Cut into 1/2 inch slices and place in a large bowl. Pour the milk over the okra and let the mixture sit for at least 10 minuter or up to 30 minutes. In a separate large bowl, combine the cornmeal, flour, corn starch, salt, pepper, and creole seasoning. Use a slotted spoon to  lift the okra out of the  milk , allowing the excess milk to drain.Place small batches of okra in the cornmeal mixture, tossing to coat the okra well.\nHeat the oil in a deep black iron skllet. Lift the okra from the bowl in batches (allowing the excess cornmeal to fall back in the bowl ) and fry in the hot oil until browned. Do not overcrowd the skillet. Remove the okra from the oil with a slotted spoon and place  on paper towels to drain. Adjust the seasonings with salt and pepper while the okra is still hot.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(245,'Entree','Entree --- Chicken Spectacular','Jane Thompson','3 ---------- Cups chicken, cooked and cubed\n1 ---------- package uncle Ben\'s wild and white rice,\n                 cooked\n1 ---------- can cream of celery soup\n1 ---------- onion chopped\n2 ---------- Cups French style green beans, drained\n1 ---------- Cup mayonnaise\n1 ---------- can waer chestnuts, chopped\n                 salt & pepper to taste\n1 ---------- Cup cracker crumbs for topping\n\nMix all ingredients. Pour into a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole. Bakle, uncovered, at 350°F for 25 to 30 minutes.\n\nVariations:\nPaprika and cheese for toppping: also parmesan cheese for topping.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(246,'Bread','Bread --- Funnel Cake','Faye Thompson','1 1/3 --------- Cup water\n3/4 ------------ stick butter (6 tablespoons)\n3 -------------- Tablespoons sugar\n1/8 ----------- Teaspoon salt\n1 -------------- Cup all-purpose flour\n1 -------------- Cup eggs, about 4 large eggs plus 2 \n                      whites\n                      peanut oil for frying\n                      powdered sugar to sprinkle on top after \n                      cooked\n\nBoil water, butter, sugar, and salt together in a saucepan. Add flour and work it in until it is all incortorated and dough forms a ball. Transfer mixture to the bowl of a standing mixer and let cool for 3 to 4 minutes. With mixer lowest speed, add eggs, 1 at a time, making sure the first egg is completely incorporated before continuing once all eggs have been added and mixture is smooth, put dough in a piping bag fitted with a numger 12 tip.You can use a small pitcher made for funnel cakes.it takes about 2/3 cup of dough for each funnel cake. Heat about 1 1/2 inches of oil in a heavy pan. Oil should be about 350 degrees.  Pipe dough into oil, Making a free-form lattice pattern, cook until light brown, fliping once. Remove cake from oil, drain on paper towels, and top with  powdered sugar. Continue until all of the batter is used.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(247,'Entree','Entree --- Meatloaf',NULL,'2 --------- eggs\n1/2 ------ Cup milk\n4 --------- slices soft bread, cubed\n1 --------- envelope lipton onion soup\n1 --------- Tablespoon worcesrershire sauce\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon dry mustard\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon pepper\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------ Cup finely chopped celery\n2 --------- pounds ground beef\n\nBeat eggs and milk together with a rotary beater. Add cubed bread, onion soup, dry mustard, pepper, salt, celery and worcestershire sauce and mix very well. Add ground beef and mix with your hands, then shape into 1 or 2 loafs. Place the loaf or loafes into a well greased meat loaf pans. Bake at 350°F for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Uncovered. You can serve with catsup.\n\nSauce for Meat Loaf\n\n2 ---------- slices bacon\n1/4 ------- Cup chopped green pepper\n1/4 ------- Cup chopped onion\n1 ---------- (8 ounce) can tomato sauce\n\nBrown bacon in small skillet until very crisp. Remove from pan and saute peppers and onion until soft but not brown. Add 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce and crumble bacon into mixture. Heat together. Serve over meat loaf slices.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(248,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Green Bean Bundles',NULL,'4 ---------- (15 ounce) cans whole green beans\n1 1/2 ---- Teaspoons butter\n1/2 ------- Cup brown sugar\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon garlic powder\n1/2 -------  Cup milk\n12 -------- strips of bacon cut in half\n\n\nWrap 7 or 8 whole beans with 1/2 strip of bacon and stick together with a tooth pick. Place folded side down in a 11 by 14 inch pan lined with foil and sprayed with cooking oil. Continue until all green beans are wraped. Melt butter, brown sugar, garlic powder and milk in a saucepan then pour over bundles. Bake 375°F oven for 40 minutes or until bacon is browned. If bacon is not brown enough put oven on broil, and cook a few minutes, you will need to watch real close are it will burn. This will make about 24 or 30 bundles.\n\nAnother way to season green beans, wrap as above and put a (16 ounce) bottle catalina dressing over and cook as above.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(249,'Entree','Entree --- Chicken Eden Isle',NULL,'6 ---------- Boneless chicken breasts\n6 ---------- slices bacon\n1 ---------- jar dried beef\n1 ---------- small sour cream (8 ounces)\n1 ---------- (8 ounce) package cream cheese\n2 ---------- cans cream of chicken soup\n\nPlace 6 slices dried beef in bottom of greased 9 by 13 inch pan. Flatten chicken breasts between wax paper. Roll each breast and wrap with bacon strips. Place each breast on top of dried beef. Mix soup, sour cream and  cream cheese, pour over chicken. Cover with foil. Bake at 325°F about 2 hours. Remove foil and brown before taking from oven. Can make ahesd and freeze. Tasty and elegant. Serves 6.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(250,'Entree','Entree --- Chicken Curry',NULL,'5 --------- pound hen\n1 --------- onion chopped\n1 --------- garlic clove chopped\n1/2 ------  stick butter ( 4 tablespoons)\n1 --------- large Tablespoon curry powder\n1 --------- large Tablespoon flour\n1/2 ------  pint heavy cream\n1/2 ------  pint chicken broth\n\nBoil together hen, onion and garlic and let cool in stock. Bone hen and cut into long strips. Melt butter in double boiler. Add curry powder and flour. Add cream and chicken broth; be sure mixture is smooth. Cook and stir until thick. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add chicken and keep hot until ready to serve. Serve over boiled rice. Let each person garnish as desired with following:\nFlaked coconut;\npeanuts;\nchopped green onions;\nchopped green pepper;\nchopped hard-cooked eggs;\nChutney and currants.\nServes 10 to 12.\nThe sauce can be made in microwave.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(251,'Entree','Entree --- Beef Stew','Faye Thompson','2 --------- Pounds boneless beef stew meat\n1 --------- pound beef bone ( ox tail Is the best)\n16 ------- ounces water  (for cooking beef)\n4 --------- large potatoes, peeled and cut in bite-size \n               pieces\n1 --------- large onion, chopped fine\n2 --------- Cans veg- all  small cut, drained\n20 ------- ounces tomato juice\n               black pepper & salt to taste\n\nPlace boneless beef, beef bone and water in a slow cooker, cover and cook until meat falls off the bone. This takes several hours. Put potatoes and onion in a sauce pan, cover with water and cook until very tender. Remove beef from slow cooker and take the bone out of the ox tail and discard. Mix potatoes and onion with beef do not drain potatoes. Mix veg-all and season with salt & pepper. Serve with cornbread or crackers. This will keep for several days in the refrigerator, Just warm in microwave.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(252,'Entree','Entree --- Chuck Beef Roast','Faye Thompson','3 ---------- Pounds beef chuck roast\n4 ---------- Tablespoons crisco shortening\n                 salt & pepper to taste\n                 flour for coating roast\n2 ---------- Tablespoons flour\n8 ---------- ounces water\n1 ---------- package of lipton dry onion soup mix\n\nIn a heavy fry pan melt shorting. Salt and pepper roast on both sides and flour all sides well. Place in medium hot shortening and brown on all sides.  Put in slow cooker. Put the 2 tablespoons of flour in fry pan you took roast out of. This is to make a gravy. Mix until smooth and brown, pour the water over the mixture.Mix well and pour over roast in slow cooker, then pour dry onion mix in cooker. Cover and cook until very tender. This takes several hours.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(253,'Cake','Cake --- Coconut Cake My favorite','Faye Thompson','1 1/2 ---------- Cups  butter, softened\n2 --------------- Cups granulated sugar\n5 --------------- eggs, separated\n1 --------------- Teaspoon coconut extract\n1 --------------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n3 1/2 ---------- Cups all-pirpose flour\n1 --------------- Teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 ------------ Teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 ------------ Teaspoon salt\n1 1/4 --------- Cups coconut milk\n1 -------------- Cup buttermilk\n\nPreheat oven to 350°F. Spray 3 (9 inch) cake pans with nonstick baking spray with flour.\nIn a large bowl, beat butter and sugar at medium speed with a mixer until fluffy. Add egg yolks and extracts, beating until combined.\nIn a medium bow., combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\nIn a small bowl, combine coconut milk and buttermilk, Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with coconut milk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture, beating just until combined after each       addition.\nIn a medium bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Gently fold into batter. Spoon batter into prepared pans, and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans, and cool completely on wire racks.\nSpread seven minute frosting between layers and top and sides of cake. Press coconut flakes around edge of cake. You can leave out the coconut extract and the coconut milk, replace coconut milk with buttermilk, and make this any kind of cake you wish.\n\nSeven minute frosting\n\n3 ---------- egg whites at room tempature\n1 1/4 ----- Cup sugar\n1/2 -------- Cup light corn syrup\n3 ----------- Tablespoons water\n1/3 --------  Teaspoon cream of tarter\n3 -----------  Cups coconut\n\nCombine all ingredients in top of double boiler over cold water. Bring to low boil; beat mixture constantly until frosting forms peaks. About 7 minutes. Yield: frosting for 3--- 9 inch layer cake.\n\nThere is another recipe for Lime Frosting some people really like, personly it is not one of my favoriate.\n\nLuscious Lime Frosting\n\n1 --------- Cup butter, softened\n1 --------- Teaspoon lime zest\n1/4 ------  Cup fresh lime juice\n5 --------- Cups confectioners sugar\n1 --------- (8 ounce) container frozen whipped topping,\n                thawed.\n\nIn a large bowl, beat butter, lime zest, and lime juice at medium speed with a mixer until combined. Gradually add confectioners sugar, beating until smooth. Add whipped topping, beating until combined.  \n\nAnother filling for Coconut cake\n\nPineapple filling\n1 --------- Cup sugar\n3 --------- Tablespoons all-purpose flour\n2 --------- eggs, beaten\n1 --------- (8 ounce) can crushed pineapple, undrained\n2 --------- Tablespoons lenon juice\n1 --------- Tablespoon butter\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nCombine sugar and flour in a small saucepan: add remaining ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened (about 2 minutes), cool. Makes 1 1/3 cups. Punch small holes in each layer of cake and pour filling over each layer of cake. Put tooth picks in the cake to hold it together. Then cover top and sides with 7 minute iceing and sprinkle coconut on top and sides.\n\nAnother filling for Coconut cake.\n\nMake basic cake and instead of milk add 1 cup coconut milk. \nFilling for cocoanut cake\n3/4 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 ------------- Cup sour cream\n4 ------------- Tablespoons milk\n1/2 ----------  Cup flaked, sweetened coconut\n\nStir together sugar sour cream, milk and coconut in a bowl until well blended. Do same as above recipe. Punch holes and pour filling over each layer of the cake. Then cover with 7 minute iceing and coconut.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(254,'Cake','Cake --- Black Walnut-Coconut Pound Cake',NULL,'3 --------- Cups flour\n2 --------- Cups sugar\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon baking powder\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon soda\n1 --------- Cup oil\n4 --------- egg, beaten\n1 --------- Cup buttermilk\n1 --------- Cup black walnuts\n1 --------- Cup cocoanut\n2 --------- Teaspoons coconut flavoring\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla\n\nCombine dry ingredients. Combine eggs, oil and dry ingredients alternately with milk. Beat well. Stir in nuts, coconut and flavoring. Pour into a well greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325°F for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Turn over, and take out of cake pan. While cake is hot immediately pour coconut syrup over it and  let sit in pan for 4 hours.\n\nCoconut Syrup\n\n1 --------- Cup sugar\n1/2 ------ Cup water\n2 --------- Tablespoons butter\n1 --------- Teaspoon coconut flavoring\n\nMix first 3 ingredients in saucepan and let come to a boil and boil 5 minutes. Remove, and flavoring. Pour over hot cake and let set.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(255,'Salads','Salad --- Deviled Eggs',NULL,'8 --------- eggs, hard-boiled and peeled\n1 --------- Tablespoon mayonnaise (Hellmann\'s)\n2 --------- Teaspoons prepared mustard\n2 --------- Tablespoons vinegar\n                Paprika\n                Salt & pepper to taste \n\nPeel eggs and cut in half length of egg.Take out the yolk and mix with mayonnaise,mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper. If this is a little thick to spread, Put in a little more vinegar. Mix until smooth. Spoon back into egg halves. Sprinkle with a little paprika. For prettier eggs, use a pastry bag with a cake decorator tip for egg yolk mixture. Squeeze egg yolk mixture on the 1/2 eggs sprinkle paprika on top. Put paprika in a salt shaker and sprinkle over eggs. This is much easier.If you use a pastry bag , I like to put the egg mixture in a food processer and mix until all the lumps are mixed.\nIf you have any lumps at all, they will get clogged in the tube and make it hard to squeeze on the egg.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(256,'Sauces','Sauces --- Vinaigrette Made from Scraps','Faye\'s',' It can be almost impossivle to get the last remaining teaspoons of mustard from a bottle. Try this.\n\n1/3 --------- Cup extra-virgin olive oil\n1/4 --------- Cup red or white wine vinegar\n                   Salt and pepper to taste\n2 ------------ cloves minced garlic\n                    Dried herbs. Of your choice\n\nMix all ingredients and pour in mustard bottle. Close the lid and give the mustard bottle a shake. The resulting homemade vinaigrette taste terrific, and it uses the last bit of mustard that usually gets thrown away.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(257,'Misscellenous','Miscellaneous --- Coconut Nest for Easter Eggs','Faye\'s','2 1/4 ---------- Cups sweetened coconut flakes \n1 ---------------  large egg white\n\nShape 1/5 cup of the mixture into a nest and place on a lined cookie sheet. The mixture makes 5 nest. Bake at 350°F oven for about 16 minutes. Let nest cool completely and then top with your favorite Easter candy eggs.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(258,'Entree','Entree --- Turkey Necks','Faye\'s','2 --------- pound Fresh Turkey necks, they are usually \n                cut in 2 or 3 inch lengths at the market\n                Salt and pepper to taste\n4 --------- Tablespoons butter\n\nLine a baking pan with foil, and place turkey necks in foil. Salt, pepper and butter cut in small pieces on top of turkey. Seal foil, place in a 350°F oven for 1 hour. Serve with dry white beans cooked until tender.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(259,'Miscellaneous','Miscellaneous --- Eagle Brand Milk',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup dry milk\n2/3 ------- Cup sugar\n3 ---------- Tablespoons butter\n1/3 ------- Cup boiling  water\n\nMix all of the ingredients together in mixing bowl. Yields the same size as one can of store bought Eagle Brand Milk.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(260,'Misscellaneous','Miscellaneous --- Baking Powder',NULL,'1/4 --------- Cup cream of tarter\n2 ----------- Tablespoons baking soda\n1 ----------- Tablespoon cornstarch\n\nSifr all of the ingredients together, three times, into a small bowl. Transfer to a clean, tightly sealed jar. The baking powder can be stored, away from sunlight, for up to six weeks. Makes 1/2 cup.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(261,'Beverages','Beverage --- Tea Southern style',NULL,'2 --------- large lemons\n3 --------- lipton family-size teabags, tags removed\n1 1/4 --- Cups granulated sugar\n\nSqueeze the lemons into a small bowl, chill the juice, and reserve the skins. Place the teabags and reserved lemon hulls in a large pottery or glass pitcher and pour in 2 cups of cold water.Bring a kittle with 4 cups water to a rolling boil. Pour the boiling water over the teabags and cover the pitcher with a small plate. Steep for 10 minutes, then remove the teabags and lemon skins. Add the sugar and lemon juice and stir until the sugar is dissolved. Add 3 more cups of cold water. Serve over ice and garnished with a fresh lemon slice.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(262,'Sauces','Sauces --- Pepper Sauce',NULL,'20 ------------- small red and green cayenne peppers\n2 1/2 to 3 --- Cups white vinegar\n\nPack the peppers into an empty wine bottle that has been cleaned. Heat the vinegar in a small saucepan until boiling. Remove from the heat and pour the vinegar itno the bottle. Let the vinegar cool and seal the bottle with the cork. Let the mixture sit for 2 weeks before using. Add more vinegar to the same peppers as needed. The pepper sauce will last as long as you keep adding vinegar. Makes about 3 cups. \n\nPepper Sauce is a must on turnip greens and field peas. Most folks leave the bottle sitting out on their kitchen table with the salt and pepper shakers.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(263,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Fresh Field Peas',NULL,'3 ---------- ounces salt pork\n2 1/2 ---- Teaspoons salt\n4 --------- Cups water\n4 --------- Cups shelled peas\n                Freshly ground bladk pepper\n                pepper sauce\n\nPlace the salt pork, salt, and water in a large heavu saucepan over high heat. Gring to a goil, lower the heat, and simmer for 15 minutes. Add the pras and simmer for 1 hour, or until tender. Add water if needed to keep the peas barlu covered with liquid at all times. Adjust the seasonings with salt and pepper. Sprinkle each serving of peas wiath pepper sauce and serve wit;h hot cornbread.\n\nThe juice from field peas or turnip greens is often called \"pot likker,\" /spoon some pot likker over a piece of hot buttered cornbread.\n\nLima beans or another variety of pea may be substituted for the field peas.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(264,'Cake','Cake --- Almond Joy Cake',NULL,'1 --------- (19 ounce) package chocolate cake mix with \n               pudding\n1 --------- Cup sugar\n1 --------- Cup evaporated milk (carnation)\n1 --------- ( 7 ounce) package coconut\n1 --------- ( 10 1/2 ounce ) package marshmallows\n1 --------- Cup chopped pecans\n1 1/2 ---- Cups sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup evaporated milk\n1/2 ------- Cup butter\n1 ---------- (14 ounce ) package milk chocolate chips\n\nPrepare cake mix according to package instructions and bake in a greased 9 by 13 by 2 inch pan. Boil 1 cup sugar with 1 cup evaporated milk in saucepan over medium heat; stir in marshmallows, coconut and pecans. Pour over warm cake. Bring 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and butter to a boil; stir in chocolate chips to melt.Spread over cake. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00');
