VALUES
	(265,'Miscellaneous','Miscellaneous --- Christmas Smell','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- Quart pineapple juice\n1 ---------- Quart water\n1 ---------- Quart apple cider\n2 ---------- pieces fresh ginger, peeled\n3 ---------- cinnamon sticks\n1 ---------- Tablespoon whole cloves\n1 ---------- Tablespoon whole allspice\n1 ---------- Tablespoon pickling spice\n\nPlace sll ingredients in a large saucepan over high heat, bring to a boil, and boil for several minutes. Lower the heat and simmer, leaving the pan on the back of the stove simmering. /Add more liquid as necessary. Do not drink.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(266,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Peaches & Cream Sweet Corn','Faye Thompson','6 ---------- ears of peaches & cream sweet corn \n                shucked & silked\n2 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup butter\n                 salt & pepper to taste\n\nBring a large pot of water with the sugar added to a rolling boil. Add the corn and allow the water to come back to a rolling boil. Cook for another 4 minutes after the water returns to a boil. Drain the corn,roll it in melted butter and season with salt and pepper.\n\nFresh corn is best cooked immediately after it is picked. Since this is not always possible, adding sugar to the water will restore some of its natural sweetness\n.When boiling corn, add a little sugar to the water instead of salt. Do not use salt while you are cooking corn, it makes it tough.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(267,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Corn in a Microwave','Faye Thompson','2 --------- ears of peaches & cream sweet corn\n1 --------- zip lock bag\n1 --------- Tablespoon butter\n                salt to taste\n\nYou can cook this corn in the skuck, or shuck and take the silks off before baking. For each ear cook on high for 3 minutes in zip lock bag or if you are cooking it in the shuck place on a microwave plate and cook. When finished cooking, place butter and salt in bag, close until butter is melted. If cooking in shuck take the shuck and silks off ,( be careful not to burn your self.) roll in butter and salt.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(268,'Bread','Bread --- Cheddar Cheese Biscuits','Red Lobster','For the Biscuits\n\n1 3/4 ------- cups all- purpose flour\n1 1/2 ------- Tablespoons baking powder\n2 1/2 ------- Teaspoons sugar\n1/4 ----------Teaspoon salt\n3 ------------ Tablespoons vegetable shortening room \n                    temperature\n4 ------------ Tablespoons cold unsalted butter cut into \n                    1/2 - inch pieces\n6 ------------ ounces grated yellow chedder cheese \n                    (about 1 1/4 cups)\n3/4 ---------- Cup whole milk\n                    cooking spray\n\nThe Garlic Butter\n\n3 ------------ Tablespoons unsalted butter\n1 ------------ clove garlic, smashed\n1 ------------ Teaspoon chopped fresh parsley\n\nPosition a rack in the upper third of the oven and preheated to 425°F. Lightly mist a large baking sheet with cooking spray.\nMake the biscuits: Pulse the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in a food processer.\nAdd the shortining and pulse until combined. Add the butter; pulse until combined. Add the butter; pulse 4 or 5 times, or until the butter is in pea-size pieces. Add the cheese and pulse 2 or 3 times. Pour in the milk and pulse just until the mixture is moistened and forms a shaggy dough. Turn out onto a clean surface and gently knead until the dough comes together. Do not overwork the dough or the biscuits will be tough.\nDrop the dough onto the baking sheet in scant 1/4 - cup portions, 2 inches apart, and bake until golden, 15 to 20 minutes.\nMeanwhile, make the garlic butter: Melt the butter with the garlic in a small saucepan over medium heat; cook for 1 minute. Remove from the heat and stir in the parsley. Brush the biscuits with the garlic butter and serve warm.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(269,'Vegetable','Vegetables --- Onion Rings Fried',NULL,'1 --------- egg white \n1 --------- Cup dark beer\n1 --------- Cup flour\n4 --------- large onions peeled\n               peanut oil or Carola oil foe frying\n\nMix all above ingredients. Cut onions about 1/2 inch thick and seperate into rings.Dip in batter. Fry in  3 inch of oil, about 350°F.\n\nThis is another way to use this batter.Peel and slice tart apples same as onions. Dip and fry.  After frying sprinkle Cinnamon sugar while hot.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(270,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Corn Dogs','Faye Thompson','3 --------- Cups plain corn meal\n3 --------- Cups aunt jemima pancake mix\n2 --------- eggs\n                water  (enough for mixture to be thinner than \n                cornbread mix)\n                wieners\n                corn dog sticks\n\nMix corn meal, pancake mix, eggs and water. Put sticks in the end of wieners, dip in batter. Deep fry in peanut oil at 350°F until golden brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(271,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- B L T Tomatoes',NULL,'4 ---------- 4 tomatoes. Average size\n2 ---------- 2 slices bacon cooked and crumbled\n1 ---------- garlic clove chopped\n1/2 ------- cup lettuce chopped\n1/2 ------- cup stale bread chopped in cubes\n2 ---------- tablespoons mayonnaise\n                 salt and pepper to taste\n\nHollow out tomatoes, season with salt and peppper and invert to drain. Mix bacon and garlic toss with lettuce,bread cubes, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Stuff into tomatoes, then brush with bacon drippings. Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 450°F oven.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(272,'Miscellanelus','Miscellaneous --- Cheese Grateing',NULL,'To make grating cheese easier --- spray cooking oil on grater and be sure cheese is very cold.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(273,'Entree','Entree --- Chicken Enchiladas',NULL,'2 ---------- cans tomato sauce ( 8 once cans) save 1 can\n                 for top\n2 ---------- cans cream of chicken soup, condensed\n                 (10 3/4 ounce cans)\n2 ---------- Cups sour cream ( 16 ounce box)\n2 ---------- jalapino peppers, seeded and chopped\n1/2 ------- medium onion chopped\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon black pepper\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n2 ---------- Cups cubed cooked chicken\n2 ---------- Cups shredded cheese, save 1 1/2 cups \n                 for the top\n18 -------- flour tortillas 8 inches) warmed\n\nI like to use foil pan. 11 3/4 x 9 3/8 x 2 3/8 inches deep.Spray each pan with cooking spray. Each pan hold 6 tortillas. In a large bowl, combine the tomato sauce, soup, sour cream jalapenos, onion, pepper, salt, cooked chicken and cheese. Be sure to save tomato sauce and cheese for top. Spread chicken mixture down the center of each tortilla. Roll up and place seam side down in prepared dishes. Top with remaining tomato sauce; sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Cover and bake at 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or until edges are bubbly.\n\nYou can freeze  any amount you can\'t use thaw  in the refrigerator overnight. Bake, covered, at 350°F oven for 30 minutes or until edges are bubbly.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(274,'Pies','Pies --- Toffee Pie','Faye Thompson','Pie Crust\n\n1 1/2 ---------- packages of graham crackers\n1 --------------- stick butter melted\n\nPlace graham crackers and butter in food processer blend to fine crumbs. Take out and place in a 9 inch pie plate and press  to cover bottom and sides. It is easier to use a cup or glass and press all around the sides and bottom. Bake in a 350°F oven until light brown. Let cool.\n\n1 --------- can sweetened condensed milk 14 ounces.\n4 --------- bananas sliced\n2 --------- Cups whipping cream\n\nPut the can of milk in a pan of water. Cove with water bring to a boil. Boil for 3 hours and make sure water is always covering can of milk. Take the can of milk out of water and let cool. Slice bananas and place in bottom of pie crust. Save one banana for top. Open can of milk and pour over bananas. Put a few bananas on top of milk. Whip cream until stiff peaks and spread over milk and bananas.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(275,'Cupcakes','Cupcakes --- Mississipppi Mud Cupcakes',NULL,'1 ---------- cup butter, softened\n1 3/4 ----  cups sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n2 ---------- large eggs\n1 3/4 ---- Cups all-purpose flour\n1/2 ------- Cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1 --------- Teaspoon baking  soda\n1 --------- Cup buttermilk\n1/2 ------ Cup sour cream\n1 --------- Cup chopped pecans\n\nFluffy marshmallow frosting (recipe follows) Garnish: mini chocolate morsels, chopped pecans, chocolate sauce.\n\nPreheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 ( 12-cup) muffin pans with paper liners.\nIn a large bowl, beat butter, sugar, and vanilla at medium speed with a mixer until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.\nIn a medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa, and baking soda. Gradually add to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture, beating just until combined after each addition. Add sour cream, stirring until combined. Stir in pecans. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, filling two-thirds full. Bake for 15 to 18 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove cupcakes from pans, and cool completely on wire racks.\nSpread Fluffy Marshmallow Frpsting over cupcakes. Garnish with mini chocolate morsels, chopped pecans and chocolate sauce, if desired. Store cupcakes, covered in refrigerator up to 3 days. This makes 2 dozen cupcakes.\n\nFluffy Marshmallow Frosting\n\n1/2 ---------- Cup butter, softened\n1 ------------  (7-ounce) jar marshmallow creme\n1 ------------  (8-ounce) container frozen whipped\n                    topping, thawed\n\nIn a large bowl, beat butter and marshmallow creme at medium speed with a mixer until smooth. Add whipped topping, beating until combined. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(276,'Cupcakes','Cupcakes --- Champagne cupcakes- Strawberry Frost.',NULL,'1 ---------- (18.25-ounces) box white cake mix\n1 ---------- Cup champagne\n1/3 ------- Cup vegetable oil\n1/4 ------- Cup water\n4 ---------- egg whites\n                Strawberry Frasting (recipe follows ) Garnish:\n                fresh strawberry halves.\n\nPreheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 (12-cup) muffin pans with paper liners.\n\nIn a large bowl, combine cake mix, champagne, oil, 1/4 cup water, and egg whites. Beat at low speed with a mixer until combined. Increase speed to medium-high, and beat untl smooth. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, filling two-thirds full. Bake for 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans, and cool completely on wire racks. \nSpread or pipe strawberry frosting over cupcakes. Garnish with strawberry halves, if dsired. Store cupcakes, covered, in refrigerator up to 3 days.\n\nStrawberry Frosting\n\n1 ---------- cup butter, softened\n1/2 ------- cup pureed thawed frozen strawberries\n6 ---------- cups confectioners sugar\n\nIn a large bowl., beat butter and pureed strawberries at medium speed with a mixer until combined. Gradually beat in comfectioners sugar until smooth.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(277,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Posh Piggies',NULL,'1 --------- lb. Sweet italian sausage, cut into 36 half-inch \n               slices\n1 --------- sheet frozen puff pastry, thawed\n1 --------- egg. Beaten\n                sesame seeds\n1/4 ------ Cup apricot jam\n6 --------- Tablespoons dijon mustard\n2 --------- Tablespoons mayonnaise\n\nHeat oven to 375°F. Brush a sheet puff pastry with a beaten egg and cut 36 circles using a 1 1/4 -inch flited cutter.\nTop each sausage round with a pastry circle and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Skewer each stack with a toothpick and place on a baking sheet. Bake on top rack of oven, until pastry is golden, 15 to 18 minutes. \nStir together jam, mustard and mayonnaise and serve with Pash Piggies. Makes 36.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(278,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Green Vegetables',NULL,'4 ---------- Slices slab bacon, cut in 2-inch lengths\n1 ---------- medium-sized white onion, cut in 1/8 sections\n2 ---------- (16-ounce) cans whole green beans or \n                 equivalent amount of fresh beans, cooked\n1/3 -------- Cup sugar\n1/3 -------- Cup vinegar\n                  salt and prpper to taste.\n\nFry bacon in large skillet until transparent; add onion and cook until soft but not brown. Add undrained beans; bring to a boil and cook for about 10 minutes. Stir in sugar, vinegar and seasonings; simmer for about 30 minutes. Yield: 5 to 6 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(279,'Pies','Pies --- Coconut Cream Pie','Faye Thompson','1----------- 9 inch pie crust baked in 400 degree oven \n                 until light brown\n1 ---------- 4.6 ounces Jell-o vanilla (cook & serve) \n                 pudding & pie mix.Do not use instant\n2 ---------- Cups carnation evaporated milk\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon coconut extract\n1 ---------- 8.5 ounces real cream of coconut\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n4 ---------- eggs at room temperpure\n1 ---------- Cup coconut\n1/4 -------- Teaspoon cream of tarter\n3 1/2 ----- ounces Marshallow creme\n\nMix jello, milk, cocoanut extract, vanilla extract, cream of coconut and egg yokes in a double boiler, cook over boiling water until thick. Beat every few minutes with electric mixer. Mix 1/2 cup coconut, let cool for a few minutes. Pour in the prepared baked pie crust. Beat egg whites until peaked.Put a pinch of salt and cream of tarter, beat again until stiff peakes. Add marshallow cream and beat again. Spread over pie, be sure to cover all edges on the pie. Sprinkle the other half cup of coconut on top of the pie, and brown  in 400°F oven until light brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(280,'Dip','Dip --- Cheese dip',NULL,'1 ---------- lb. Velveeta cheese\n1 ---------- 10 ounce can Ro-Tel (original)\n\nCut cheese in small chunks place in a microwave bowl, and microwave for 2 minutes take out and stir. Put back in microwave cook for 1 or 2 more minutes. Take out and stir until smooth. Add Ro-Tel and stir again until smooth. You can serve cold or rewarm when ready to serve. Serve with some good corn chips.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(281,'Pies','Pies --- Cocolate Pie','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- 4.6 ounce box  Chocolate Jello-o pudding\n                 & pie filling (be sure to use cook & serve) not\n                  instane.\n1 ----------- Cup sugar\n3 ----------- Cups carnation milk\n4 ----------- egg yokes\n1 ----------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ----------- pre cooked 9 inch pie crust\n\nMix above ingredients in a double boiler. Cook until thick. Use a hand electric mixer to beat several times while cooking. Cool slightly, and pour in pie crust.\n\nMargarine\n\n4 ---------- egg whites at room tempature\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon cream tarter\n3 1/2 ----  ounces marshmallow cream\n\nBeat egg whites until stiff peaks. Add salt and cream of tarter, beat until stiff peaks, add marshmallow cream beat until well mixed. Pour on top of pie mix. Place in a 400°F oven and brown lightly.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(282,'Desserts','Desserts --- Cocolate Pudding','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- 4.6 ounce box chocolate Jello-o pudding & \n                 pie filling (be sure to use cook & serve)  \n                 not instane\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n3 ---------- Cups carnation milk\n4 ---------- eggs\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract ( use pure vanilla)\n1 ---------- 11 ounce package of Jackson vanilla wafers\n\nMix above ingredients in a double boiler. Cook until thick. Use a hand electric mixer to beat several times while cooking. Cool slightly. Place vanilla wafers in a 9 by 13 baking dish, pour pudding mix over vanilla wafers.\n\nMargarine\n\n4 --------- egg whites at room tempature\n1/8 ------ Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon cream tarter\n3 1/2 ---  ounces marshmallow cream \n\nBeat egg whites until stiff peaks. Add salt and cream of tarter, beat until stiff peaks, add marshmallow cream beat until well mixed. Pour on top of pudding mix. Place in a 400°F oven and brown lightly.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(283,'Bread','Bread --- Beer Bread','Faye Thompson','3 ---------- Cups self-rising flour\n3 ---------- Tablespoons sugar \n1 ---------- 12 ounce can beer\n4 ---------- Tablespoons butter\n\nCombine the flour, sugar and beer in a bowl. Scrape it into a well-greased loaf pan or 1-quart souffle dish. Bake at 375°F for about 50 minutes. Pour the melted butter over the top and bake 10 minutes longer. Cool on a rack. \n\nVeriation 1---------- Increase flour to 4 cups. Add 2 eggs, 2 cups sharp chedder cheese, grated, 1/4 cup vegetable oil, 1 Teaspoon each of tyme and oregano, and 12 ounces beer. Mix all ingredients and bake as above.\n\nSomeone once said of this recipe that it is so simple they were embarrassed to tell anyone. It really is that simple and it\'s equally delicious. Beer gives the loaf a robust, yeasty flavor. It\'s wonderful eaten soon after it has been taken from the oven and it makes toast like no other.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(284,'Entree','Entree --- Crown Pork Roast','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- 5 pound crown roast of pork\n1 1/2 ----  Teaspoon salt\n4 ---------- cloves of garlic\n2 ---------- Tablespoon rosemary \n1/2 ------- Teaspoon pepper\n5 ---------- Tablespoons of olive oil \n\nTo prepare the pork, in a blender, puree the oil, garlic. Rosemary, salt, and pepper until smooth. Rub the mixture over the pork roast, making sure to cover the area between the chops. Transfer the pork to a roasting pan and cover it with a foil. Refrigerate it for at least 2 hours and up to 48 hours. Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour before roasting.\nPreheat oven to 450°F. Turn the roast upside down (rib bones down) in a roasting pan for 15 minutes. Turn roast over with ribs up, uncovered then  reduce the heat to 350°F and roast for about 1 1/2 hours more, until an instant-read thermometer reads 155 degrees when inserted 2 inches into the center of the meat. When roast is done, remove it from the oven, tent with foil, let stand for 15 minutes.\nYou can use any kind of spice in place of resemary, like sage. You can also stuff the crown with different types of dressing. I like the same dressing as the chicken and dressing in this book. Cook the dressing as directed, and stuff the center of the roast and serve while hot. Slice at the table. This is a very impressive cut of meat. I cook this without the dressing. Use the drippings from the roasting pan and cook down until liquid is reduced, serve on side over sliced roast.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(285,'Vegetables','Vegetables ---  Spinach Casserole','Jane Thompson','1 ---------- 10 package of frozen spinach-thaw & \n                 drain.\n12 --------  ounces cottage cheese (small curd)\n3/4 -------  stick of butter (real butter)\n1/4 ------- Cup velvetta cheese (cut up)\n1/4 ------- Cup parmesan cheese\n3 ---------- eggs\n2 ---------- Tablespoons flour\n\nMix & stir all ingredients together. Bake at 325°F for 1 hour uncovered. Jane doubles this recipe in a 9 by 13 baking pan.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(286,'Beverage','Beverage --- Hot Cranberry Punch','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- pound fresh cranberries\n2 ---------- quarts water\n2 ---------- Tablespoon grated orange peel\n6 ---------- cinnamon sticks\n12 -------- whole cloves\n4 ---------- Cups orange juice\n1/2 ------- Cup lemon juice\n1 1/2 ----- Cups sugar\n\nCombine in a sauce pan, cranberries, water, orange peel, cinnamon sticks and cloves. Cook until cranberries are soft. Strain, add orange juice, lemon juice and sugar. Heat untill sugar is dissolved. Serve hot. I like more sugar than recipe calls for. Serves 10.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(287,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Green Beans',NULL,'5 ---------- cans whole green beans (drained) (14.5 oz.)\n1 ---------- medium size onions sliced thin\n1/2 ------- Cup brown sugar\n1/2 -------  stick butter\n5 ---------- thin sliced bacon\n\nplace green beans in a greased baking dish. Put onions on top, than sprinkle brown sugar over onions, Cut butter in small pieces and spread over onions, then lay strips of bacon on top. Bake in a 350°F oven for 45 minutes covered, then uncover and bake 15 more minites.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(288,'Salad','Salad --- Lime Salad',NULL,'2 ---------- 3 ounce package lime jello\n1 1/2-----  Cup boiling water\n                 Cool slightly and stir in\n2 ---------- Cups evaporated carnation milk\n                 chill until very thick but not set up completely \n18 --------- ounces crushed pineapple (drain)\n2 ----------- Teaspoons lenon juice\n2 ----------- Cups cream style cottage cheese small \n                  curds(Drain)\n1 ----------- Cup pecans cut small\n1 ----------- Cup celery chopped fine\n1 ----------- Cup Hellmanns mayonnaise\n\nMix last 6 ingredients and spread over jelled mixture. This needs a 9 by 13 by 2 inch dish. This is good to cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(289,'Cookies','Cookies --- A Good Cookies',NULL,'1 ---------- Cup butter\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- Cup light brown sugar\n1 ---------- egg\n1 ---------- Cup vegetable oil\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ---------- Cup regular rolled oats\n1 ---------- Cup crushed corn flakes\n1/2 ------- Cup shredded coconut\n1/2 ------- Cup chopped walnuts or pecans\n3 1/2 ----- Cups sifted all-purpose flour\n1 ---------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n\nPreheat oven to 325°F 325°F\nCream butter and sugar until light and fluffy\nAdd egg, oil and vanilla. Mix well\nAdd oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts stir well\nAdd flour, soda and salt. Stir until well blended\nDrop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets. Flattin with fork dipped in water\nBake 15 minutes. This freezes well.This makes about 8 dozen.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(290,'Salads','Salad --- Frozen Strawbery Salad',NULL,'1 ---------- medium carton cool whip\n1 ---------- 10 ounce frozen strawberries with sugar and\n                  juice\n1 ---------- 15 1/2 ounces crushed pineapple, drained\n2 ---------- sliced bananas mashed\n1/2 ------- Cup chopped pecans\n1 ---------- 4 ounce cream cheese\n3/4 ------- Cup sugar\n\nCream cheese and sugar. Add rest of ingredients. Freeze covered. Take out a few minutes before serving. Cut and serve on lettuce leaves.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(291,'Cakes','Cake --- Harvey Wallbanger Cake',NULL,'1 ---------- Box yellow cake mix\n1 ---------- (3 ounce) package vanilla instant pudding\n1 ---------- Cup vegetable oil\n4 ---------- eggs \n1/4 ------- Cup vodka\n1/4 ------- Cup Galliano (if you don\'t have Gailiano use \n                 another 1/4 cup of vodka).\n3/4 -------  Cup orange juice\n\nCombine the above ingredioents in a large mixing bowl. Beat at slow speed until all ingredients are moistened, then beat at medium speed 4 minutes. Grease bundt pan generously. Dust with flour. Pour batter into pan. Bake in preheated 350°F oven 50 minutes or until done. Cool pan on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool on rack. Frost with orange glaze. \n\nOrange frosting\n\n1 ---------- Cup sifted powdered sugar\n2 ---------- Tablespoons orange juice\n\nCombine sugar and juice. Drizzle on cooled cake.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(292,'Cake','Cake --- Maw\'s Maw\'s Nut Cake','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- Cup butter\n2 ---------- Cups sugar\n4 ---------- eggs\n3 ---------- Cups self-rising flour\n1 ---------- Tablespoon baking powder\n14 -------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- Cup milk\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ---------- Cup coconut\n1 ---------- Cup black walnuts, chopped\n1 ---------- Cup peacans, chopped\n\nCream butter: add sugar, beat medium speed. Add eggs, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to mixture alternately with milk. After all above is mixed well, add coconut and nuts to mixrure. Pour batter in 3 greased and floured 9 inch pans. Bake at 350°F fir 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and Spread with following iceing.\n\nIceing\n\n2 ---------- Cups sugar\n2 ---------- Cups butter\n2 ---------- Cups carnation milk\n2 ---------- Cups coconut\n2 ---------- Cups chopped pecans\n2 ---------- Cups black walnuts chopped\n\nCream sugar and butter. Add 2 cups milk and cook about 8 minutes stir constently. This needs to reach about 212 degrees on candy thermometer. Do not cook to much it will not spread very well. Remove from heat and add coconut and nuts. Spread before it cools.\n\nThis recipe has been in my family over 100 years.\nMy family use to have this recipe every Christmas. All the children would have to pick out the walnuts and pecans, that grew on the farm. We always had wood blocks in the wood shed, so we got a block of wood and hammer to creck the walnut shells. They were hard to crack.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(293,'Sandwiches','Sandwiches --- Toasted Reuben Sandwiches','Faye Thompson','1/4 ---------- Cup butter, softened\n8 ------------  slices marble rye bread\n1/4 ---------- Cup russian salad dressing\n1/4 ---------- Cup mayonnaise\n1 1/3 -------  pounds thinly sliced corned beef\n1 1/3 ------- Cups sauerkraut\n8 ------------- slices swiss cheese\n\nMakes 4 Sandwiches\n\nSpread 1/2 Tablespoon butter on side of each slice of bread. In a small bowl, stir together russian dressing and mayonnaise.\n\nPlace 4 bread slices, buttered sides down, on wax paper; top each with one-fourth of corned beef. Drizzle each with 2 tablespoons dressing mixture, and top each with 1/3 cup sauerkraut and 2 slices cheese. Top with remaining bread slices, buttered sides up.\n\n Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Cook sandwiches for 5 minutes per side or until bread is golden brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(294,'Cakes','Cake --- Lemon Lover\'s Cake','Gaye Thompson','Cake\n\n3 --------- Cups all-purpose flour\n2 --------- Teaspoons baking powder\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon baking soda\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n2 1/4 ---- Cups sugar\n8 ---------- large eggs, at room tempature\n1/4 ------- Cup grated lemon zest ( about 4 lemons)\n1/4 ------- Cup fresh lemon juice\n2 ---------- Cups ( 4 sticks) butter melted and cooled\n1/2 ------- Cup sour cream, at room temperature\n2 ---------- Teaspoons vanilla extract\n\nfor lemon syrup \n\n1/3 ---------- Cup fresh lemon juice\n1/3 ---------- Cup sugar\n\nLemon Glaze\n\n2 ----------- Cups confectioners sugar sifted \n5 ----------- Tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n\nCake\n\nPreheat the oven to 350°F. Spray the sides and bottom of two 9-by-5-by3-inch loaf pans with nonstick cooking spray. Line the bottom with parchment paper and spray the paper.\nSift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together in a medium bowl.\nPut the sugar, eggs, lemon zest, and lemon juice in a food processor and pulse until combined. Transfer to a large bowl.\nSprinkle in the flour mixture, one-third at a time, folding gently after each addition until just combined. Do not overmix.\nDivide the batter evenly between the prepared pans. Bake in the center of the oven for 20 minutes, rotate the pans, reduce the oven tempature to 325°F, and bake for another 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the loaf comes out clean.\nCool in the pans for 15 minutes.\n\nLemon syrup\n\n In a small saucepan over medium heat, heat the lemon juice and sugar until the sugar is completely dissolved. Once dissolved, continue to cook for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.\nLine a half sheet pan with parchment paper and invert the loaves onto the pan. Use a toothpick to poke holes in the tops and sides of the loaves. \nBrush the tops and sides of the loaves with the lemon syrup. Let the syrup soak into the cake and brush again. Let the cakes cool completely, at least 30 minutes. \n( The soaked but unglazed loaves will keep, wrapped in two layers of plastic wrap and frozen, for up to 6 weeks.)\n\nLemon Glaze\n\nIn a small bowl, whisk together the confecdtioners sugar and 5 tablespoons of the lemon juice. The mixture should be thick but pourable. If the mixture is too stiff, add up to another 2 tablespoons lemon juice and whisk again, adding small amounts of lemon juice  Or confectioners sugar until you get the right consistency. Pour the lemon glaze over the top of each loaf and let it drip down the sides. Let the lemon glaze harden, about 15 minutes, before serving.\nThe glazed loaves will keep for up to 3 days, wrapped tightly in plastic wrap, at room temperature.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(295,'Entree','Entree --- Reuben Casserole','Faye Thompson','Coat:\n1 ---------- Tablespoon butter\n\nCover\n1 1/4 ----- pounds sliced pumpernickel bread,or rye \n                 bread\n3 ---------- Cups diced corned beef (about 1 pound)\n3 ---------- Cups sauerkraut, well drained\n4 ---------- Cups shredded swiss cheese\n1 1/2 ----- Cups dressing  (3/4 Cup Russian dressing \n                 3/4 Cup mayonnaise)\n                 salt & black pepper\nBlend\n10 --------- eggs\n2 1/2 ------ Cups whole milk\n2 ----------- Tablespoons dijon mustard\n\nCoat bottom and sides of a 12 by 15 inch baking dish with butter. \nCover bottom of dish with a layer of bread slices. Top with 1 cup each corned beef, sauerkraut, and cheese. Drizzle 1/2 cup dressing over top, then season with salt and pepper. Repeat layering two more times.\nBlend eggs, milk, and dijon until combined; pour over layers in baking dish. Sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese over top. Cover with plastic wrap and press down. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 24 hours. Remove plastic and preheat oven to 350°F.\nBake uncovered, until puffy and cooked though (160 degrees), about 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.\nFor 9 by 13 inch pan you can cut this recipe in half.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(296,'Sandwitchs','Sandwiches --- Corn Dogs','Faye Thompson','1/4 ---------- Cup cornstarch\n1 ------------- (16 ounce) package all-beef hot dogs\n12 -----------  wooden skewers or lollipop sticks\n1 1/2 -------- Cups self-rising cornmeal mix\n1/2 ----------- Cup all-ourpose flour\n3 -------------- Tablespoons sugar\n1/2 ----------- Teaspoon salt\n1 3/4 --------- Cups buttermilk\n                      peanut oil for frying\n\nIn a shallow dish, place cornstarch. Thread hot dogs onto wooden skewers. Dredge hot dogs in cornstarch, gently tapping off excess.\n\nIn a large bowl, combine cornmeal mix, flour, sugar, and salt. Add buttermilk, whisking until smooth.\n\nIn a large dutch oven, pour oil to a depth of 4 inches; heat to 360 degrees. I use a deep fryer somtimes.\n\nHolding the ends of the skewers, dip hot dogs completely in cornmeal batter, letting excess drip off. Carefully place battered hot dogs into hot oil. Fry for 2 or 3 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Serve immediately. This makes 12 hot dogs.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(297,'Miscellenous','Miscelleneous --- Extracts Made At Home','Faye Thompson','Vanilla Extrace\n\n1/2 ---------- Cup vodka\n1 or 2 ------  Vanilla beans, split open or cut into small \n                     pieces\n\nIn a glass jar with a tight fitting lid, combine vodka and vanilla beans. Store in cool dark place, shaking bottle every few days, for at least 3 weeks before using. If desired, strain mixture, discarding solids. Or use extract and replenish with more vodka and vanilla beans every so often.\n\n\nLemon extract\n\n1/2 ---------- Cup vodka\n2 ------------- lemons, scrubbed\n\nUsing a sharp knife or zester, remove the zest (colored portion of the skin) being careful to avoid the bitter white pith, from each lemon.\nPlace zest in a glass jar with a tight fitting lid (a half-pint mason jar is ideal), then pour vodka over zest, making sure zest is completely submerged. Cover and refrigerate for 2 or 3 weeks. Strain, discarding lemon zest.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(298,'Vanilla Creme Brulee','Desserts --- Vanilla Creme Brulee','Faye Thompson','1/2 ---------- vanilla bean, chopped into 1/4 inch pieces.\n                    Or 1 Tablespoon of pure vanilla extract to \n                     the egg mixture\n2 ------------- Tablespoons sugar\n1 ------------- Cup heavy cream\n1 ------------- Cup half & half\n3 ------------- egg yolks\n1 ------------- egg\n1/4 ---------- Cup sugar   \n                     pinch of salt\n\nPreheat oven to 325°F.\nPulverize vanilla bean and 2 Tablespoons sugar in a coffee grinder.\nWARM cream, in a saucepan over medium heat just until steam rises.\nWISK egg yolks, egg, 1/4 cup sugar, and salt together in amixing bowl. Slowly whisk hot cream mixture into eggs to temper.\nSTRAIN egg mixture into a measuring cup with pour spout and divide among the six 4-oz, ovenproof ramekins. Arrange dishes in a baking pan, then carefully transfer pan to oven.  Add water to the pan; and bake cusard until set, 35-40 minutes; don\'t overcook.\nREMOVE ramekins from water bath, cool, then cover loosely with plastic wrap. Chill until completely cold, preferably overnight.\nCARAMELIZE each custard before serving by burning sugar on top. Let the burlees stand a few minutes after caramelizing so the topping hardens.\n\nWhen setting up the water bath, use a baking pan with sides that are no taller than 2 inches. Be sure the pan is larger enough so that the dishes don\'t touch, water should surround each one. Dash',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(299,'Salad','Salad --- Guacamole Vinaigrette Salad','Faye Thompson','FOR THE VINAIGETTE, WHISK:\n\n2 ---------- Tablespoon each fresh lime juice \n                 and red wine vinegar\n1 ---------- Tablespoon chopped fresh cilantro\n1 ---------- Teaspoon minced garlic\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon ground cumin\n3 ---------- Tablespoon olive oil\n                 salt and black pepper to taste\n\nFOR THE SALAD, ARRANGEMENT:\n\n2 ----------- beefsteak tomatoes, peeled and \n                  sliced\n1 ----------- avocado, sliced\n1/4 -------- Cup thinly sliced red onion\n\nFOR THE VINAIGRETTE, WHISK \ntogether lime juice, vinegar, cilantro, garlic, and cumin in a small bowl. Drizzle in oil while whisking,then season with salt and pepper.\nFOR THE SALAD arrange tomatoes on a large platter. Drizzle half of the vinaigrette over tomatoes; top with avocado and onion. Season salad with salt and pepper and drizzle remaining vinaigrette over salad. \n\nThis makes 4 servings and takes about 15 minutes.\nThis fresh salad version is perfect with enchiladas.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(300,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Collard Greens',NULL,'1/2 ---------- pound smoked Ham hocks or fresh turkey \n                    necks\n1/2 --------- Tablespoon black pepper\n1/2 --------- Tablespoon salt\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon red pepper flakes\n1 -----------  large bunch collard greens\n4 ----------- Tablespoons bacon greese\n\nIn a large pot, bring 3 quarts of water to a boil and add snoked meat, black pepper, salt and red pepper flakes.Reduce heat to medium and cook for 1 hour. Wash collard greens thoroughly.Remove the stems that run down the center by holding the leaf in left hand and stripping the leaf down with your right hand. The tender young leaves in the heart of the collards don\'t need to be stripped. Stack 6 to 8 leaves on top of one another, roll up, and slice into 1/2 to 1- inch thick slices, Place greens in pot with meat and add bacon greese. Cook for 1 hour or more until very tender. Stirring occasionaly. You can adjust seasoning after cooked.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(301,'Entree','Entree --- Chicken Gumbo','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- fryer, boiled\n1/4 ------- lb. Bacon, diced\n1/4 ------- Cup onion, chopped\n1/4 ------- Cup green bell pepper, Diced\n1 ---------- Cup celery, diced\n3 ---------- sprigs parsley, finely chopped\n1 ---------- Cup tomatoes, fresh or canned\n4 ---------- Cups chicken stock\n                 salt & pepper to taste\n1 ----------- Teaspoon thyme\n1 ----------- Cup cooked long grain rice\n2 ----------- Cups okra, sliced in 1/2 inch slices\n\nDebone chicken and cut into medium chunks. Saute bacon in soup pot. Add onion, green pepper, celery, and saute. Add parsley, tomatoes, stock and seasonings. Slowly simmer until vegetables are soft. Add chicken, okra and rice; cook for 10 minutes.Serves 6.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(302,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Okra & Tomato Casserole',NULL,'1 1/2 ---------- pounds tender okra\n3 --------------- frest large tomatoes\n1 --------------- onon, chopped\n1/2 ------------ Bell pepper, chopped\n                       salt & pepper, to taste\n5 --------------- strips bacon, cut in small pieces and fried\n5 --------------- strips bacon, left uncut\n\nSlice okra into 1/2 inch  rounds. Grease a 2 1/2 quart casserole. Place layers of okra, tomatoes, onion, bell pepper, cooked bacon, salt and pepper. Repeat layers. Lay bacon, overlapping, on the top. Bake at 350°F degrees for one hour. If bacon is not cooked crisp enough turn on broiler and watch close until brown. Serves 6 to 8.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(303,'Entree','Entree --- Pork Ribs With Souerkraut & Apples',NULL,'5 ---------- pounds bone-in contry-style pork ribs\n                 salt & pepper to taste\n2 1/2 ---- Teaspoons paprika\n3 --------- Tablespoons olive oil\n4 --------- Teaspoons butter (1/2 stick)\n2 ---------  granny smith apples (3/4 pound), unpeeled \n                 and cut into 1/4- inch-thick slices\n1 ---------- yellow onion, thinly sliced\n1/2 ------- Cup white wine\n32 -------- ounces sauerkraut, drained\n1 ---------- bay leaf\n\npreheat the oven to 325°F.\nRemove the white membrane from the bony side of the rack of ribs. Season the ribs generously all over with salt and black pepper. Sprinkle the paprika over the ribs. Coat the ribs evenly with the oil.\nIn a large skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the apples and onion and cook, stiring, until both are golden, about 10 minutes. Season with 1/2 Teaspoon salt and 1/2 Teaspoon  black pepper. Pour in the wine and simmer for 2 minutes, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan. Line the roasting pan with foil. Place the ribs in the pan ,cover and bake for 1 hour. After 1 hour transfer the apple-onion mixture to the roasting pan. Add the saurekraut and bay leaf; toss the mixture well to combine. Nestle the ribs on top of the sauerkraut. Cover the pan with foil. Bake until the ribs are very tender and falling off the bone, 1 1/2 hour. Remove and discard the bay leaf. Serve immediately, alongside the sauerkraut.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(304,'Candy','Candy --- Bon Bons',NULL,'2 ---------- 32 ounces confectioners sugar\n8 ---------- Tablespoons butter ( 1 stick).\n1 ---------- 14 ounce can sweetened condensed milk\n\nmix sugar butter and milk in a mixing bowl. Be sure to mix well. I use my hands, You can mix this better. Roll into small balls and refrigerate overnight. If you are in a hurry put them in the freezer for a little while. This is where you can make Bon Bon any flavor you would like. If you want coconut add 1 small can sweetened coconut, If you want nuts add 2 cups of pecans to the above. If you want orange flavor add orange extract. And any other flavor.\n\nCoating\n1 ---------- box  milk chocolate \n1/2 -------  box unsweetened chocolate\n1/2 -------  block paraffin\n\nMix and put in a double boiler. When melted, stick a toothpick in each ball and dip in chocolate mixture.\n\nAnother coating;\n\nmelt milk chocolate in double boiler or in the microwave if you are very careful. Heat 1/2 minute at a time until the chocolate is melted. Coat as above.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(305,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Cabbage Fried',NULL,'6 ---------- slices of salt meat or bacon cut in 1 inch \n                 pieces\n1/4 ------- Cup bacon drippings\n2 ---------- cloves garlic smashed\n1/4 ------- Cup water\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------ Teaspoon cayenne pepper\n16 ------- Cups shredded cabbage ( about 1 small \n                head).\n\nIn a large skillet, brown the meat, remove meat , set aside. Add enough drippings to equil 1/4 cup, add garlic, cayene pepper heat. Add meat and water heat until hot. Add cabbage hand full at a time sprinkle salt over cabbage , cook until tender. About 10 minutes. You can add more salt and cayenne pepper if you think it need it.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(306,'Bread','Bread --- Banana Nut Bread',NULL,'1 ---------- box classic yellow Duncan Hines cake mix\n3/4 ------- Cup sugar\n3/4 ------- Cup crisco oil\n4 ---------- eggs\n3 ---------- large bananas mashed\n1 ---------- Cup chopped nuts\n\nMix above ingredients. Use two loaf pans sprayed with baking spray. Bake 45 minutes  in a 350°F oven. Cool for 5 minutes. Wrap in foil and freeze.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(307,'Cake','Cake --- Best Ever Chocolate Cake',NULL,'2 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n2 ---------- Cups granulated sugar\n1/2 -------- Cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1 1/2 ----- Teaspoons baking soda\n1/4 -------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 -------- Cup vegetable shortening\n1 ----------- Cup milk\n1/2 --------- Cup cold black coffee \n1 ------------ Teaspoon vaqnilla extract\n2 ------------ large eggs\n\nFrosting\n1 ---------- Cup unsweetened cocoa powder\n1/2 ------- Cup softened butter\n1/2 ------- Cup  light corn syrup\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1/4 ------- Cup warm water\n4 ---------- Cups confectioners sugar\n1 ---------- Cup chopped walnuts, divided\n\nCake\n Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. In a large bowl, mix the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt.\n\nBeat in the shorting with an eledtric mixer on low speed. Beat in milk, coffee and vanilla until combined. Increase speed to high and beat for 2 minutes. Add the eggs; beat for 2 minutes.\n\n      Pour the batter into the prepared pans; smooth with a spatula. Bake the cakes in the middle of the oven until a toothpick inserted in the centers comes out clean, 30 -35 minutes. Cool the cakes in the; pans for 5 minutes then turn the cakes onto  wire racks to cool completely.\n\nFrosting\nCombine the cocoa powder, butter, corn syrup, vanilla and salt in a large bowl Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Add the warm water; mix well. Beat in the confectioners sugar in two batches. Beat until smooth.\n\nPlace one layer top side down on a large, flat plate. Spread with 1 cup of the frosting; sprinkle with 2/3 cup walnuts. Top with the remaining cake layer, top side up. Frost the top and sides with the remaining frosting,  swirling with a small spatula. Garnish the cake with the remaining walnuts.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(308,'Entree','Entree --- Chinese Casserole',NULL,'1 1/2 ---------- pounds ground sausage (mild)\n5 --------------- green onions, chopped\n1 --------------- Tablespoon butter\n2 --------------- packages Lipton noodle soup\n1 --------------- Cup raw rice\n1 --------------- Cup water chestnuts, chopped\n\nBrown 1 1/2  pounds mild sausage in skillet and drain. Saute 5 green onions in 1 tablespoon butter. Boil 4 1/2 cups water and 2 packages of lipton noodle soup and 1 cup raw rice . Cook until rice is almost done. Add to soup mixture. Put in chestnuts to drained sausage. Add to soup mixture. Put in casserole and cover. Cook 1 hour at 325°F.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(309,'Salad','Salad --- Spicy Cucumbers',NULL,'2 ---------- cucumbers fully peeled or peel strips to\n                 make cucumber look pretty cut across in \n                 1/4 inch slices.\n1 ---------- Cup water to cover\n1 1/2 ----- Cup vinegar\n2 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n2 ---------- Teaspoons salt\n3 ---------- cloves garlic chopped\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon red crushed pepper\n1 ---------- Teaspoon black pepper\n\nMix and let set for 2 hours serving. If you do not use all of them. Do not leave them in liquid they get to strong. You can use the liquid over several times.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(310,'Pickles','Pickles --- Pear Perserves',NULL,'12 ---------- Quarts pealed and sliced [ears\n6 ------------ # sugar\n\nBe sure you have ripe pears. Peal and slice in  medium slices, I use a Mandelin it makes slicening much faster. Put in a large stock pot. Pour sugar on top of pears. Cover with a cloth and let set over night. This will make it\'s own juice.Next morning let pears come to a boil and turn heat down to medium heat, let cook until the syrup is thickened. This take 3 or 4 hours. Stir every 30 minutes until  a candy thermometer reaches 210 degrees. Put them in any size jar you would like. Be sure to sterlize jar and lids in hot water and seal.\n\nTo make caned pearsm prepare as above and cook until pears are tender. This does not take as long as perserves. Sterlize jars and',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(311,'Entree','Entree --- Boston Butt Grilled Or Baked',NULL,'3 ---------- pound boston butt\n                 lawry\'s seasoned salt\n\nWash with clear water. Dry with paper towl. Rub Lawy\'s seasoned salt over all boston butt. Place on a smoker unraped or in a 400°F oven unraped until browned. Wrap in foil an continue to cook 1 hour per pound. If useing oven turn to 350°F. Serve with bar b que sauce or  plain.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(312,'Salad','Salad --- Sea Foam LIME Salad',NULL,'1 ---------- 3 ounce. Box lime jello\n1 ---------- 3 ounce. Box lemon jello\n2 ---------- Cups boiling water ( let cool before mixing)\n1 ---------- Cup mayonnaise\n1 ---------- 14 ounce can eagle brand milk\n1 ---------- Cup small curd cottage cheese\n1 ---------- Teaspoon lemon juice\n1 ---------- 15 ounce can crushed pineapple + juice\n1 ---------- Cup chopped nuts ( I like to use pecans)\n\nMix jello in hot water, let cool. Mix all the other ingredients in jello mix. Pour in a 9 by 13 by 2 inch pyex dish or two smaller ones. Let cool in ref. Until firm.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(313,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Tomatoes , Famous Baked',NULL,'3 ---------- Cups canned tomatoes, drained and\n                 chopped\n1 ----------- Cup granulated sugar\n1 ----------- Cup butter\n1 ----------- Teaspoon dried basil\n6 ----------- slices white bread, toasted and crumbled\n1/2 -------- Cup shreddar cheese  shredded\n\nHeat oven 350°F degrees.\nIn a saucepan heat the tomatoes, sugar and butter until the butter meltd. Add the basil and bread, simmer until most of the liquid is absorbed. Pour into a greased 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350°F for about 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and continue baking until cheese melts. Makes about 6 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(314,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Poke Salad',NULL,'1 ---------- Gal. Tender poke leaves, cut out large\n                 steams. This is a green that growes wild. \n                 The leaves are good to eat, but the berries \n                  are poision.\n6 ---------- eggs\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt or to taste\n1 ---------- Teaspoon black pepper or to taste\n2 ---------- Tablespoons butter\n\nWash greens , put them in a pot of water, about 1/2 way in the pot. The greens cook down a lot. Cook on medium high heat until tender. Pour greens in a colander and drain well, run cold water over and wash well. After washing them squeese all of the water out you can. Add eggs, salt and pepper.beat until well mixed. Heat butter over medium heat and pour green mixture in butter, cook until eggs are cooked.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(315,'Cake','Cake --- Banana Cake With Peanut Butter Frostinng',NULL,'1/2 ---------- Cup butter\n1 1/2 ------- Cups granulated sugar\n2 ------------  eggs\n1 ------------ Teaspoon vanilla extract\n3/4 ---------- Cup sour cream\n1/4 ---------- Cup buttermilk\n2 ------------ Cups all-purpose flour\n1 ------------ Teaspoon baking soda\n1 ------------ Cup chopped nuts\n1 ------------ Cup mashed ripe bananas (2 large\n                    bananas)\nFrosting\n2 ------------ Tablespoons butter\n1/4 --------- Cup hot water\n2 ------------ Cups confectioners sugar\n1/4 --------- Cup peanut butter\n1 ------------ Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nHeat oven 350°F degrees. Grease 2- 8 inch cake pans.\nCream the butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time; beat in vanilla and sour cream and buttermilk. Combine the flour and baking soda with a wisk and add to the batter. Fold in the bananas and nuts. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 30 minutes, or until done.Cool completely,\n\nFrosting\nIn a saucepan, combine the butter and hot water and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add the sugar, peanut butter and vanilla. Beat until smooth and creamy. Spread immediately on cooled cake. Cup',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(316,'Salad','Salad --- Tomato & Artichoke',NULL,'10 ----------  tomatoes peeled and sliced\n3 ------------ 6 1/2 ounces jars marinated quartered \n                   artichoke hearts and liquid  \n                   zesty italian dressing \n                   salt & pepper to tasrte\n\nMix all ingredients together and let set over night.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(317,'Salad','Salad --- Mixed Vegetable Salad','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- can water chestnuts ( chopped & drained)\n1 ---------- can shoepeg corn ( drained)\n1 ---------- can early june peas (drained)\n1 ---------- can pimientos (drained)\n1 ---------- Cup celery (chopped small)\n1 ---------- Cup onions (chopped small)\n1 ---------- Cup bell pepper (chopped small)\n\nmix\n1 ---------- Cup cold water\n2/3 ------- Cup crisco oil\n3/4 ------- Cup sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup white vinegar\n                 salt & pepper to taste\n\nmix water, oil, sugar and vinegar, heat until sugar is melted. Mix vegetables with liquid. Let set in ref. Over night. This will last in ref. Several days.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(318,'Pickles','Pickles --- Squash Pickles Or Green Tomato Pickles',NULL,'8 -------- onions \n2 -------- bell peppers\n25 ------ medium yellow squash sliced 1/4 inch or\n20 ------ medium green tomatoes cut in bite size\n              pieces.\n1/2 ----- Cup salt\n\nChop all ingredients. Mix. Place in ice and let stand for 3 hours. Drain and rinse.\n\nMix\n5 ---------- Cups sugar\n5 ---------- Cups vinegar\n2 ---------- Tablespoons mustard seed\n1 ---------- Teaspoon termeric\n\nBring to a boil, add squash or green tomatos above. \nBring to a good boil. Cool and put in sterilize jars, and seal.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(319,'Picckles','Pickles --- Refrigerator Pickles','Bonnye Sisk','4 ---------- onions sliced\n3 ---------- doz medium cucumbers\n4 ---------- Cups sugar\n4 ---------- Cups vinegar\n1/2 ------- Cup canning salt\n1 1/3 ---- Teaspoon mustard seed\n1 1/3 ---- Teaspoon celery seed\n1 1/2 ---- Teaspoon tumeric\n\nMix heat to boil. Cool in refrigerator. Slice cucumbers layer onions and cucumbers. Pour spices over cucumbers and onions let set 5 days in refrigerator before eating them.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(320,'Pickles','Pickles --- Dill Pickles','Ann Pearson','1 ---------- Quart vinegar\n2 ---------- Quarts  water\n2/3 ------- Cup salt\n\nBring to a boil, pour over cucumbers\n\n2 ---------- or 3 hot peppers\n2 ---------- garlic buds\n2 ---------- Teaspoons dill seed\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon mustard seed\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon alum\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon pickle crisp \n                 cucumbers cut or whole\n\nThis is per Quart.\n\nThis is also a good recipe for caned okra.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(321,'Salad','Salad --- Layered Salad','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- Cup shredded lettuce\n1 ---------- Cup chopped bell pepper\n1 ---------- Cup english peas, drained\n1 ---------- Cup chopped green onions\n1 ---------- Cup chopped celery\n1 ---------- Cup grated carrots\n1 ---------- ( 4 ounce ) package cheddar cheese, grated\n2 ---------- Cups mayonnaise\n2 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n1/2 ------- Cup cooked and  crumbled bacon \n3 ---------- hard boiled eggs sliced\n\nLayer vegetables in order listed in a clear glass container. Combine mayonnaise and sugar. Spread over cheese layer. Sprinkle with bacon and sliced eggs on top. Serves 10 to 12.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(322,'Salads','Salads --- Potato Salad',NULL,'10 ---------- medium size potatoes\n5 ------------ hard-boiled eggs\n1 ------------ Cup sweet pickle relish ( if you don\'t have \n                    relish chop up bread and butter pickles)\n1 ------------ large onion, chopped\n1 ------------ Teaspoon salt\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon pepper\n1 1/2 ------- Cups salad dressing\n1 ------------ Teaspoon vinegar\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon yellow mustard\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon sugar\n\nBoil potaatoes with jackets on until tender. You can also bake them in the mirowave. Let cool; peel and cube. Add eggs, pickle relish ,onions, salt and pepper. Mix lightly. In a separate bowl, combine salad dressing, vinegar, mustard, and sugar. Mix well; add to potato mixture and stir together, being careful not to mash potatoes. Refrigerate.  This is  better if made several hours ahead or overnught before serving. Serves 10 to 12.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(323,'Pickles','Pickles --- Green Tomato Pickles',NULL,'4 ---------- onions\n2 ---------- bell peppers\n1 ---------- red bell pepper\n25 -------- medium green tomatoes\n1/2 ------- Cup salt\n\nChop all ingredients.Be sure not to chop to fine. You can use small tomatoes just more of them to fit the recipe. I like to cut a tomato thats 2 inches in diameter 4 times.  Mix. Place in ice and let stand for 3 hours. Drain and rinse.\n\nMix\n5 ---------- Cups sugar\n5 ---------- Cups vinegar\n2 ---------- Tablespoons mustard seed\n1 ---------- Teaspoon termeric\n\n Add tomatoes and ingredients above. Bring to a boil. Do not boil. Take off burner.Cool and put in sterilize jars, and seal.This makes about 20 pints.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(324,'Pies','Pies --- Pecan Pie With Less Calories','Faye Thompson',' This is a Pecan pie that has less calories.\n\nUse a 9 inch pie plate\n\n3 ---------- egg whites\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon  baking powder\n1 ---------- pinch salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n12 --------  squares graham crackers (crushed).\n1 ---------- Cup pecans (chopped).\n\nBeat egg whites until begain to stiffen add sugar and beat until stiff. Set aside. Mix all other ingredients and add to egg whites and sugar. Pour in a 9 inch pie plate. Bake 350°F degree oven for 30 minutes. Cool put in ref. For 1 hour. Top with whip cream, Refrigerator again. Serve.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(325,'Bread','Bread --- Refrigerator Rolls','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- qt. Milk\n1 ---------- Cup melted butter\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n2 ---------- packages dry yeast\n1/2 ------- Cup warm water\n1 ---------- Teaspoon soda\n1 ---------- Teaspoon baking powder\n9 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n\nCombine milk, shortening, sugar and salt. Bring to boil. Let cool. Add yeast softened in warm water. Sift together soda, baking powder, and flour. Add to milk mixture and mix well. Cover and let rise at room temperature until doubled in bulk. Punch down and refrigerate 3 hours to 10 days (cover tightly). To use, roll out dough 1/4 inch thick and cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Dip in melted butter and crease roll with dull knife to make Parkerhouse rolls. Let rise 1 1/2 - 2 hours. Bake at 400°F oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 12 dozen. \nMade up rolls can be frozen before baking. Remove from freezer 2 to 3 hours before baking. Let rise in a warm place 85 to 95 degrees. \nMy stove needs to be cooked in upper rack to keep from burning on the bottom.Watch after 10 minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(326,'Candy','Candy --- Chocolate Candy','Faye Thompson','3 ---------- Cups Ghirardelli milk chocolate\n1/2 -------  Stick butter or( 4 Tablespoons).\n14 --------- Oz can sweetened condensed milk\n1 ----------- Cup chopped pecans\n\nMix chocolate, butter and milk in a microwave bowl. Microwave for 2 minutes take out and stir well. Put back in microwave and cook 2 more minutes. Take out and stir well, add pecans. Butter a 9 by 13 inch pan.Pour in and let cool. It\'s best to have everything at room temperature before you start.\n\nThere is another thing you can add, use large sea salt sprinkle on top and take a torch to burn the top slightly.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(327,'Entree','Entree --- Crown Rib Pork Roast','Faye Thompson','16 - 18 ---------- rib pork roast\n                           lawry\'s seasoned salt\n1 ------------------ Cup apple cider\n\nSpeak sweetly to your butcher and have him shape your pork ribs into a crown, allowing two ribs per person.\n\nPreheat oven to 325°F. Place crown in shallow roasting pan, insert meat thermometer into center of a meaty part of one of the chops. Roast the pork until thermometer reaches 185 degrees (about 3 hours), basting from time to time with cider and pan juiices. \n\nTo serve--- place crown roast on platter, You can fill it with wild and white rice cooked or some type of cornbread dressing. Surround roast with crab apples and parsley or pickled whole peaches or tomatoes.I serve plain. The little white paper tips on each rib you can buy them or make them yourself. Take typing paper fold  to about 3 inches wide cut small slits on folded side and make long enough to wrap around rib and tape with scotch tape.\n\nSauce to serve with crown roast\nPlum Sauce\n1 ---------- (18ounce) jar plum jelly\n1 ---------- bunch green onions, chopped\n3 ---------- Teaspoons prepared mustard\n1 ---------- Tablespoon raisins\nMix all ingredients and heat. This is delicious with duck or pork reast.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(328,'Salad','Salad --- Carrot Marshmallow Salad','Faye Thompson','3 1/2 ---------- Cups shredded carrots ( about 1 lb)\n1 --------------- Cup small marshmallows\n1/4 ------------ Cup pineapple (cut in 1\'2 inch pieces)\n1/4 ------------ Cup seedless raisins\n1/2 ------------ Cup shredded sweet coconut\n1/2 ------------ Cup mayonnaise\n1 --------------- Cup whipping cream (whipped)\n\nPeel carrots, Shred with coarse shredder into a mixing bowl. You can buy these alread shreded in the stores. Add marshmallows, pineapple, raisins and cocoanut. Toss lightly to mix. Combine the mayonnaise with the carrot mixture. Carefully fold in the whipped ceam.Serve in  crisp lettuce cups. Garnish top with additional cocoanut if desired. Serves 6 to 8. \nIf the carrots are very moist it may be necessary to reduce the amount of mayonnaise. This salad freezes nicely.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(329,'Bread','Bread --- Clastic Belgian Waffles','Faye Thompson','1 1/2 ----- Cups water\n2 1/4 ----- Teaspoons active dry yeast (one packet)\n3 ---------- Cups sifted all purpose flour \n1/4 -------- Teaspoon salt\n3 ----------- large eggs, separated & save 2 egg whites \n                  to beat seperate\n1/3 -------- Cup sugar\n8 ----------- Tablespoons unsalted butter-melted and \n                  cooled\n2 ----------- Teaspoons vegetable oil\n2 ----------- Teaspoons vanilla extract\n1 1/2 ------ Cups whole milk\n\nHeat 1/2 of the water to lukewarm, 105 to 110 degrees. Dissolve the yeast in the water with a pinch of the sugar from the recipe, let stand 5 to 10 minutes, until the mixture begins to foam.\n\nPut the flour and salt into a large bowl; stir to blend and reserve. Add the egg yolks, one of the egg whites, and remaining sugar to the yeast mixture; Stir to blend. Add the remaining water, milk, melted butter, oil, and vanilla; Stir the liquid mixture into the flour mixture and beat until the mixture is smooth.\n\nBeat the egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold the egg whites gently into the batter. Let the batter stand for 1 hour. Stirring ever;y 15 minutes. This mix will keep in the ref. For 2 to 3 days. Be sure  you put it in a container 3 times as large as mixture, it will rise and run over.\n\n Preheat your  waffle maker on setting recomanded by your waffle maker for gest results, do not open waffle maker during cooking process. Ge sure to select a waffle maker that will not stick. There are a lot of them on the market.\n\nBe sure when you are using yeast in any food not to add liquids hotter then what is called for in the mixture of the yeast. Anything to hot will kill the yeast. This is a be mistake people make in making bread with yeast.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(330,'Bread','Bread --- Ultimate Pancake','Faye Thompson','2 ---------- Cups original bisquick mix\n2 ---------- Teaspoons baking powder\n2 ---------- Tablespoons vegetable oil\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n3 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n1 ---------- Cup seltzer water\n2 ---------- eggs\n\nMix all ingredients until well blended. Pour slightly less than 1/4 cupfuls onto hot greased griddle. Cook until edges are dry. Turn; cook until golden. For thinner pancakes: increase Seltzer water. For blueberry pancakes stir in 1 cup blueberries. Chocolate chip pancakes: Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips. The above recipe well make about 14 pancakes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(331,'Candy','Candy --- Caramelize Pretzel Squares','Faye Thompson','2 ---------- Teaspoons butter, softened\n4 ---------- Cups pretzel\n2 1/2 ----- Cups pecan halves, toasted\n2 1/4 ----- Cups packed brown sugar\n1 ---------- Cup butter, cubed\n1 ---------- Cup corn syrup\n1 ---------- can (14oz.) sweetened condensed milk\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ---------- package (11-1/2 oz.) milk chocolate chips\n1 ---------- Tablespoon plus 1 Teaspoon shortening, \n                 divided\n1/3 -------- Cup white baking chips\n\nLine a 9 by 13 inch pan with foil; grease foil with butter. Spread pretzels and pecans on bottom of prepared pan.\nIn a large heavy saucepan, combine brown sugar, cubed butter, corn syrup, milk and salt; cook and stir over medium heat until a candy thermometer reads 240 degrees (soft ball stage). Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Pour over pretzel mixture.\nIn a microwave, melt chocolate chips and 1 Tablespoon shortening; stir until smooth. Spread over caramel layer. In microwave, melt baking chips and remaining shortening; stir until smooth. Drizzle over top let stand until set.\nUsing foil, lift candy out of pan;remove foil. Using a buttered knife, cut candy into 72 bite-size pieces.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(332,'Candy','Candy --- Coconut Creme Chocolates','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- jar (7 0unce) marshmallow creme\n2 2/3 ----- Cups flaked coconut\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n                 Dash salt\n1 ---------- 8 ounces milk chocolate chips\n1 1/2 ---- Teaspoon shortening\n\nIn a large bowl, mix marshallow creme, coconut, vanilla and salt until blended. Refrigerate, covered, at least 1 hour.\nShape mixture into 1 inch balls. Place on a waxed paper-lined baking sheet. Refrigerate, covered, for at least 3 hours. This is very important to get the balls cold, I like to put them in the freezer for a while.\nPut the chocolate in the  microwave, melt chocolate and shortening; take out and stir, put back in microwave and cook 2 more minutes. Stir until smooth. Dip coconut balls in chocolate; allow excess to drip off. Place on waxed paper; let stand until set. This makes about 2 1/2 dozen. 91 cal.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(333,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Caramel Corn','Faye Thompson','5 ---------- Quarts popcorn (popped)\n2 ---------- Cups brown sugar\n2 ---------- sticks butter\n1/2 ------- Cup white karo syrup\n1 ---------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n2 ---------- Cups roasted  peanutes (shelled)\n\nFirst pop your popcorn ( this should be about 3/ 4 Cup of raw popcorn) Do not use seasoned popcorn. \nMix brown sugar, butter, and karo syrup in a 2 1/2 quart saucepan. Bring to a boil and turn down on medium heat and let boil 5 minutes. Stir often. Remove from heat and add soda, vanilla, salt and peanutes. The soda will make the mixture rise and double in size. Have a large pan sprayed with cooking oil to mix the corn. Then spray  2 large pans 12 x 18 x 1 inch pans to cook the corn. Cook about 50 minutes in a 250 degree oven. Stir every 15 minutes. \n\nThis recipe can be used for Cracker Jacks and add all kind of goodies.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(334,'Miscellaneous','Miscellaneous --- High altitude cooking tips',NULL,'Water boils at a lower temperature (each 500-ft increase in altitude causes a drop of about 1° in the boiling point). For example, at 7,500 feet the boiling point will be 198˚.  Since it will not be as hot as it is at lower altitudes, you will have to boil it longer to achieve the same affect. \n\nBaked goods that include yeast or baking powder will rise faster which may sound good, but it\'s not. They will dry out. \n\nBoil things longer if you are at an elevation of 5000 feet or more.   \n\nOven temperatures are affected by altitude, so it is sometimes necessary to adjust the suggested oven temperature.  For batters and doughs, you should increase the temperature by 25 degrees Fahrenheit if you are at an elevation of 3500 feet or more. \n\nAdjust ingredients that cause your baked goods to rise.  Smaller pans work better at high altitudes. \n\nUse more liquids (including that used in rice, soups and vegetables) slightly to allow for longer cooking times. \n \nReduce baking powder \nFor each teaspoon, decrease by:\n3000 feet  1/8 teaspoon\n5000 feet  1/8 - 1/4 teaspoon\n7000 feet  1/4 teaspoon\n \nReduce sugar \nFor each cup, decrease:\n3000 feet   0 - 1 tablespoon\n5000 feet   0 - 2 tablespoon\n7000 feet   1 - 3 tablespoon\n \nIncrease liquid \nFor each cup, add:\n3000 feet   1 - 2 tablespoon\n5000 feet   2 - 4 tablespoon\n7000 feet   3 - 4 tablespoon',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(335,'Miscellaneous','Miscellaneous --- Keep Clothes From Fading',NULL,'2 gallons warm water\n2 tablespoon white vinegar\n1 teaspoon salt\nSoak for 2 hrs.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(336,'Sea Food','Sea Food --- Lemon - Dill Fried Bass','Faye Thompson','2lb bass filets\n2/3 cup lemon juice\n3/4 cup self-rising flour\n3/4 cup self rising cornmeal\n1 teaspoon dill weed\n1/4 teaspoon pepper\nOil for frying\nCut bass fillets into serving portions and place in a shallow dish. Pour lemon over fillets and let stand about one hour. Leave in refriguater turning once.\nStir together ingredients. \nCoat fish with flour mixture.\nFry in hot oil at 350 until lightly brown on both sides, 5-8 min.\n\nIf all purpose flour is used, add 1 teaspoon salt.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(337,'Salad','Salad --- Old Recipe For Potato salad','Faye Thompson','Don’t get too fancy with this! It\'ll taste better if you keep it simple. \nMake if for a crowd\nPrepare it a day in advance for flavors to blend in     \n 10-12 baking potatoes with salt with skins on.\nStick a table knife t0o check when done, don\'t overcook.\nBoil eggs (equal number to potatoes).\nLet both get cold. Never warm.\n\nWhen cold, slice potatoes about 1/4\" thick in quarters after skinning them.\nSlice eggs in egg slicer and then in quarters.\nAdd one whole celery bunch chopped fine as well as one white onion.\nMix all together.\nAdd one jar of mayonnaise--don\'t use diet. Fat tastes good!\nOne jar pickle relish. \nAdd a little plain French\'s mustard.\nAdd some sweet pickle juice if you have it.\nI don\'t add pepper but taste for salt, it usually needs a lot.\nPut in bowl and sprinkle paprika on top.\n\nTip: Mix potatoes and mayo and pickle relish and then start adding the celery and onions until it tastes right, add salt here too.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(338,'Entrée','Entree --- Talorni','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- clove garlic ( crushed )\n1 ---------- large onion ( chopped )\n1 ---------- green pepper (chopped )\n3 ---------- tablespoon olive oil\n1 ----------14.5 ounce can petite diced tomatoes\n1 ---------- large can whole corn\n1 ---------- Pound ground beef ( buy the best ground\n                 beef on the market)\n2 ---------- Teaspoons salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon black pepper\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon cayenne pepper\n1 1/2 -----Tablespoons olive oil\n1 ---------- can pitted olives ( chopped )\n1 ---------- 8 ounce package noodles ( medium width )\n1/2 ------- pound mild chedder grate cheese\n\nMince and fry garlic, onion and green pepper in olive oil.\nAdd tomatoes and cook 10 min.\nBoil noodles until tender.\nFry hamburger until it lightly brown\nadd salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper.\nAdd corn and olives ( include liquid from olives ).\nAdd cheese and cayenne pepper leave enough cheese to sprinkle on top.\nPour into 9 x 13 x 2 inch greesed baking dish\nBake 1 hr at 350. Covered.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(339,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Spicey Cabbage','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- Pound ground beef (buy the best grade of \n                 ground beef)\n1 ---------- medium onion (finely chopped)\n1/2 ------- bell pepper ( finely chopped)\n1 ---------- clove garlic, mashed\n1/2 ------- can cheddar cheese soup\n1/2 ------- can rotel\n1/2 ------- can stewed tomatoes (15 oz.)\n1 ---------- head cabbage, shredded\n1 ---------- Tablespoon black pepper\n1 ---------- Tablespoon salt\n\nBrown first four ingredients together in a dutch oven. Cook until the beef is done. Add soup, rotel and tomatoes, then add cabbage, salt and pepper. Cook on medium heat with lid. Stir often it seems to be easy to stick. Cook for about 30 minutes or until desired doneness,\nThe left over soup,rotel and tomatoes, add 1 pound of velveeta cheese and more 1 can of rotel and it makes a great cheese dip. You can melt cheese in microwave. The best chips you can buy is Tortilla Rounds (Mission)\n\nThis is a good for vegetarian diet. Just leave out ground beef.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(340,'Entree','Entree --- Cornish Hen With Honey','Faye Thompson','1/2 ---------- Cup honey\n1/4 ---------- Cup prepared mustard\n8 ------------ Tablespoons butter\n2 ------------ Teaspoons lemon juice\n1 ------------ Teaspoon salt\n2 ------------ Cornish hens or cut-up fryer.\n\nHeat ingredients to boil. Place chicken in a zip lock bag pour mixture over chicken: Let marinate one hour. Place chicken in a foil lined baking pan, Pour marinate over chicken, Place in a 350°F oven for 1 hour. Turn and baste several times. If chicken need to be more tender cover with foil and bake longer. This is good with rice or salad. Serves 4 to 6 peoole.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(341,'Entree','Entree --- 10 Can Chicken Casserole','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- large fryer, deboned and diced.\n1 ---------- can chedder cheese soup\n1 ---------- can  cream mushroom soup\n1 ---------- small can carnation evaropated milk\n1 ---------- can asparagus bits, drained  or whole\n                 asparagus choped in small pieces.\n1 ---------- can french style green beans, drained\n1 ---------- can sliced mushrooms\n1 ---------- small jar pimentos\n1 ---------- can water chestnuts, drained and sliced\n1 ---------- Can chow mein noodles or you can use dry \n                 chow mein noodles, just a handful or two\n2 ---------- Teaspoons salt\n1/2 -------  Teaspoon cauenne pepper or to taste.  \n2 ---------- cans of fried onion rings\n\nUse a 9 x13 x 2 inch baking pan or a 3 quart casserole dish. Mix all ingrdients together except onion rings. Top with onion rings. Bake 350°F oven for about 30 minites. This can be frozen and used later. This serves about 12 to 15 people.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(342,'Miscellaneous','Miscellaneous --- Rum substitute','Faye Thompson','1/4 ---------- Cup heavy cream\n1 ------------- Teaspoon rum extract\n\nThis is a substitute, in case you con\'t have Rum on hand.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(343,'Candy','Candy --- Millionaires','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- l4 ounce package kraft caramels\n3 ---------- Tablespoons vanilla extract\n1/3 ------- block paraffin\n1 --------- ( 9 ounce ) hershey bar\n2 --------- Cups chopped nuts, ( I prefer pecans )\n4 --------- Tablespoons milk\n\nMelt caramels, milk and vanilla in double boiler. Add pecans and mix well. Drop by spoon onto waz paper and flatten. Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler. Spoon onto caramel. When cool, turn over and repeat.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(344,'Cookies','Cookies --- Santa\'s Thumbprints','Faye Thompsoh','1 1/2 ---------- Cups butter flavor crisco\n1 --------------- Cup firmly packed brown sugar\n1 --------------- egg\n1 --------------- Tablespoon vanilla extract\n2 1/2 ---------- Cups quaker oats ( quick or old-\n                        fashioned),\n2 --------------- Cup all-purpose flour\n1/2 ------------- Teaspoon salt ( optional)\n1 3/4 ---------- Cups finely chopped nuts\n2/3 ------------- Cup fruit preserves \n\nHeat oven 350°F. Beat crisco and sugar until fluffy. Mix egg and vanilla; add combined oats, flour and salt. Mix well. Form one inch balls; roll in nuts. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Press centers with thumb; fill with perserves. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown. Remove to wire rack; cool completely. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(345,'Desserts','Desserts --- Rice Pudding','Faye Thompson','3 ---------- Cups cooked rice\n1 ---------- (14 ounce ) can eagle brand milk\n1 ---------- Cup sweet milk\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon nutmeg\n2 ---------- eggs\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nMix above ingredients, pour in a buttered casserole. Bake for about 30 minutes or until thick and light brown around edges.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(346,'Cookies','Cookies --- Hershey Candy Bar Cookies','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- Cup butter\n1 ---------- Cup flour\n1 ---------- Cup brown sugar\n1 ---------- egg yolk\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n1/4 -------  Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------- Cup nuts ( I perfer pecans ).\n4 ---------- hershey candy bars ( regular size )\n\nMix first five ingredients and bake in a 9 x 15 x 2 inch baking pan, for 20 minutes at 350°F. While hot. Spread Hershey candy bars over mixture and sprinkle nuts on top. Cut in size you perfer to serve.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(347,'Dip','Dip --- Popppy Seed Dressing','Faye Thompson','1/2 ---------- Cup mayonnaise\n2 ------------ Tablespoons sugar\n1 ------------ Tablespoon poppy seed\n1 ------------ Tablespoon lemon juice\n\nMix together. Serve as fruit dip/',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(348,'Dip','Dip --- Dip For Fried Mushrooms','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- Cup sour cream\n1/4 ------- Cup horseradish\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon salt\n\nMix and chill.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(349,'Dip','Dip --- Fruit Dip','Renee Rucker Clark','12 ---------- Ounces caramel candy\n2/3 ---------- Cup evaporated milk\n1/2 ---------- Cup small marshmallows\n\nMix and heat untilo melted. Serve as a dip for fresh fruit. I like to serve this warm.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(350,'Breakfast','Breakfast --- Sausage Pinwheels','Faye Thompson','2 ---------- Cups self- risen flour\n2 ---------- Teaspoons baking powder\n2----------- Tablespoons sugar\n1/4 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1/3 ------- Cup crisco\n2/3 ------- Cup 2 % milk\n1 ---------- Pound pork sausage ( hot or mild )\n\nCombine all ingredients except sausage. Mix to form a nice textured dough. ( I use a food processor). Chill dough for at least one hour. Roll out dough to a large sized rectangle. Spread uncooked sausage over dough. Roll up like a jelly roll. If you have trouble getting the dough to stick after you roll it in a roll, beat a egg white slightly and brush on the dough this works like a glue.(At this point sausage roll may be frozen). Slice into pinwheels 1/2 inch thick, and bake on a cookie sheet with a  side (so any grease will not get in the oven). Bake in a 375°F oven until light brown.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(351,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Calas    ( Creole Food)','Faye Thompson','2 ---------- Cups cooked rice\n2 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n2 ---------- Cups bisquick\n1/2 ------- Cup  evaporsted milk ( I perfer carnation)\n2 ---------- eggs\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n                 Peanut oil for frying\n                 powdered sugar and cinnamon.( I do not like \n                 cinnamon on the ones I have eaten)\n\nMix all ingredients together and drop by small teaspoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towel. Roll in powdered sugar or cinnamon and sugar. May be made the night begore, but cook and serve hot.½ ',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(352,'Beverage','Beverage --- Hot Spiced Tea','Bradgord Show Room','1 ---------- Quart weak tea\n2 ---------- ( 3 ounce) package strawberry or lemon jello\n1/2 -------  gallon boiling water\n6 ---------- cinnamon sticks\n12 -------- whole cloves\n1 ---------- pint water\n1 ---------- Cup realLemon juice\n3 ---------- Cups sugar\n1 ---------- large can pineapple juice\n1 ---------- quart water\n\nDissolve jello in boiling water. In separate pan. Simmer cinnamon and cloves in the 1 quart water. Then mix all the other ingredients Add more juice or water if you prefer. serve hot, but do not let boil. Serves 30.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(353,'Desserts','Desserts --- Deep Dish Apple Cobbler','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- box frozen Pillsbury pie crust ( 2 crust )\n\n10 ---------- Cups sliced peeled tart apples ( about\n                   8 medium )\n1 ------------ Teaspoon lemon juice\n1/4 --------- Cup sugar\n1/4 --------- Cup packed brown sugar\n3 ------------ Tablespoons all-purpose flour\n1 ------------ Teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1/2 --------- Teaspoon ground nutmeg\n1 ------------ Tablespoon butter\n1 ------------ egg\n1 ----------- -Tablespoon milk\n\nPreheat oven to 375°F. For filling, in a large bowl, toss apples with lemon juice. In a small bowl, combine sugars, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to apple mixture and toss to coat. Transfer to a 9 x 13 x 2 inches deep baking dish; dot with butter. \nOn a lightly floured surface, roll dough to fit top of pie. Place over filling. Trim and flute edges. In a small bowl, whisk egg with milk; buush over pastry. Cut slits in top. Bake 50 minutes or until crust is golden brown and apples are tender. Cool on a wire rack.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(354,'Candy','Candy --- Chocolate Covered Nut Balls','Faye Thompson','3 ---------- (16 ounces ) confectioners sugar\n2 --------- sticks butter ( 1/2 pound )\n1 --------- (14 ounce ) can sweetened condensed  milk\n1 --------- pound chopped nuts ( about 2 cups )\n2 --------- Cups angle flake coconut\n1 --------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n2 --------- 11.5 ounces milk chocolate morsels\n1/2 ------ pound paraffin\n\nMix first 6 ingredients. This is very hard to mix if you have a heavy duty mixer, I like to use the medal beater.When mixed , shape into small balls and place in the refrigerator to chill. This is importent, when you dip them in hot chocolate they will not come apart. Mix 2 packages of chocolate and 1/2 pound paraffin in a double boiler. Stir until smooth. I find it easier to leave top of double boiler over hot water while dipping candy balls. Dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper. Store in cool dry place in covered container. You can freeze them also.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(355,'Desserts','Desserts --- Blackberry cobbler','Faye Thompson','1---------- Quart fresh or frozen blackberries\n2 --------- Cups sugar (or to your taste)\n1/2 ------ Cup water\n1 --------- Package pillsberry frozen pie dough (2 crust ) \n                or you can make your own pie crust.\n6 --------- Tablespoons butter\n1/4 ------ Cup sugar\n\nWash berries and place in a saucepan with 2 cups sugar, Bring to a boil cook just enough to melt sugar. Pour 1/2 of the berries in a casserole, Take 1 pie crust cut to fit the casserole place over berries. Cut small slits in the crust just enough to excape hot air. Cut 3 Tablespoons butter in small pieces and put on top of crust. Sprinkle 1/8 Cup sugar over crust put in a 400°F oven until crust is brown. Take out of oven repeat the above steps and put back in oven to brown top crust. Other fruits may be used instead of blackberries, or you can use canned fruit, I do not like canned fruit as well, but frozen fruit taste is same as fresh fruit.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(356,'Cookies','Cookies --- Butterscotch Chip Cookies','Faye Thompsin','3/4 ---------- Cup white sugar\n3/4 ---------- Cup light brown sugar\n1 ------------ Cup butter\n2/3 ---------- Cup vegetable oil\n\n1 ------------- egg\n1 ------------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n3 ------------- Cups all-purpose flour\n1/4 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ------------- Teaspoon soda\n1/2 ---------- Teaspoon baking powder\n\n1 ------------- Cup oatmeal \n1 ------------- Cup corn flakes (crushed ) \n1/2 ---------- Cup coconut\n\n1/2 ---------- Cup black walnuts\n6 ------------- ounces butterscotch chips\n\nCream sugars, butter and oil. Add egg and extract. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Add to creamed mixture. Add oatmeal, corn flakes, coconut, then add nuts and chips, mix well. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet, press down lightly. Bake at 350°F until desired shade of brown. About 10 t0 12 minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(357,'Miscellaneous','Miscellaneous --- Sauteed mushrooms','Faye Thompson',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(358,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Cheese Bites','Faye Thomposn','2 ---------- sticks butter ( softened )\n2 ---------- Cups self risen flour ( I use W.R. )\n1 ---------- Cup sharpe chedder cheese\n1 ---------- Cup sour cream\n1 ---------- Teaspoon cayenne pepper\n1 ---------- mayonaise ( if it is to dry )\n\nMix all the above ingredients. I use my hands. Be sure to mix well. Drop in minature muffin pans sprayed with cooking oil. Do not fill more than half full. Take your fingers and press tops to smooth. They are better not so thick. Bake in a 350°F oven for 12 to 15 minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(359,'Bread','Bread --- Coconut Gread','Pat Neal\'','3 ---------- Cups  All-purpose flour\n2 ---------- Teaspoons baking powder\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon salt\n2 ---------- Cups sugar\n\n2 ---------- Cups vegetable oil\n4 ---------- eggs, lightly beaten\n2 ---------- Teaspoon coconut extract\n\n1 ---------- Cup buttermilk \n1 ---------- Cup flaked cocoanut\n1 ---------- Cup chopped pecans\n\nCombine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar. Set aside In a large bowl, combine eggs, oil and coconut extract. Add dry ingredients alterrately with buttermilk, Stir just until moistened. Fold in coconut and nuts. Pour into two 9 x5 x 3  inch loaf pans. Bake 1 hour in a 325°F oven, teat with toothpick. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan. Then cool on rack.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(360,'Entree','Entree --- Cheesey Rice','Bonnye Sisk','1 1/2 ---------- Cups uncooked rice ( cook as directed)\n1 --------------- large onion chopped\n1 --------------- 10 3/4 ounce can cream of chicken soup\n1 --------------- 10 3/4 ounce can chedder cheese soup\n8 --------------- ounces sour cream\n8 --------------- Tablespoons butter (melted)\n1 --------------- Cup mild chedder cheese ( shredded )\n1 --------------- 9 ounce ruffle potato chips ( crushed )\n4 --------------- Tablespoons butter\n\nMix onion, chicken soup, chedder soup, sour cream, butter,and chedder cheese in a  large bowl. Set aside. Take cooked rice and pour one half in a 9 x 13 inch greesed baking pan. Take cheese mixture and pour over rice. Take rest of the rice and pour over cheese mixture. Put potato chips over cheese mixture. Pour butter over potato chips. Bake in a 350°F oven for 45 minutes uncovered.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(361,'Entree','Entree --- Pork Chop Casserole',NULL,'4 ---------- pork chops, lightly browned\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- envelope lipton instant onion soup mix\n1 ---------- Cup uncooked long grain white rice\n2 ---------- Cups water\n1 ---------- Tablespoon butter\n\nIf the pork chops are large use a 9 x 13 x 2 inch casserole. Mix Rice, onion soup, salt and water in a bowl. Pour in casserole , place brown pork chops on top of rice, and dot with butter. Cover and bake 350°F degree oven for 60 minutes.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(362,'Pies','Pies --- Apple Pie In A Paper Bag','Faye Thompson','4 ---------- average size tart apples or 3 large ones. \n                 Peeled and sliced thin.\n1 ---------- unbaked 9 inch pastery shell\n1 ---------- Cup sugar\n1/8 ------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------- Teaspoon ground cinnamon\n1/2 ------- Cup plus 5 Tablespoons all-purpose flour, \n                 divided\n1 ---------- Tablespoon lemon juice\n1/2 -------- Cup firmly packed brown sugar\n1/8 -------- Teaspoon nutmeg\n1/2 -------- Cup butter\n\nPlace apples in pastry shell. Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, 5 tablespoons flour and lemon juice;\nsprinkle over apples.Combine brown sugar, 1/2 cup flour and nutmeg; cut in butter; lightly press mixture on apples. Place in brown paper grocery bag, securing tightly with paper clips or any wire handy.Place on baking sheet. Bake at 425°F degrees for 45 minutes. This makes 6 to 8 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(363,'Entree','Entree --- Country fried steak with gravy','Faye Thompson','8 to 10 ---------- Pieces of cubed steak ( about 2 1/2 \n                          pounds\n                          salt & pepper to taste\n1 ----------------- Cup flour\n1/2 -------------- Cup corn starch\n3/4 -------------- Cup buttter milk\n1/4 -------------- Cup vegetable oil\n1 ----------------- large yellow onion, sliced into thin rings\n1 ----------------- 14 oz. Can beef broth \n\nGeneously season the meat on both sides with salt and pepper. Place flour and corn starch in a resealable plastic bag, Dip steak in buttermilk. \nSeveral piece at a time. Shake excess and add to flour in plastic bag. Shaking to coat all sides. Place the flored meat on a piece of waxed paper next to the cooktop.\nPour the oil into a heavy flat bottomed skillet. Heat oil over medium-high heat for about 1 minute add the steak pieces. Brown meat on each side until crispy and brown, about 3minutes on each  side.If it want fit in skillet you may have to brown the meat in 2 batches.After browning, place in a slow cooker on high heat. Place the onions in the skillet where the meat was browned, cook until onions are translucent. Pour onions and oil over steak. Pour beef broth over steak and onions. Cook  about 1 hour.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(364,'Vegetables','Vegetables --- Best Squash Casserole','Jane Thompson','4 --------- Cups sliced yellow squash\n1/2 ------ Cup chopped yellow onion\n35 ------- round ritz crackers, crushed\n2 --------- Tablespoons butter\n1 --------- Cup shredded cheddar cheese\n2 --------- eggs beaten\n3/4 ------ Cup milk\n2 --------- Tablespoons butter\n1 --------- Teaspoon salt\n1/2 ------ Teaspoon black pepper\n2 --------- Tablespoon butter\n\nPreheat oven to 400 degrees. Place squash and onions in a large skillet over medium heat. Saute in 2 tablespoons of butter about 5 or 10 minites until tender. Drain well, and place in a large bowl. In a medium bowl, mix together cracker crumbs and cheese. Stir half of the cracker mixture into the cooked squash and onions. In a small bowl, mix together eggs and milk, then add to squash mixture. Stir in 2 Tablespoons melted butter, and season with salt and pepper. Spray a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with cooking oil, and spread mixture in the pan.. Sprinkle with remaining cracker mixture, and dot with 2 Tablespoons butter. Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned. Uncovered.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(365,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Corn Dip','Jane Thompson','4 ---------- Mexican-style corn (drained)\n5 ---------- green onions chopped\n1 ---------- 8 ounces sour cream\n3/4 ------- Cup mayonnaise\n10 -------- ounces shredded chedder cheese or 2 cups\n1 ---------- Teaspoon ( Slap ya Mama ) Cajun seasoning\nOptions\n1/4 -------- ounce can diced green chiles, drained\n1 ----------- Jalapeno pepper, chopped\n\nMix and refrigerate. 12 servings.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(366,'Appetizers','Appetizers --- Pineapple Cheese Ball','Faye Thompson','2 ---------- 8 ounce packages cream cheese\n1 ---------- 15.5 ounces crushed pineapple, ( drained)\n2 ---------- Cups pecans, (chopped)\n1/4 ------- Cup bell pepper, (chopped)\n2 ---------- Tablespoons onion, (finely chopped)\n1 ---------- Tablespoon seasoning salt\n4 ---------- Tablespoons sugar\n\nIn medium bowl mix cream cheese with pineapple until smooth. Stir in galf of pecans and other ingrdients. Shape into ball or 2 small balls and roll in remaining pecans. Serve with triscuits or sciables crackers. (Can be frozen).',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(367,'Dip','Dip --- Panchio\'s Dip',NULL,'1 ---------- 29 ounce can tomatoes\n3 ---------- jalapeno peppers\n1 ---------- Med onion\n1 ---------- Tablespoon garlic powder\n1 ---------- Tablespoon accent seasoning\n1 ---------- Teaspoon cumin seed\n                 salt to taste\n2 ----------- Tablespoons veg. oil\n\nChop tomatoes, pepper and onion until very fine. Add all spices and bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat and let cool to serve. I also like to serve warm.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(368,'Entree','Entree --- Yumasetti','Amish  recipe','1 1/2 ---------- pounds ground beef ( best grade )\n1 --------------- med to small onion (diced small)\n1 --------------- 8 ounce package (egg noodles)\n1 --------------- Cup canned blackeyed peas (undrained)\n1 --------------- can cream of mushroom soup (10 3/4 oz).\n1 --------------- can cream chicken soup (10 3/4 oz.)\n1/2 ------------ Cup sour cream\n5 --------------- bread slices, toasted and cubed\n1 --------------- Cup shredded cheese of your choice\n\nPreheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a large casserole dish and set aside. (9 x 13)\nIn a large skillet, cook the beef and the onion over medium heat. Remove from the heat when the beef is browned. Drain the grease and transfer the meat mixture to a large bowl. Cook the egg noodles in salted water, according to the package directions, until tender. Drain well. Add the noodles, peas, mushroom soup, chicken soup, sour cream, and bread to the meat mixture. Stir until all the ingrdients are well combined. Transfer the mixture to the prepared casserole dish. Bake for 20 minutes uncovered, then top with cheese, and bake 10 more minutes covered  until the casserole is bubbling and the cheese is melted.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(369,'Cookies','Cookiies --- The Best Sugar Cookie','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- Cup powdered sugar\n1 ---------- Cup granulated sugar\n1 ---------- Cup butter softened\n1 ---------- Cup vegetable oil\n2 ---------- Teaspoons vanilla extract\n2 ---------- large eggs\n5 ---------- Cups all-purpose flour\n1 ---------- Teaspoon salt\n1 ---------- Teaspoon baking soda\n1 ---------- Teaspoon cream of tarter\n\nPreheat oven 350°F\n     In a large bowl, cream together the powdered sugar, granulated sugar, butter, oil, and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add the eggs and beat until evenly incorporated. In a second bowl, sift together the flour, salt, baking soda, and cream of tarter. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture, stirring until well combined.\n    Form the cookie dough into balls 1 1/2\'\' to 2\'\' in diameter and place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Flatten the balls using the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar. Or just plain. Try to get a glass that has a pretty decoration on the bottom. Bake 15 to 18 minutes, until they ore golden brown.Allow cookies to cool 2 minutes on the baking sheets before removing. Transfer the cookies to wire rack to cool completely. Cookies may then be frosted, if desired. Use what ever frosting you perfer.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(370,'Cookies','Cookies --- Thimble Cookies','Faye Thompson','1 ---------- Cup butter ( 2 sricks ), softened\n1/2 ------- Cup sugar\n4 ---------- eggs\n1 ---------- Teaspoon vanilla extract\n2 ---------- Cups all - purpose flour\n1/2 ------- Cup jam, any flavor of your choice, you can \n                 use chocolate chip or candies.\n\nPreheat oven to 325°F.\n     In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar until well blended. Beat in the eggs and vanilla. Work in the flour until a firm dough forms. If the dough seems too sticky, Let it chill for a couple of hours in the refrigerator. \n     Form the dough into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Use a clean thimble to press a hole in each cookie. If the dough is still sticky put a little flour on your hands and the thimble. If you don\'t have a thimble use a spoon or your thumb to make a hole. Fill the hole with a small amount of jam. Bake until the edges of the cookies are golden brown and the jam begins to bubble, about 25 minutes.\n     Cool the cookies on a wire rack or a plate and then put into containers. These cookies will stay fresh for up to 5 days.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(371,'Pies','Pies --- Smicker Pie','Faye Thompson','4 ---------- ounces whole pretzel sticks, finely ground in \n                a food processor or blender\n1/2 ------- Cup unslted butter, melted\n1/2 ------- Cup creamy peanut butter\n1/2 ------- Cup caramel sauce\n6 ---------- full size snicker bars, roughly chopped\n8 ---------- ounces milk chocolate chips\n1 ---------- Tablespoon canola oil\n\nHeat oven to 350°F.\nIn a medium bowl, combine ground pretzels, melted butter, and a pinch of salt. Press mixture into the bottom of a 9 inch pie pan and bake 8 minutes. Refrigerate 45 minutes.\nHeat peanut butter in the microwave until warm and spreadable. About 1 minute. Carefully smooth warmed peanut butter evenly over bottom of pretzel crust. Refrigerate pie 30 minutes to set.\nMeanwhile, warm caramel sauce in the microwave oven, and allow to cool a few minutes. Remove pie from refrigerator, then sprinkle chopped snickers over peanut butter layer and drizzle caramel sauce over top. Refrigerate pie and additional 10 minutes to set \nHeat chocolate in microwave in 20-seconds increments until almost completely melted, about 1 minute. Stir in oil until combined. Drizzle chocolate over caramel layer. Refrigerate pie until chocolate is firm, about 1 hour. Before serving, remove pie from refrigerator and warm to room temperature.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(372,'Desserts','Desserts --- Ice Cteam Bars','Faye Thompson','20 ---------- oreo cookies chopped fine\n3 ----------- Tablespoons butter melted\n\n1 ----------- Quart cookie dough ice cream softened\n1/2 -------- Cup caramel ice cream topping\n2 ----------- Cups whipped topping\n1/2 -------- Cup milk chocolate cut in shavings\n\nLine a 9x9 inch pan with foil. Mix cookies and butter , press in bottom of foil pan. Spread softened ice cream over cookies. Swirl caramel ice cream topping over ice cream,Then spread whipped cream over caramel.  Then spread the final layer of milk chocolate shavings. Freeze for 3 hours. Take out cut in bars and serve.',NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00');
